INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (26, 'Night into Day', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '  You know, what they say is really true.  Being up late at night is just \r\nas good as being up during the day.  I have successfully migrated back to \r\na non-nocturnal schedule.  I guess you would call that dayurnal or \r\nsomething.  But that\'s what I am now.   I regular nine to fiver (I\'m awake \r\nduring those hours, don\'t even talk about work, cause I don\'t).  I went to \r\nbed at 8:00 pm last night and awoke fully rested at 5:45 am.  Do the math, \r\nthat\'s a lot of sleep.  And I didn\'t really notice the difference of being \r\nawake during the day.  Sure I can bother my friends at work now, rather \r\nthan waking them up at night but that\'s not a great perk really.  So, as I \r\nsit in my room with a sheet over the window, my music up loud, with the \r\nair-conditioner blazing, I think, ahhhh daytime is great. :>\r\n\r\nin the words of Kurt Cobain:\r\n\r\nSell the kids for food\r\nWeather changes moods\r\nSpring is here again\r\nReproductive glands\r\n\r\ngood night.\r\n', 'Sleeping normally again. No more late nights.\r\n', 20000822145156, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (22, 'Bhaskar Sinha vs. Ted Nugent (dork from Kiss)', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '\r\n  Bhaskar was protesting at Nieman Marcus (Fur is bad), as usual this \r\nweekend, and Ted Nugent (some ancient pro-gun backwards ass rocker from \r\nthat sold out commercial entity known as Kiss) came up to the protesters \r\nand began spitting on them.  So Bhaskar and his group, follow him trying \r\nto make a peaceful citizen\'s arrest.  People in this country have the \r\nright to protest.  You may not be aware of this, Nugent, you backwards ass \r\npunk.  So Nugent physically assaults Bhaskar and carries him to the cops.  \r\nThe cops, typically arrest the wrong man, and Bhaskar gets to spend \r\nanother night in jail.  That\'s some fucked up shit.\r\n\r\n  Well, the good part is, Nugent is famous, so the whole thing has blown \r\nopen like gangbusters in the media, check out some of these links:\r\n\r\nBe sure to visit Netscape and vote for Ted in the poll, TED SUCKS!\r\n\r\nRelated Coverage:\r\n<UL>\r\n<LI><a \r\nhref="http://www.vh1.com/thewire/news/article.jhtml?ID=754">VH1 Coverage\r\n</a><LI><a \r\nhref="http://netscape.digitalcity.com/sanfrancisco/issues/main.dci?\r\npage=nugent">Netscape Netcenter Coverage, with a poll!</a>\r\n<LI><a href="http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?\r\nfile=/chronicle/archive/2000/08/02/MN88753.DTL">SF Chronicle Coverage</a>\r\n<LI><a href="http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?\r\nfile=/examiner/archive/2000/07/31/NEWS4480.dtl">SF Examiner Coverage</a>\r\n<LI><a href="http://www.indiawest.com/cgi-bin/news/viewNews.cgi?\r\narticle=965098525&Department=Coverpage">India West Coverage</a>\r\n</UL>\r\n\r\n\r\nRIGHT ON!\r\n', 'Ted Nugent from Kiss attacked Bhaskar.... Netscape has a poll, vote for TED!', 20000804143958, 'normal', 'http://netscape.digitalcity.com/sanfrancisco/issues/main.dci?page=nugent');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (25, 'I like my sense of humor and I think I should sell it on Ebay', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '  I was out mini-golfing with some of my mates and their ladyfriends the \r\nother day when I realized what a great sense of humor I have.  I would say \r\nthat it is very dry, sprinkled with sarcasm, in a sort of sardonic \r\nsensibility about it.  Wait, I don\'t even know what sardonic means,\r\n\r\nsardonic - disdainfully or skeptically humorous : derisively mocking\r\n\r\nYeah, that\'s pretty much what I thought.  And I have pretty good timing, \r\nlike Carson.  The memory and the speed to recall info and bring it out at \r\nthe right time. \r\n\r\nAlthough sometimes my humor is too wacky for others or my quotes too \r\nobscure but I get by. \r\n\r\nAnother thing I like about me is I just read a book cover to cover in one \r\nsitting.  About a boy by Nick Hornby.  It was really good.  It was by the \r\nsame guy who wrote High Fidelity, a movie I\'ve seen 4 times and already \r\nordered the DVD. :>\r\n\r\nEnough self appreciation.  It\'s time for Narcissus to go to sleep. \r\n\r\nGood night all.', 'Funny. Sarodonic. l8r.', 20000815041558, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (27, 'Caller ID for Girls', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '  Ok, I had a thought.  Everybody loves caller ID.  It\'s great, a little \r\nbox next to your phone and after the phone rings two times, you know who\'s \r\ncalling you. It\'s great.\r\n\r\n  Well, I had a better idea.  Caller ID for girls.  Here\'s how it works, \r\nyou get a girl on the phone and you talk to her for about two minutes.  It \r\ndoesn\'t work right away, you\'ve got to keep her on the line while it \r\ntraces her, kinda like those cop movies where they do the trace and they \r\nhave to keep the bad guy on the line for a while before they can find out \r\nwhere he is.  So the box hooks up with a chip implanted in her brain, or \r\nperhaps it would just analyze her speech frequencies or something.  So, \r\nthen it reports to you what you need to know.\r\n\r\nI figure it would report something like this:\r\n\r\n   <B>Really Interested</B> (your box is probably broken)\r\n   <B>Interested</B>\r\n   <B>Possibly Interested</B>\r\n   <B>Just a friend</B>\r\n   <B>Interested in using you for free stuff</B>\r\n   <B>Interested in treating you poorly then dating your friends</B>\r\n   <B>Would rather eat shards of broken glass</b>\r\n   <B>If you\'d like to make a call please hang up and try again</B>\r\n\r\netc, etc.....\r\n\r\nHopefully it will be out this spring retailing for 49.95, operators are \r\nstanding by.  It\'s 3:44 am! WOOOO.', 'all the questions answered. no fuss, no muss.\r\n', 20000824033849, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (28, 'Ightetto.com - Ebonics, Movies, and More!', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'Ighetto.com is pretty damn cool.  \r\n\r\nI espically recommend the Delta Commercial, and the Star Wars Gangsta rap.\r\n\r\nthey be fly, you mutherfucka.\r\n\r\n', '', 20000831080904, 'net_interest', 'www.ighetto.com');
