INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (30, 'Mr. Andrew Horatio Duong, Superstar', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '<I>And now, an AUTHENTIC fictional interview with Andrew Horatio Duong, \r\ncreative director at the State hornet, a local rag newspaper.  (Note that \r\nI do not bother to mention their website as it is not worth mentioning, \r\nseeing how it has been down all weekend because the pathetic rebus monkeys \r\nthey have hired to work on it do not understand why you shouldn’t \r\nexperiment on a “live” server.)  Andrew is the star of many direct to \r\nvideo pornography titles, such as “I put feces in the paper” and “Horny \r\ncocks with Nuts!”  He is currently in negations with David Letterman to \r\nreplace Paul Schaffer and his book “Andrew Horatio Duong, the story of a \r\nman” will be out this fall from Random House.</I>\r\n\r\n\r\n<B>Thunt.net: </B>So Mr. Duong, I understand that you are responsible for \r\nall of the artwork and layout of the State Hornet newspaper.\r\n\r\n<B>Mr. Duong: </B>Yes, that is true.\r\n\r\n<B>Thunt.net:  </B>Do you enjoy your work at the State Hornet?\r\n\r\n<B>Mr. Duong: </B>I have never found work more fulfilling than this.  I \r\nmean, I treasure all of the days that I am forced to stay at the office \r\nuntil midnight on a Monday evening rather than spending it out with my \r\nfriends.  I have never worked anywhere that would crucify you at the drop \r\nof the hat and then sing your praises the next day.  It is a radical kind \r\nof working environment.\r\n\r\n<B>Thunt.net: </B>I assume you are referring to the new, ehhm, leadership \r\nof BBB?\r\n\r\n<B>Mr. Duong: </B>Exactly.  They say that a jack-of-all-trades can teach \r\nan old dog new tricks, but that is not entirely true in this case.  I \r\nmean, sure at first it seemed as though what they say was absolutely true, \r\nbut in the end it has all come to pass.\r\n\r\n<B>Thunt.net: </B>That’s just what I’ve heard.\r\n\r\n<B>Mr. Duong: </B>Yup, the street never lies.\r\n\r\n<B>Thunt.net: </B> True that.  So how is your interaction with the other \r\nsections of the paper been, since you took ultimate creative control of \r\nthe paper?\r\n\r\n<B>Mr. Duong: </B> Well, I like to have a little motto, it helps me sleep \r\nat night.  And that is: I’m responsible for the graphics and the layout, \r\nnothing else.  If I didn’t have that I’d probably locked up in the nuthouse or something.\r\n\r\n<B>Thunt.net: </B> I assume you’re referring to the former editor of the \r\nHornet.  I understand that after the destruction of his car at the frail \r\nand demonic hands of mother nature, he was forced into “early retirement” \r\nand is now resting comfortably. \r\n\r\n<B>Mr. Duong: </B> I understand he is greatly enjoying the “good life” \r\nwhile chowing down on their delicious macaroni and cheese, now with Yellow \r\nDye #5.\r\n\r\n<B>aNDY!: </B> I smell crackers!\r\n\r\n<B>Thunt.net: </B> Who are you?  We are in the middle of an important \r\ninterview here.\r\n\r\n<B>aNDy!: </B> I am ANdY!  I rule!  YEAH!\r\n\r\n<B>Thunt.net: </B> Are you feeling ok Mr. Duong?\r\n\r\n<B>Mr. Duong: </B> Uhhh, yes, I feel \r\n\r\n<B>AnDy!: </B> like a fucking madman and shit! Bring it on you wretched \r\nbitch.  I heard you were an incompetent cocksucker, but to be fired from \r\ncorporate America and to have to beg for your job back while retiring from \r\nthe sorority with your big fucking shirt, man you should step back bitch!\r\n\r\n<B>Mr. Duong: </B> As I was saying, I feel fine.\r\n\r\n<B>AndY!: </B> That’s great it starts with an earthquake.  I am the ripper \r\nman.  I am the one who is called I am.  Feces! FECES! NUTS! Fucking ‘a \r\nman.  I’m going nuts being trapped in this square.  Use soap! USE SOAP!\r\n\r\n<B>Thunt.net: </B> Mr. Duong if you can not contain yourself, I will be \r\nforced to end this interview.\r\n\r\n<B>Mr. Duong: </B> It’s ok, I’m a fucking nutbar.  Bring on with the \r\nquestions bitch! I never sleep. I’m mad like that. Bring me in you fucking \r\nwhore.  Layout layout layout.  I am the one for that shit.  All I see is \r\nbig P small p.  That’s what I live.  I live layout.  Apartment, don’t got \r\nit.  House, no way.  Car, sold it for another quark license.  It’s all \r\nI’ve got left is the whining and the screaming and the incompetence.  I \r\njust can’t go on with this much longer.  What is left for me in this foul \r\nworld but the production of this bullshit douche rag of a paper.  Oh the \r\nhumanity how can there be any rest for the man who holds up the soul of \r\nthe world.  I travel the land with my soul on the souls of my feet. \r\nWithout earth and life I only see death and hate.  Without love I only \r\nfeel for beveling and debossing.  Kerning and kerning and kerning, towards \r\nvictory.  America demands a winner and I personally fucking hate losers.  \r\n\r\n<B>Thunt.net:</B> Thank you Mr. Duong, for your precious time.  Good night \r\nAmerica, just sign and return those pledges to uphold the constitution and \r\nwe will shortly return to your regularly scheduled broadcast.\r\n\r\n', 'an interview with Andrew Horatio Duong', 20000904190856, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (39, 'Olympic athletes get ambitious condom allowance', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '', 'That\'s a lot of condoms.', 20000909134424, 'net_interest', 'dailynews.yahoo.com/h/nm/20000908/hl/condoms.html');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (33, 'A very special audio interview & Inside the Newsroom', 'Thomas Hunt & Rev. Jim Jones', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'Good evening boys and girls we\'ve got a special treat for you today on \r\nThunt.net, a real audio interview with a very special member of the State \r\nHornet staff.  Please click the link below to listen, and if you\'re in the \r\nState Hornet office, I suggest you don headphones.... Enjoy!\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<a href="audio/interview.ram">click to listen</a>\r\n<a href="http://www.real.com/player/index.html?src=000831realhome">\r\n<img src="http://images.real.com/pics/real/download_player.gif" border="0">\r\n</a>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n<hr>\r\n<br>\r\n<b>Inside the Newsroom</b>\r\nBy <b>Rev. Jim Jones</b>\r\n\r\nFirst I got in trouble for the kool-aid and then for touching the children,\r\nbut when I get in trouble for reading a website, that’s ridiculous. \r\nIt’s not like I am asking people to drink cyanide or anything.\r\n\r\n“Don’t log onto thunt.net or else?\r\n\r\nOr else, what? It’s a free country and we can log onto any website we want.\r\n\r\n“We accept the fact that we have to sacrifice a whole semester in detention\r\nfor whatever it is we did wrong, but we think you\'re crazy for making us\r\nwrite a newspaper telling you who we think we are. You see us as you want \r\nto see us, in the simplest terms, in the most convenient definitions. But \r\nwhat we found out, is that each one of us is a brain, and an athlete, and a\r\nbasketcase, a princess, and a criminal. Does that answer your question?”\r\n\r\n   Sincerely yours, \r\n\r\n      Rev. Jim Jones\r\n\r\nps: Guyana is a beautiful place, come join us…\r\n    It is beautiful here…\r\n', 'audio interview. rich media. experience the madness.', 20000907001142, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (61, 'The State of the State University', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '	It is crowed out there.  Way too crowded.  I don’t know whether \r\nit’s just this year or if it’s been every year and I just haven’t noticed \r\nit, but Sac State is fucking crowded.  I was walking around the computer \r\nlabs after teaching my class today and I was not practically but actually \r\ntripping over people.  It was like a third world country or being in L.A.  \r\nAnd what’s worse is all of these people are talking.  The endless chatter \r\nof students filled the usually stoic computer lab.  And it’s a wonder that \r\npeople are complaining about lab service as I watched my fellow lab \r\nassistants scramble to help the five students pounding on the desk for \r\ntheir print outs as the dot matrix printer clicked away in the background \r\nspewing out never ending sheets of C code and the occasional web page.  \r\nHow can the lab assistants hope to keep up with this kind of demand?  How \r\ncan our school continue to accommodate far more students than the \r\ndesigners of this school intended?  The complaints about parking are never \r\nending and never going to end at this rate.  I wouldn’t be surprised if I \r\npicked up a copy of the school newspaper ten years from now and the \r\nheadline still read: “Huge Parking Problem on Campus” or perhaps something \r\nwitty like “Campus Clogged with Congestive Traffic.”  Ok, so it’s not that \r\nwitty but what school newspaper ever is.  The frantic sprint to increase \r\nenrollment and gain the oh so important dollars placed upon each head by \r\nthe state continues each year like a never-ending fraternity rush week.  \r\nSomehow, they continue to hide the problems of congestion, parking, \r\ntraffic and lack of teachers every year as they continue their quest for \r\nincreased enrollment.\r\n	Did I mention that I’m teaching a class?  That’s right, both I and \r\nmy roommate Matt Brown are lab instructors for Computer Science 8 – \r\nExploring the Internet for the goodly Professor Floyd LeCureux.  It’s just \r\nanother plank in the administrations plan to expand the number of students \r\ntaught without the costly hiring of new faculty (applicants in the \r\ncomputer science field being virtually non-existent due to the \r\npreternaturally good job market).  Therefore, Dr. LeCureux teaches the \r\nclass for all of the students in lectures televised on Cable TV, while \r\nMatt and I answer their questions in class, grade their assignments and \r\nhelp Dr. LeCureux create the assignments for them to do.  Sure, it’s a \r\ngreat way of expanding one professor and allowing him to teach a great \r\ndeal more students than the traditional method, but it is another one of \r\nthe brilliant schemes of the administration to expand enrollment.  \r\nSomething needs to be done about this hegemonic educational policy.  \r\nBecause it’s only a matter of time before Sac State becomes so crowded \r\nthat you will have to buy a seat license to have an actual seat in your \r\nphilosophy class with a real teacher and those who didn’t buy the licenses \r\nwill have to watch from another lecture hall on campus.  Of course, it \r\nwill be presented in Dolby digital surround sound, with a 16x9 letter-\r\nboxed picture to ensure a true THX quality-learning environment.\r\n', 'Sac State is over crowded.\r\nA "thought" piece.\r\n', 20000926225832, 'normal', '');
