INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (131, 'Thunt.net 1, Statehornet.com 0', 'thunt@thunt.net', '', 'Let\'s do a quick check.  \r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.statehornet.com">www.statehornet.com</a> - Down\r\n  - gives apache error.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.thunt.net">www.thunt.net</a> - Up\r\n  - still up, in fact, you\'re reading it right now.\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\nCorporate Check:\r\n\r\nPeople employed by Thunt.net: 1\r\nPeople employed by CampusEngine.com: 0\r\n\r\nAnother victory for Thunt.net\r\n\r\nIt’s gloating time ladies and gentlemen.  CampusEngine is bankrupt.  They \r\nnever had a product and I always said that they didn\'t.  The StateHornet\'s \r\nwebsite is down and they\'ve already decided to repeat their mistakes by \r\ngoing to another outside company instead of trying to talk to the Computer \r\nScience Department, or the new Web Certification Program and get some \r\ntechnical people.  The StateHornet\'s leadership is so foolish, that I \r\ncannot but help to be reminded of the classical failures of History: The \r\nMaginot Line of the French, Betamax and Sony, Napoleon attacking Russia in \r\nthe Winter, Hitler repeating Napoleon\'s mistake and of course the be-all \r\nand end-all of historical knowledge: never get involved in a land war in \r\nAsia.  One learns these simple things as a History major.  Obviously, no \r\none at the Statehornet has heard of any of these things, nor will they try \r\nto learn about them.\r\n\r\nLet\'s see.  If I was negotiating with Mars, and I did not speak their \r\nlanguage, I could go home after the negotiation thinking that I had just \r\ngotten a great deal even though I had signed away all rights to the \r\nEarth.  This is very similar to the State Hornet\'s situation.  They don\'t \r\nhave any technical staff members.  The closest thing they have to a \r\ntechnical staff member doesn\'t understand how to register a domain name, \r\nmuch less HTML.  But despite their lack of knowledge, their "business-\r\nsavvy" leader has negotiated a deal with <a \r\nhref="http://collegepublisher.com">CollegePublisher.com</a>.  This is most \r\nimpressive.  Considering they have already signed away their domain name \r\nto college publisher, despite their "6-week trial" status.  Like it\'s a \r\ntrial, HA!, in the middle of the semester they are going to want to change \r\nweb companies. The very idea of them wasting their precious time (during \r\nwinter break), that they could be using to rebuild their site and hiring \r\nsome technical people, they are squandering it, assured by this novelle-\r\nCampus Engine that everything will be ok.  I\'m sure it will be.  Just like \r\nthe American Navy on December 6th, 1941 sleep soundly StateHornet.com, \r\nbecause the worst has yet to begin.\r\n\r\n<i>Editor\'s Note: Thunt has called their leader "business-savvy", \r\nobviously being satirical.  Although the leader called itself "business-\r\nsavvy" in the Sacramento Bee, that can only be interpreted as sarcasm. \r\nThanks for reading Thunt.net!</i>\r\n\r\n', '', 20001221172151, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (132, '2001 in 2001', 'Thomas Hunt', '', '\r\nImagine if you will.  New Years Eve in the year 2000.  Two men set out on \r\na quest.  A quest to watch a film.  A quest that cannot fail.  Failure is \r\nsimply not an option for these two men.  They are on a voyage, a voyage to \r\na cabin.  A cabin that has a VCR.  A VCR that may or may not have RCA \r\ninputs.  A VCR that may or may not work.  A limited number of power outlet \r\nplugs perhaps.  These contingencies have been planned for.  \r\n\r\nLet us examine the contents of the bag.  1 stereo + video RCA cable, of a \r\ndecent length.  1 extension cord with three outlets and no ground.  One \r\nextension cord with three outlets and a ground.  1 Toshiba DVD player.  \r\n1 "Kubrick Collection" copy of 2001, on DVD of course.  And finally, \r\none "backup" copy of 2001 on Videotape.  As I said earlier, failure is not \r\nan option.\r\n\r\nAnd now to the particulars of the situation.  They have arrived at the \r\ncabin and things are not looking good.  The VCR does have RCA inputs but \r\nthere seems to be something wrong with it as the movie is playing behind a \r\nblue screen and rotating on and off the screen.  Fortunately, our heroes \r\nhave a backup plan.  However, something far more sinister is afoot...\r\n\r\nThe partiers at this New Year\'s Eve party seem to be another obstacle to \r\nthis quest.  As they are all female.  That\'s right oh my brothers and only \r\nfriends, all female.  Let us recount a few of the things that Thunt knows \r\nabout females: 1. Chicks dig flowers.  Ok, so, that was only one thing, \r\nbut that\'s what Thunt knows.  Regardless, Thunt was about to learn one \r\nmore thing: Chicks do not dig Sci-Fi.  It\'s not that they don\'t dig it or \r\nthey couldn\'t learn to dig it or that they aren\'t some genetic misfits who \r\ndo not represent the rest of their race, it just seems that when you \r\nmention the title like 2001: A Space Odyssey the room turns harsh and \r\nwhile hopes were previously high they now seemed to be thoroughly dashed \r\nupon jagged rocks like a hippy on an acid trip watching the Titanic sink.  \r\nOr perhaps it wasn\'t science fiction.  It could be some kind of Anti-\r\nKubrick kick due to the nudity and crazy sex parties in Eyes Wide Shut, or \r\nsome kind of throwback anger about the rape scenes in A Clockwork Orange.  \r\nDespite these reasons for female anger, Kubrick remains, in this author\'s \r\neyes to be without a doubt, one of the best American filmmakers ever \r\n(period).\r\n\r\nThese were indeed dark times for our intrepid heroes who simply wished to \r\nwatch 2001 in 2001.  But their leader knew that the best thing to do was \r\nto wait.  Perhaps their animosity would diminish at the evening dragged on \r\nand the cosmopolitans flowed like water under a bridge.  Perhaps a liberal \r\namount of kindness and salsa mixed with cream cheese would sooth the anger \r\nof these savage beasts and allow our brave heroes a chance to experience \r\nthe HAL 9000 in the year for which his story was named.\r\n\r\nTheir leader was right, for the most part.  After the clock struck twelve, \r\nthe party poppers popped and the evening began to wind down to it\'s \r\ninevitable sleepy conclusion, our hero gave a sign to our other hero and \r\nthe tape began upon its merry way through the video cassette player.  Thus \r\nSpake Zarthursta, the famous chords of Strauss begin as the sun shone over \r\nthe monolith.  Just then, the outrage of the beasts began to be heard, \r\nmatching in time with the grunting of the primordial humans.  "Turn it \r\noff", "Put on Austin Powers", "Can we watch this tomorrow?", "Pour me \r\nanother drink".  It was at this time that we were to find out who was \r\ntruly a hero willing to be martyred for his cause, and who was a \r\ndaytripping rebel, only along for the ride.  One of our brave heroes \r\nshowed himself to be not so brave and retreated with his wife to bed, \r\nleaving our brave leader and hero among heroes to deal with the jeers and \r\ncatcalls of these vicious sirens.  But unlike this quasi-hero, the true \r\nhero would not break.  He turned the volume low and waited for the effects \r\nof the potions to take effect and return these naysayers to their full and \r\nupright sleeping positions.  Our hero bided his time well, explaining that \r\nthe bit with the monkeys was only the beginning of the picture.  And that \r\nthe picture would make sense when one committed oneself to it\'s dark cold \r\ntunnel and emerged upon the other side.  These comments aligned with the \r\nbeautiful Blue Danube Waltz relaxed these unrelentless firedragons and \r\nthey began to sleep soundly on their respective couches.  Leaving our hero \r\nundisturbed as he once more enjoyed Stanley Kubrick\'s immortal vision of \r\nthe future.  A vision entitled: 2001: A Space Odyssey.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', 20010102122700, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (133, 'A Response From The Quasi-Hero', 'John the Quasi-Hero', 'thehistorydude@hotmail.com', '   The new year has come and I failed our fearless leader our mission to \r\nwatch a movie that needed to watched by all this New Years Eve "2001: A \r\nSpace Odyssey".  I realize my failure ruined a once in a lifetime chance \r\nto watch Kubrick\'s classic sci-fi epic, but I must defend myself.\r\n\r\n   First, I had a sinking feeling that the company me and our fearless \r\nleader would be keeping would be anti-Kubrick and all female.  This was \r\none of the reasons that I asked Mr. Hunt to accompany me, because he does \r\nneed more exposure to the other sex, and EVERYONE needs to be exposed to \r\nKubrick.\r\n\r\n   Second, I did get the movie, along with Mr. Hunt to the cabin and the \r\nmovie was played.  I realize that Mr. Hunt would have liked a companion \r\nduring the movie, and I realize that I was too intoxicated to watch the \r\nmovie, but never the less the movie was shown and therefore our mission \r\nwas not a complete failure.\r\n\r\n   Third, I AM MARRIED.  My wife had been sick, and she needed my company \r\nto fall asleep, besides I am COMPLETELY WHIPPED. I felt that if I did not \r\ngo to bed with my wife at that time, the possibility of me getting laid in \r\nthe near future would have been slight.\r\n\r\n    I do apologize to Mr. Hunt on my lack of backbone but I feel the \r\nreasons that I have given are acceptable, especially #3, and I know that \r\nmany of you out there would have done the same.  I hope that Mr. Hunt has \r\nnot lost faith in me for I am willing to redeem myself at anytime, besides \r\nit will be 2001 for a whole year and the movie will be around for much \r\nlonger than that.\r\n\r\n<I>Editor’s Note: The capital letters on the words “COMPLETELY \r\nWHIPPED” were placed there by the author, not by the editor.  \r\n\r\nAlso, the Editor would like to take this moment to remind the world that \r\nthe fearless leader was not the only one enjoying 2001 that night.  Across \r\nthe galaxy, in Southern California, Brother Brown and Brother  Kemper were \r\nalso enjoying the picture.  On a projector and with a crowd of scientists \r\nno less.</I>\r\n', '', 20010103203145, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (135, 'Quixotic in 2001', 'Conscientious Objector', '', 'I was also present at the New Year’s Eve Party and I would like to respond \r\nto Thunt’s shameful article.  \r\n\r\nThunt may call himself a hero, but clearly he falls quite short of that \r\nlofty title.  In the case of his article “2001 on 2001”, Thunt is nothing \r\nmore than a hero of ludicrous insults.  For Thunt to call me and my \r\nfriends savage beasts and vicious sirens is an outrage.  If anyone was \r\nsavage or beastly at that party, it was Thunt with his incessant whining \r\nabout how no one wanted to watch his “great” (his opinion, not mine) \r\nmovie.  We came to the cabin to have fun, not to watch some cinematic \r\ndinosaur of 1969.  I think that Austin Powers is a hilarious movie and I \r\nenjoy watching it, even when I am a little tipsy.  Thunt is wacked, he \r\ndescribes himself as a hero on a quest, but at the cabin he was more like \r\nDon Quixote ignorantly and foolishly attacking windmills.  And his \r\nsidekick Sancho Panza was none less impressive in his actions I must say.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, Thunt’s comments about women and science fiction are \r\ncompletely random and unfounded.  I and my friends frequently enjoy \r\nscience fiction, just not on New Year’s Eve when we’re trying to have a \r\ngood time.  I don’t know how many of you are into science fiction but \r\ntypically it isn’t very uplifting to the human spirit (as most of them \r\nrevolve around the human race destroying the earth in some way.)\r\n\r\nThunt is despicable pond scum and the next time I see him, I plan to kick \r\nhim square in the nutz.\r\n\r\n<I>Editor’s Note: It’s a good thing we have a non-biased editor here at \r\nThunt.net to ensure that you people get the truth, the whole truth and \r\nnothing but the truth, because there is no way that Thunt would have let \r\nthis article through.  The part where she calls 2001 a cinematic dinosaur \r\nwould have probably set him off ranting for 2-3 hours easy.</I>\r\n', '', 20010104222628, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (136, 'Thoughts on a Friday', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'Do you ever think back to when you were a kid and you were first told of \r\nwhat Communist Russia was like.  I recall hearing about a test that you \r\nwould have to take and this test would tell the government what your \r\naptitudes were in subjects such as Math, Science, Writing, Russian, etc.  \r\nAnd based upon this test you would be sent to a school to learn how to do \r\nbetter what you do well or you were sent to a farm to raise crops, or sent \r\nto the city to be a bathroom attendant.  Now, I have to say that I found \r\nthis to be an interesting system.  It seemed sensible to assign those good \r\nat science to the field of scientists.  Although I must say it is \r\negotistical for me to believe that my test results would place me into one \r\nof the schools of higher learning, but surely the readers of Thunt.net \r\n(yourselves being made up of 87% college attendees or graduates) must \r\nunderstand the reasons for my and assumedly your positive outlook for the \r\ntest results.  Personally I can’t see myself or any reader of Thunt.net \r\nhanding out towels to strangers in a bathroom somewhere.  It’s just not \r\nplausible.  \r\n\r\nAnyway, today I was thinking about the stuff I want to do and perhaps it \r\nwould be easier I could just walk downtown to some Ministry of Writers, \r\nDirectors and Novelists and apply to take the test.  It just seems nice \r\nthat if you want to do something you take the test, if you fail, I guess \r\nthat’s a major setback and you have to regroup, but if you passed, you \r\nwould be on a government tested and approved fast track towards your \r\ndesired profession.  Not that I’m any kind of communist, but sometimes it \r\nis discouraging to sit on the floor and think about where your future is \r\ngoing to go, what you are going to be, what you are going to do, what you \r\nwant to do and not know.  The alternative system seems to provide at the \r\nvery least: certainty and job security.  That sounds pretty good to me \r\nright now.\r\n\r\n<I>Thunt is a former columnist for the State Hornet, a world-famous movie \r\ncritic and frequently tries to use the nonsense word apon instead of the \r\nproper upon.</I>\r\n', '', 20010105162324, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (137, 'A Siren He Said', 'Richelle', 'chillibn6@hotmail.com', '2001 in 2001 was an idea all right. \r\n\r\nAn idea from our so called heroes who were on a mission. A mission to \r\nwatch their acclaimed video. Well, I must say that I had a mission too. \r\nAnd, unlike our two heroes (I use the term hero loosely),my mission, and \r\nthe mission of the other so called "sirens", was definitly accomlished. \r\nFor the new millineum, we sirens had a fantastic plan. Our plan was to get \r\ntotally wasted amoungst our best of friends. Most guys would find the \r\nentire situation extremely interesting I am sure. We were, after all, \r\ncelebrating with boos and controlled party substances. Not to mention the \r\nfact that there were 5 partying women and only two so called male heroes. \r\n(1 not counting the very married and EXTREMELY WHIPPED hero.)So, sounds \r\nlike a pretty good ratio huh? It is very obvious to me that SOMEONE (no \r\nnames mentioned, Mr. Hunt) might have had a better time if he had stopped \r\nthinking so much about his mission, and had just gone with the flow of \r\nthings. \r\n\r\nI personally have nothing against SciFi, or Kubrick for that matter. \r\nHowever, to stand up for myself and the other 4 beautiful, intelligent \r\nwomen that were with me, the movie definitly did not go with the jovial \r\nspirit of the evening. I know that I speak for the rest of us when I say \r\nthe we had a great time goofing off and keeping the party going upstairs, \r\neven after our hero was watching his cherished video. All that we wanted \r\nwas to be happy and have fun. We are reasonably young after all. So, Mr. \r\nHunt, I am thrilled you got to watch 2001 in 2001. Maybe the next get \r\ntogether we all have will be more entertaining to you. Just be watchful of \r\nwho you call beasts next time, k? \r\n\r\n', '', 20010106205544, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (138, 'Laments of a Video Game Junkie', 'Thomas Hunt', '', 'With the recent release of the X-Box and the clamor of the populace to \r\npurchase the Playstation 2 I find myself thinking about video games, and I \r\ncannot help but name them as one of the foremost distractions of my life.\r\n\r\nWhen I was a child, I read constantly.  Right up until the release of the \r\nNintendo Entertainment System.  Before the Nintendo, video games were a \r\nonce in a while thing.  A fun way to spend a few quarters at the local \r\nChuck-E-Cheese’s, but not a full-blown lifestyle obsession.  But when I \r\nfinally convinced my parents to purchase the brand new Nintendo as my \r\nChristmas present everything changed.\r\n\r\nWhen I think about it now, I can’t fathom how much time I spent playing \r\nvideo games.  Until my parents banned Nintendo during the week and \r\nsubjugated my obsession to a weekend passion I played every waking \r\nminute.  Little did I know that this glowing box was destroying my social \r\nskills one level at a time.  Not to say that I stopped socializing or that \r\nI can’t socialize today, but I think that I would be better equipped if I \r\nhadn’t been strapped to the glowing box day and night.  I did have \r\nfriends. They also played video games.  Of course, when I describe playing \r\nvideo games, I don’t mean just playing occasionally for fun, I’m \r\ndescribing total emergence in the subject matter.  We bought strategy \r\nguides, read Nintendo Power, agonized over what new games to purchase and \r\nfrequently combined our skills to slay the water demon in level 8.  \r\n\r\nIn the end, I look back to see what the years of gaming has accomplished.  \r\nThe unfortunate answer is not a whole lot.  Certainly, I have beaten the \r\nLegend of Zelda (1,2,3), the Super Mario Bros games (1,2,3,4) and dozens \r\nof other popular titles.  I have achieved near dominance at some sports \r\ngames so that no non-computer opponent will dare to face my team on the \r\nfield, but what does all of this amount to in the real world: nothing.  \r\n\r\nBut I suppose all of the hobbies of childhood pale when confronted ten to \r\nfifteen years down the line.  I’m sure some of you regret or lament the \r\namount of time spent killing imaginary dragons in D&D.  Others probably \r\nfear what the perfect body of Barbie had done for their self-esteem and \r\nworldview.  There are many good things about childhood, but sometimes you \r\nfind yourself looking back, wishing that you had spent that time more \r\nproductively.  But if you did, you probably never would have experienced \r\nchildhood.\r\n\r\n<I>Thomas Hunt is still a vicious killer in Half-life and proudly states \r\nfor the record the only thing resembling a video game installed on his \r\nsystem is Chessmaster 8000.</I>\r\n', '', 20010107194555, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (139, 'Pillsbury Doughboy vs. The Internet', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '', '', 20010121115518, 'net_interest', 'www.salon.com/tech/log/2001/01/19/pillsbury/index.html');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (140, 'A Goodbye Letter (or Ryan is scared shitless about tomorrow)', 'Ryan Anne Polli', 'il_disegno@yahoo.com', 'At 21 years old I have successfully put off the\r\nremoval of my wisdom teeth, something my dentist has\r\nbeen urging me to since 1997. I actually had a date to\r\ndo it then but backed out because I had to watch the\r\npaint dry or something of serious urgency like that.\r\nSo now, I am T minus 15 hours away from my appointment\r\nwith my friend Anesthesia and just slightly freaked\r\nout at the thought of having someone rip pieces of\r\nbone out of my skull. So, in the possibility that I am\r\nthe one in 968,392 people in this world to not come\r\nback from the happy gas I thought I would write a\r\nlittle something to be forever etched in the cached\r\npages of the world wide web and this fantastic site\r\nthat our friend Thunt has built. Here are my thoughts_\r\nlaugh and/or learn. These are in no particular order\r\nof importance.\r\n\r\n- Lemon covered with salt is not a good snack.\r\nI recently discovered (yesterday) that my better half\r\nmight possibly be crazy. At a dining excursion he had\r\na lemon on his plate, doused it with salt and ate it.\r\nHe didn\'t seem to mind it... it sounded neat. I should\r\nhave known. better_ but who am I to talk. Ask Endean\r\nand he_ll tell you that I combine fruit and meat as an\r\nappetizer. \r\n\r\n- Kharma is a bitch.\r\nI am happy with the knowledge that the people in my\r\nlife who have fucked with me and those close to me\r\nwill get it in the end... you know who you are and you\r\nknow I am right.\r\n\r\n- There is life without frosted flakes\r\nHard to believe but it is true. This is only knowledge\r\nbecause being on the road in the summer when all your\r\nmoney is gone you find that a box of cereal goes a\r\nlong way to replace meals before your next paycheck.\r\nMilk not included.\r\n\r\n- There are places not to get drunk.\r\nArizona, Santa Rosa (but not like there is anything\r\nelse to do) and well I don’t really remember the\r\nother place.\r\n\r\n- Alora Blum is an awesome person.\r\nShe gets props because of all the things that I have\r\never done in my life (proud and not so proud) Alora\r\nhas always been there. She is the only one who kicked\r\nit with me in the lodge when I broke my wrist\r\nsnowboarding, she defended me when I was stone drunk\r\nand passed out on New Years 2000, and she even helped\r\nme hail crazy people from the freeway to tow my truck\r\nout of the dirt. Everyone needs an Alora Blum in their\r\nlives.\r\n\r\n- "Brother, if you can\'t paint in Paris, you better\r\ngive up and marry the bosses daughter."\r\n\r\n- Everyone has a theme song. Whether it changes from\r\nyear to year or day to day_ know it and own the CD.\r\nThose who know me best know me as the Dixie Chicks\r\nsong Sin Wagon. Give it a listen and you will\r\nunderstand why. Music (and I am not talking about the\r\nMadonna CD) is a fantastic release for anyone. If you\r\ndon_t like music, you must not have a soul.\r\n\r\n- Silent Horizon kicks ass.\r\n‘nuff said. Well, not to mention their bass player is\r\nfreakin’ hot.\r\n\r\n-Long stories and articles get boring.\r\nSo I hope to see you all at the right end of the\r\ntunnel. Man this is going to suck.\r\n', '', 20010121195108, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (141, 'This Just In! (gerth & award)', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'The President of Sac State just won an award!  I am so proud I just had to \r\npop on and tell you all!  Be sure you check it out.  It also mentions the \r\nState Hornet, the newspaper that hopefully I’ll be working for/with next \r\nsemester! KICK ASS!\r\n\r\nCheck it out at <a \r\nhref="http://www.usnews.com/usnews/issue/000103/03john.htm">US News & \r\nWorld Report\r\n</a>', '', 20010123141719, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (142, 'Mornings Ruminations', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'Corl has dropped.  I’m happy.  This will give me another chance to get \r\nin.  I originally picked the stock at 3 a few months ago and it recently \r\nhit an all time high of 44.  Course, I wasn’t in on it, but now that it’s \r\nback down to 13, I might be able to get in on the next ride up.  That \r\nwould be nice, then I could use the money to buy:\r\n\r\nDV Imac.  Looks pretty neat.  Stupid looking box computer, but let’s face \r\nit, I’m attracted by the theory of having a Word/Netscape machine that I \r\nwould never have to rebuild and I would never ever open up.  Also the \r\nprospect of no more video capture, just direct input with firewire is very \r\ndroolable.  Sure, it seems like I’m a sell out, but I would still own a PC \r\nor two.\r\n\r\nCompliments.  I received the best compliment ever from my boss the other \r\nday.  When I was telling them how I liked the idea of the IMAC because I’m \r\nsick of knowing too much about PCs, he said “Well you are anti-\r\nestablisment enough to do it”.  Isn’t that great?  So, I think the whole \r\nthing is pretty much wide open now.  Espically since the IMAC comes with a \r\nmodem and a network card and it would emmulate windows so I could run \r\nAdvanced Disk Catalog and some others of my PC favorites.\r\n\r\nWelcome to the new page.  This is our first shot into the dark.  Hopefully \r\nit will grow.   I wish you and yours the best during this holiday season.  \r\nWith any luck we won’t go back to living in tribes in a few days, course I \r\nwouldn’t mind that much either.  I think I would be much more appreciated \r\nin a tribal environment.  Good night, and Godspeed.\r\n\r\n', '', 20010123141802, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (143, 'Rebel with a cause: Bhaskar Sinha', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'original time: 03-20-00, 11:43 am\r\n\r\nI would like to give credit today to my friend, Bhaskar Sinha, animal \r\nrights activist. While the rest of us toil at colleges Bhaskar has dropped \r\nout of his to follow his heart, not his wallet or dick, reasons the rest \r\nof us think about dropping out for. Last I heard from him Bhaskar was \r\ninterning for IDA (In Defense of Animals) in San Francisco. San Francisco \r\nis a special place Bhaskar tells me, because the people are excessively \r\nliberal, so the court system will not even take any cases of civil \r\ndisobedience to the juries because they would never convict them. This \r\nmakes San Francisco a perfect battleground for the cause of animal rights. \r\nWith Neiman-Marcus right downtown, and the fur trade running strong, \r\nBhaskar has found himself a niche right in the heart of the protest and he \r\nis using it, to the fullest extent. \r\n\r\nBhaskar is pretty hardcore. Here is a recent quote from the San Francisco \r\nExaminer:\r\n\r\n"I support any nonviolent action taken on behalf of fur-bearing animals," \r\nsaid Sinha, who belongs to the Coalition to Abolish the Fur Trade. "Thirty \r\nbroken windows is nothing compared to the 40 million animals that are \r\nkilled every year for frivolous luxury products."\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?\r\nfile=/examiner/hotnews/stories/28/vandalism.dtl">\r\nRead the article</a>\r\n\r\nI like the second half. It is a perfect sound byte.\r\n\r\nWell Bhaskar, we salute you. \r\n\r\nExpect this to be updated as soon as I find more articles and hopefully a \r\npicture of the bald-headed one himself.\r\n\r\n', '', 20010123141813, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (144, 'Oh brave new world, with such people in it.', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'original time: 04-13-00 10:31 pm\r\n\r\nTen minutes ago I was standing in line at Safeway. In front of me stood \r\ntwo male blonde tall guys buying two six pack of cheap looking beer in \r\nbottles. Sadly, I overheard their conversation.\r\n\r\nDork #1: "When they say a stock goes down twenty percent, does that mean \r\nthe same as if it went down twenty percent the day before?"\r\n\r\nDork #2: "No man, it\'s a different ammount each day."\r\n\r\nDork #1: "No, what I\'m saying is if it goes down five percent, that\'s not \r\nthe same ammount as if it goes up five percent."\r\n\r\nDork #2: "Yes it is."\r\n\r\nDork #1: "No it isn\'t. If it goes down five percent from 7.00, it\'s \r\ndifferent than if it goes up five percent from 5.00."\r\n\r\nAnd so on and so on. Both of them just not quite understanding the concept \r\nof percentages. A high school math concept. And these people are obviously \r\nold enough to buy beer. I live in the same zip code as these people. I\'m \r\ndisgusted that they even breathe the same air as I do. It\'s fucking \r\naweful. It\'s a good thing I don\'t carry a weapon with me, because I \r\nseriously contemplated just walking up behind both of them, drawing a \r\nglock and double-tapping both of them to the head right there, paying for \r\nmy groceries and leaving.\r\ns and leaving.\r\n', '', 20010124080459, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (145, 'Success of the Praetorian Guard', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'The Praetorian Guard was assigned to guard the Emperor\'s personal\r\nsecurity in the Roman Empire.  Here are a few of their greator\r\nsuccesses.\r\n\r\n\r\nTiberius (14-37 CE) <I>presumably poisoned by Caligula, his successor</i>\r\n\r\nCaligula (37-41 CE)\r\n     <I>Highlights of his reign: Incestuous relations with his sisters, \r\nlaughable military campaigns in the north, the building of a pontoon \r\nbridge across the Bay at Baiae, and the plan to make his horse a consul</I>\r\n\r\n<B>Death:</B> A conspiracy led by the Praetorian Guard.  Aparently \r\nsupported by the senate as well.  Might have had the support of Claudius, \r\nhis successor.\r\n\r\nClaudius (41-54 CE) <I>presumably poisoned by Nero, his successor</i>\r\n\r\nGalba (68-69 CE) <I>murdered by the Praetorian Guard</I>\r\n\r\nDomitian (81-96 CE) <I>Assassinated by M. Cocceius Nerva, A senator</i>\r\n\r\nCommodus (180-192 CE) <I>Assassinated</i>\r\n\r\nPertinax (180-192 CE) <I>Assassinated by the Praetorian Guard</i>\r\n\r\nCaracalla (211-217 CE) <I>Assassinated by the Praetorian Guard</i>\r\n\r\nGeta  (211 CE) <I>Murdered by Centurions</i>\r\n', '', 20010124080504, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (146, 'Single people are the strongest people in the world.', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'original date: 04-16-00 2:21 am\r\n\r\nI know a lot of people in co-dependant relationships and relationships \r\nthat are quickly on the way to the heights of co-dependance. You know the \r\ntype. The kind that are never seen seperate. The kind that constantly make \r\nout in public. Etc, Etc. \r\n\r\nWell, I got to thinking, how noble it is to be single. I come home each \r\nday to a completely empty house. Each night I sleep in a completely empty \r\nbed. I tell my day to myself. No one else is around to care. Good day, bad \r\nday, it\'s up to me to resolve it personally before I drift of unto the \r\nslumber of wretched sleep. I eat alone, unless you count the television as \r\na counterpart. No one cares what I wear or if I bother to shave.\r\n\r\nAll of these feelings of lonelyness, and yet there are thousands of single \r\npeople out there. When I find myself plagued by these feelings, I find it \r\na wonder that the suicide rate is so incredibly low. I would expect \r\nsomething like 50%. Anything lower than that reeks of delusionality on a \r\nmassive scale.\r\n\r\nI mean, so what if most single people I know constantly or semi-constantly \r\nwhine about how it\'s fucking impossible to find anyone worth talking to, \r\nlet alone dating. I find it amazing that there are so many of us left out \r\nthere, just walking around, living our lives, and never ever giving up.\r\n\r\nUpside of this article: I find it insightful and am going to include it in \r\nmy novel notes.\r\n\r\nDownside of this article: It sounds suicidal and now a bunch of people are \r\ngoing to bother me with annoying, "life is worth living" e-mails. Gotta \r\nlove that.\r\n\r\n', '', 20010124080508, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (147, 'Chaos on a Monday', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'Welcome back.  I hope you had a nice weekend.  I suppose I did.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n2:30 – listening to offspring again.  Reading brunching shuttle cocks, \r\nthinking about buying a new dictionary.  I own a blue felt pen and a \r\ndigital camcorder, does this prove omnipotence?  Grammer is a joke.  He \r\ndid a voice in Toy Story 2, funny, good.  \r\n\r\n2:33 – still offspring, they say that the truth is that crime does pay.  \r\nHow punk of them.  I almost believe them.  \r\n\r\n2:34 – thirsty.  I want a diet coke.  Will try to contact God.  Hey GOD! I \r\nwant a diet coke! How about some service down here?\r\n\r\n2:35 – No response from God, we’ll see if I ever shop here again.\r\n\r\n2:37 – 8 dollars, 2 movie stubs, 17+ free dvd rentals in my wallet, we \r\nmight be able to fix this coke problem.\r\n\r\n2:38 – how can I tell when users are going to ask me a question, they just \r\nseem to have this lost deer look on their face.  Usually they don’t know \r\nhow to turn on the monitor.  I hate that.  Damn users.  Some of them don’t \r\nknow if they’re allowed to use this lab, they look around and notice that \r\nI have authoriti, but they don’t realize I don’t care.  Nor should I have \r\nto.\r\n\r\nThere is a pencil on my desk named “MONGOL 482”.  It must have some \r\nsignifigance.  I’m going to spell check this so I’ll probably end up \r\nspelling signifigance right, isn’t that neat?  \r\n\r\n2:39 – Pepsi one. To buy or not to buy.  That is the question.  Whether it \r\nis nobler in the mind to save 1.25 or to drink pepsi.  Let’s see what \r\npepsi.com has to say.\r\n\r\n2:40 – Pepsi is telling me all about their “star-studded (is that really \r\nhow you spell that? How lame!)  into “New Generation” advertising”.  Pepsi \r\nbought sports heros, music icons, and film and television stars.  That’s \r\nneat, they should collect them all.  How is this selling me on the \r\nproduct.  Personally I have little or no interest in Pepsi History.  Could \r\nI get a job and become a proffessional Pepsi scholar?  \r\n\r\n2:45 – No more offspring, their rendition of feelings is at first \r\nenjoyable because they changed the words but at times it is too grating.  \r\nOn to the classics, REM – Up…\r\n\r\n2:46 – desperation setting in.  I’ll ask jeeves what pepsi tastes like to \r\nsee if he can help me make my decision.\r\n\r\nI’ve found Mike and Jo Ann Vath (of Apple Valley Minnesota)’s facinating \r\npage about their pepsi collectables.  When I put a logo on my webpage \r\nclaiming that I’m a member of the “PEPSI COLA COLLECTOR CLUB” I hope that \r\none of you will have the good sense and decency to shoot me in the fucking \r\nhead.  Who are these people?\r\n\r\nThe pepsi people tell me to “Have a Pepsi Day”.  These people are wackos.  \r\nRemind me never to visit Minnesota.  Now that’s two states I don’t want to \r\ngo to, Texas, because of Varsity Blues (if you’ve seen the film, you know \r\nwhat I mean), and now Minnesota, because of these pepsi freaks.  \r\nFrightning.  Also I suppose I don’t’ want to go to Fargo, North Dakota, \r\ncause it looked fucking cold, and wherever the hell they shot Deliverance, \r\nthat was a little weird, “you sure do have a purdy mouth”.\r\n\r\n2:54 – Thirst has broken me, I must have pepsi one, I will return.  I hope \r\nyou guys will be ok without me.\r\n\r\nAh, Pespi One, how do I describe thee:\r\n\r\nFirst my mouth is hit with the cold\r\n\r\nThen the back of my throat feels the liquid\r\n\r\nThe the roof of my mouth is electrfied with the joy of the carbonation\r\n\r\nThen down my throat it goes and I am left with the taste in my mouth\r\n\r\nKind of a brown, carmely type sugary taste\r\n\r\nThen Burp!\r\nahhh, the armoma floats through my mouth as my body does discharge it’s \r\nexcess gas built up by this strange carbonation.\r\n\r\n2:57 – I think I’ll call Ryan, Brian and Lisa now.  L2 and I recently \r\nfilled up their answering machine.  I wonder if they’ve checked it yet.\r\n\r\n3:00 – they aren’t back yet. Ahahahaha. Their answering machine is still \r\nfull. \r\n\r\n3:07 – my hand hurts, I wish I had my squezzy ball with me.\r\n\r\n3:11 – Trendyness, listening to Third Eye Blind. Trendy, but not bad, esp: \r\nMotocycle drive by.  Why do I still enjoy taking phones apart, at my age, \r\nreally.\r\n\r\n3:35 – my pepsi bottle is empty.  Why do they have to make them so small.  \r\nNot enough caffine, thinking about sleep.\r\n\r\n3:37 – some asshole is printing multiple copies.  Damn I hate that.\r\n\r\n3:50 – when did real player become so worthless, I just tried to watch a \r\nfew episodes of family guy to burn up the rest of my time, and it crashed \r\ntwice.  I’m downloading some new one, but I’ll bet it’s the same.  Fucking \r\nbastards.\r\n\r\n3:51 – I’m going to start work on some new french fries.\r\n\r\n3:52 – irony continues, as the installer for real player crashes.\r\n\r\n4:16 – I get tired, this article ends.\r\n\r\n', '', 20010126083603, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (148, 'Happenings and detonations', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '<B>I. Detonations</B>\r\n\r\nI started this article by writing the Happenings (or the work that I’ve \r\ndone recently to add some new toys to thunt.net) but it turns out you’re \r\nprobably all more interested in the battle royal that’s going down on the \r\nthunt.net message board.\r\n\r\nI don’t know who the mysterious author is who writing angrily on the \r\nmessage board.  But I’ve got to tell you I find it incredibly entertaining \r\nand I hope he or she keeps it up.  His/her recent comments about Ryan \r\nEndeeean are pretty damn funny.  There’s something about the phrase "my \r\npencil-neck is so far up my superior\'s ass that I can suck her dick" that \r\nI just fancy so.  It’s good to a phrase that so deftly attacks two people at the \r\nsame time.  My only regret is that I’m not behind this recent rash of \r\ncomments.  So, regardless of your views, my hat is off to you sir or madam \r\nfor spicing up the message board and raising up some controversy and \r\nmystery.\r\n\r\n<B>II. Happenings</B>\r\n\r\nI wanted to write a brief message out to all you Thunt.neters outlining \r\nsome of the new features I’ve recently implemented on Thunt.net.  They \r\naren’t much, but I thought I’d drop you all a line and let you know what’s \r\nup.\r\n\r\n<B>Thunt.net 2.0 (simplicity)</B> - I’ve adapted the new thunt.net code to \r\nallow you to surf thunt.net the classic 2.0 way.  Look for version 1.0 to \r\ncome along soon.\r\n\r\n<B>Thunt.net - State Hornet Style</b> - Now that the business-savvy State \r\nHornet has decided to sign with yet another corporation, I’ve launched \r\nThunt.net - State Hornet Style.  It’s a parody of the old statehornet.com \r\nwebsite packed with, you guessed it, the content of Thunt.net. (expect \r\nthem to attempt to kick me out of school again for this.  Also they’ll be \r\nquite mad to think that I’m allowing you to check out the new ISPI \r\ngenerated <a href=http://www.hornetonline.com>www.hornetonline.com</a>)\r\n  \r\nDamn it’s ugly and template-like.  But you’ve gotta respect the hornet for \r\nspending so much time and using the mighty marketing forces of \r\nCampusEngine to market statehornet.com to turn around and change their \r\ndomain name.  Maybe I should change this site’s name to thuntnetonline.net.\r\n\r\n<B>Quick Recap of other features</B> - Remember you can always sign up for \r\nthe Thunt.net mailing list, that will send you an automated message \r\nwhenever thunt.net is updated.  It’s the best way to keep up on what’s up \r\nat thunt.net, without doing any work. Also remember that we have a site \r\nsearch here at thunt.net (thanks to Matt).  The site search includes a \r\noffensive picture that those who understand satire will find funny.  Also \r\ntry searching for fuck.  You can pull up most of the archive that way.  \r\nAdditionally we have the submit a story button that allows you to write \r\nfor thunt.net.  And finally the Email story to a friend feature which \r\nallows you to easily send an article on thunt.net to your friends, or your \r\nenemies or whatever.\r\n\r\n', '', 20010126084805, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (149, 'Number One', 'Ain', 'ainvar@thunt.net', 'original time: 04-10-00, 7:03 pm\r\n\r\nStandard Disclaimer: The views and opinions at Thunt.net are views and \r\nopinions.  If they offend you, then FUCK OFF!  Thank you.  – Thunt\r\n\r\nYes boys and girls, not a single one of you know me.  In fact, I’m willing \r\nto bet that you don’t give a shit.  Thirdly, I don’t give a fuck\r\n\r\nFuck You\r\n\r\nNow that we got those beginning pleasantries out of the way, I might as \r\nwell introduce myself.  I am nobody.  Fuck you again.\r\n\r\nWell, now that’s a fine introduction, someone tell me how great I am.\r\n\r\nOk, Now the answer to the question I know that not a single person gives a \r\nflying monkey fuck about.  “What in hell is this webpage about?”\r\n\r\nIts really really REALLY easy for me to tell you.  Lucky answer is!------ \r\nWhatever in hell I want it to be.  Sigh, Honest, ill get more original as \r\nI write more posts.  Right now I\'m tired, have way to many term papers to \r\nwrite, and well, Fuck you.  \r\n\r\nBasically, This web page will be about Life.  Guess who’s life its about.  \r\nGuess.  Please?  Doh, well, I’ll tell ya what.  It’s not about my life.  \r\nAnd it’s not about yours.  It’s about nobody’s life. Therefore, since this \r\npage is about nobody, I have free reign to do whatever in hell I want.  I \r\nget to make shit up.  You won’t know the difference.  And guess what….(I’m \r\nsupposed to make a point here, but hell, I’m not going to.)\r\n\r\nJust as general topics to shoot off, this page could possibly be about \r\nGames.  Tekken in specific, and any online role-playing game that I’m in \r\nthe mood to bitch about.  This page COULD also be about the Internet in \r\ngeneral, and the stupid people we all get to meet and fuck around with.  \r\nThis page COULD also be about college life, just because I go to some \r\ncollege, in some city that’s not really special.  Finally, This page COULD \r\nbe about be about life, drugs, sex, beer, alcohol, woman, men, bitches, \r\ncrap, Some stupid ass motherfuckin British dude, some monkey fuck named \r\nPaco (had to get a Mexican name in here somewhere) some girl that just \r\nhappens to be in my life, and some girl that I happened to know Living in \r\nsome other part of the country.  Plus, if I didn’t mention it here, well, \r\nI can put it on this page anyway.\r\n\r\nWell, Gosh, wasn’t that fun.  Lets keep this simple.  I’m a New Yorker.  I \r\ngrew up knowing exactly 1 Asian kid.  This girl was a genius, and in fact, \r\nuntil moving to some other rat nasty place, I thought all Asians were \r\nintelligent.  God I crashed hard when I realized Asians were just as \r\nstupid as us dumb as white nazi’s.  In Upstate New York, I also grew up \r\naround black people.  However, unlike all you Californian freaks, there \r\nwas about a good erm, 10 black people in my school.  99.9% of them were \r\ndumb as fuck.  The other .1% didn’t exist.  \r\n\r\nThe intelligent person might ask this question, “Why IN HELL ARE YOU \r\nBASHING ETHNIC GROUPS.”  Shit Junior, yer just as dumb as the ethnics I \r\nbashed.  Answer is this simple.  Humans in general are stupid.  You, me, \r\nyer dog (probably more civil then most humans) the freak down the kid that \r\nfucks 5 year olds, THEY ARE ALL STUPID AS FUCK.  But talkin about those \r\npeople is not very funny.  Therefore we bash ethnics, not only to \r\nstereotype people in general, but because I want to.\r\n\r\nAnd TO CLEARLY DEFINE THE TERM ETHNIC (and I do mean clearly) ETHNIC \r\n=========== Any dumb fuck I feel like bashing.  White, black purple, \r\norange, Since everyone is a fuckin idiot, Everyone is a fuckin Ethnic.\r\n\r\nDon’t like my definition?  Screw you, screw me, screw yer dog.  Twice.\r\n\r\nWell, That about raps up today’s lesson.  I don’t really have a purpose \r\nfor this page other then to vent.  In fact, I don’t really have a purpose \r\nin life other then to sleep.  These two facts are not related.\r\n\r\nTherefore, since I conducted all the necessary introductions for a first \r\npost on a web page that no one reads, I guess they call this the end.\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', 20010126084812, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (150, 'Thomas Hunt:: Famous Movie Critic', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'original time: 03-24-00, 12:29 am\r\n\r\nMy fellow americans, I am now the "Hot Pick" of movie reviews at \r\n<a \r\nhref="http://www.rottentomatoes.com/movies/titles/whatever_it_takes/reviews\r\n.php">Rotten Tomatoes</a> \r\n\r\nfor my review of Whatever it takes.\r\n\r\nI beat the NY Times, I beat USA Today, I beat Chicago Tribune.\r\n\r\nMore importantly, Roger Ebert\'s big fat head lies at my feet.\r\n\r\nI am a movie trashing GOD!\r\n\r\nYES YES YES YES YES', '', 20010126084818, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (151, 'McCain visited my Campus.', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'The man that would be king was here. \r\n\r\nThe lobby was packed.\r\n\r\nThe carnival barker was standing on a chair and was riling up the \r\ncrowd. "Run in, get seats! Scramble" he yelled over the furor of the \r\ncrowd. \r\n\r\nThe woman at the end of the line was more realistic. "You can watch it on \r\nTV in the Auditorium, or in the lounge" she said.\r\n\r\nWhat was the point, I thought, of waking up early to see the man that \r\nwould be king, only to sit in an auditorium and watch him on TV.\r\n\r\nThey were holding signs saying "Apologize McCain". While the barker \r\ncontinued his tirade about the video broadcast, I suppose with this chaos \r\ngoing on, some were not to pleased with the man from Arizona and his quest \r\nto become king.\r\n\r\nThe barker never seemed to stop his never ending tirade, I wondered if he \r\nmight soon announce the soup of the day, I could easily hear him \r\nyelling "Chowda, we got Chowda here!"\r\n\r\nYou could easily spot the politicos in the crowd. Dressed up in their \r\nsharp business suits and their short skirts, they were pumped to see their \r\nman was in such great demand this dark morning in the year two thousand, \r\nwhen this man from Arizona was running for president, and the face of \r\nLeonardo De Caprio graced the cover of Time Magazine.\r\n\r\n"40 people! Let\'s go!" the barker screamed. Suddenly there was a huge rush \r\nof people practically trampling me as I stood stoically against a poll \r\nlaughing hysterically at the scene, as this man herded these people like \r\nthe sheep they were, so small, so weak, and so desperate to catch even the \r\nslightest glimpse of this man who would be king.\r\n\r\n"I guarantee, no more than 10 will get in" the barker screamed at the top \r\nof his lungs! The sheep remained in line, hoping that their shepherd could \r\nbe wrong, and they could get that all-important glimpse that would make \r\ntheir lives worth living.\r\n\r\nThe muzak was overpowering the mood of the scene; the epic work of Carlos \r\nSantana was not the right tunes for this group. It gave me an erie feeling \r\nthat things here were none too democratic.\r\n\r\nThe scene continued as the barker resumed his tired rant about alternate \r\nviewing areas. The people continued to stand in line.\r\n\r\nThe jackals from the local TV station were here harassing some old woman, \r\ntypically. This was an event for college students, kind of a Rock the Vote \r\nkind of experience, but these degenerate slime cared little for righteous.\r\n\r\nThe "Apologize McCain" sign-people apparently feel that McCain had used \r\nthe word "gook" to describe the Vietnamese he fought in the war over in \r\nnam. They felt he used the term on the press bus to improve his standings \r\namong the nazi-esqu elements of the backward southern state of South \r\nCarolina. They told me they were demanding an apology to all Californians, \r\nespecially the gook community that he had offended so. It sounded ok to \r\nme, although after he apologized would they still vote for him? It seems \r\nto me that his apology would be an admission that he was guilty of the \r\nreally bad use of the word chinaman in private. What shame he must feel.\r\n\r\nThe cop\'s eyes were nervous as he scanned the crowd, looking for those who \r\ncould potentially cause trouble for our loyal despot.\r\n\r\nThe barker started up again, he offered standing room only for a few of \r\nthe sheep in the front of the line, but the rest he told sharply, "there \r\nis no more room, there will be no more room, there is no point, of \r\nstanding in line." The man\'s attitude was not very good and soon he began \r\nscreaming "Get away from that door!" and it ravaged the feeling of calm \r\nthat drifted over the lobby as we awaited the speech of our own belated \r\nSun King.\r\n\r\n"No sense in hanging out here", his speech continued, quit the politico \r\nthis barker was.\r\n\r\nThey had set up a barrier of thin white rope to keep the sheep out of the \r\nballroom. I think an electric fence would have been much more appropriate.\r\n\r\nI wonder if I asked if his Royal Highness has SS protection yet, if they \r\nwould choose to have me shot as a political execution of those who dare to \r\nask questions?\r\n\r\nThe atmosphere made me wonder if after the big show, there would be a \r\nhandshaking session and our very own chance to meet the mouse himself.\r\n\r\nThe other cop was clearly ready. I could see him stretching from where I \r\nwas standing. This man was clearly ready to bust some heads if things \r\nstarted to go wrong.\r\n\r\nA roar of applause went through the crowd as McCain (presumably) took the \r\nstage. The barker yelled "No" as though he thought would rush him and \r\noverthrow his totalitarian control to catch a glimpse of Caesar himself.\r\n\r\n(Watching on TV)\r\n\r\nThe King passed through the crowd with the ease and grace one would \r\nexpect, with a popular Rock anthem, perhaps by Cher playing in the \r\nbackground, giving the event that special "we\'re speaking at a college \r\ncampus" touch.\r\n\r\nHe thanked us heartily for our "Arizona" reception, then he told us a joke \r\nabout trees chasing dogs to break the embarrassment of his idiotic \r\nmistake. \r\n\r\nHe joked about getting shot down in Vietnam. What a phony way to bring up \r\nhis war record, I thought. Not that being in a war was even a requirement \r\nfor being president anymore, now that we should be working towards having \r\nno more wars.\r\n\r\nHe was a man of the people and paced back and forth on the stage instead \r\nof using a podium and he also used no notes. \r\n\r\nHe stressed the importance of voting and threatened to break up the Iron \r\nTriangle. Like this little white haired man could be the Triangle. \r\n\r\nHe said he had 100 meetings in New Hampshire. Big deal I thought, that \r\ndoesn\'t mean a damned thing to me, I live in California. \r\n\r\nThe Arizona Man continued with more canned jokes.\r\n\r\nLike a stand up comic, the man moved the crowd.\r\n\r\nNo issues were raised.\r\n\r\nHe told people to buy his book at amazon.com, he talked about supporting \r\nhis kids and selling the movie rights to the book.\r\n\r\nFinally he showed the meat. He pushed the I\'m a veteran button and the \r\ncrowd exploded in applause like the sheep they were. \r\n\r\n30,000 dead WW2 vets dead a month he said. He blames health care, but I \r\nthink with the war being 55 years ago, most men being 20-25 while \r\nfighting, now making them 75-80, I think their recent deaths is simply \r\nattrition, no amount of health care can save them.\r\n\r\nHe casually speaks of a new war, that we young Americans might have to \r\nfight. He says more military is necessary, we need a bigger war machine. \r\n\r\nWhat happened to the idea of not having to fight a war again? I thought \r\nthat was a pretty good idea.\r\n\r\nHe spoke of how the President, Sec State and Sec Def have not had to fight \r\nin a war. "That was going to change", he wants everyone in office to have \r\nfought in a war. The only way I can see that happening is for this \r\nbloodthirsty tyrant to start more wars. \r\n\r\nHe spoke of pork barreling, which is really just the CIA hiding their \r\nbudget in the military\'s budget. \r\n\r\nHe said there would be no more "Food Stamp Army".\r\n\r\nQuoted Truman about "one armed-economists" and "to get a friend in D.C. \r\nget a dog".\r\n\r\nIt was all bread and circuses. He spoke of "giving the surplus back to \r\nyou". The crowd applauded. \r\n\r\nLike a used car salesman, he offered the crowd their money back. With \r\na "flatter, fairer, tax". \r\n\r\nWorking families taxed, lets get the rich!!! BREAD AND CIRCUES.\r\n\r\nGates and the other rich should be burnt in effigy!\r\n\r\nMore jokes, about Elvis living and people not believing in SS checks.\r\n\r\nPut more money into SS and Medicare, stop debt. Where would he get all of \r\nthis money? To give us a Tax Cut, save SS and Medicare and pay off the \r\ndebt. Does this man from Arizona have a pot of gold at the end of the \r\nrainbow to solve this financial problem?\r\n\r\nHe attacked his competition. Bush is un clean. I\'m a fiscal conservative. \r\nLet me tell you this my dear friends, seemed to be his battle cry for when \r\nthe going got rough. \r\n\r\n"I have no comment at this time" says Phillip Sublett as he sits next to \r\nme using a ugly purple IMAC.\r\n\r\nHe wants more money for the army. He talks of his website. He wants to \r\nstop pork barreling! No more spending increases! Campaign finance reform! \r\nHe wants to reform this government, he wants to fix the tax code.\r\n\r\nHe says that he is running as an outsider. He wants to reformed. "they \r\ndeprived you of your government". He called us cynical, he says we have \r\nlow voter turn out and think that our government is corrupt. The man has a \r\nhell of a positive attitude for 9 am in the morning.\r\n\r\nHe says that he will fight to the last breath to give us back our \r\ngovernment that was stolen by special interest. \r\n\r\nHe attacked Clinton and the way he rented out the Lincoln bedroom. \r\n\r\nHe said Gore collected money from a monastery and claimed he didn\'t know \r\nwhere he was.\r\n\r\nHe said he believed in Ethics. And that he would beat Gore like a Drum!\r\n\r\nHe said he was taking on the establishment and the tobacco companies.\r\n\r\nHe said no negative campaigning, despite his attacks against Clinton and \r\nGore less than a minute ago.\r\n\r\nReagan, Kennedy, FDR, TR, were inspirational presidents, he said.\r\n\r\nHe said he felt like Luke Skywalker at the death star. The man was a \r\ncompendium of hip new quotes.\r\n\r\nHe said:\r\n\r\nReagan consensus.\r\n\r\nReform party.\r\n\r\nReagan democrats\r\n\r\nBush treats the demos like aliens.\r\n\r\nParty of Lincoln\r\n\r\nPolitics of addition\r\n\r\nNot the politics of division.\r\n\r\nStrongest military\r\n\r\nStrongest economics\r\n\r\nLook at challenges:\r\nAfrica?????\r\n\r\nChallenge?\r\nNobility of democracy.\r\n\r\nHe told a story about how he always tells the truth.\r\n\r\nHe almost said yes to "Star Wars (strat laser def)" but he wussed out and \r\nspoke of a sea based missile def system. \r\n\r\nHe said China was a threat to Taiwan.\r\n\r\nThe king had lost his mind, he was talking about a war.\r\n\r\nHe wanted to give Knowledge and freedom to China, with the internet. \r\n\r\nHe said no to Star Wars, thank god, the man is not totally fucking \r\ntranqued.\r\n\r\nHe said Mars and space exploration is good.\r\n\r\nI agree.\r\n\r\nHe was attacked on ROTC and homosexuals, he stumbled and fell back to "my \r\ndear friends", my god, my dear young friend, he bubbled. He succeeds at \r\nthe end by pulling the good ole, "racism is bad point" out of his ass and \r\ngoes back to his wife and his adopted daughter from Bangladesh, he then \r\nhits the point again, "racism is bad, bush went to that bad school to \r\nspeak, he\'s bad!"\r\n\r\nWTF is a log cabin republican? Who are they? Well, whoever they are, he \r\nbelieves in don\'t ask, don\'t tell, and he agrees with them on other issues.\r\n\r\n"Art good" said the arizonian.\r\n\r\nHero Worship\r\n\r\nWhat makes a hero?\r\nI\'m not a hero.\r\n\r\nI failed in prison.\r\n\r\nServed with heroes.\r\n\r\nThousands of acts of courage, compassion and love.\r\n\r\nReal heroes are on the wall.\r\n\r\n(i.e.: gotta be dead to be a hero. Yup yup.)\r\nThis king was a piece of work indeed.\r\n\r\nI\'m Crazy about CENSORSHIP!\r\n\r\nNo more violence, no more poor, no more evil influence, no more video \r\ngames. Responsibility of parents. We must monitor our children and make \r\nsure they have good Judeo-Christian thoughts.\r\n\r\nInet new challenge, we must filter objectionable material from all \r\nlibraries.\r\n\r\nThe man is insane. First, it\'s impossible. Second, who will decide what \r\nis "objectionable", fucking NAZI!\r\n\r\nDignity plant\r\n\r\nThis woman asked him to uphold the dignity of the office, and shake her \r\nson\'s hand. It was so moving, I was almost brought to tears. It was \r\nscripted out like a WWF match.\r\n\r\nMore the buck stops here, quotes from Truman, the man who dropped two A-\r\nBombs on Japan. Definitely one to be idolized.\r\n\r\nGreenspan == Bernie\r\n\r\nThis was the best fucking part. He said if Greenspan died, we would \r\nprobably put sunglasses on him and parade him around like in Weekend at \r\nBernies. I have to admit, that was a pretty damn awesome thing to say.\r\n\r\nMore ramblings\r\n\r\nGNP of Rus is bigger than the Netherlands. Good job insulting our allies \r\nthere, buddy. Putin is aligned with the commies. The technology transfer \r\nis bad. No Loans for Russia if they sell tech. The man really was serious \r\nabout starting that war. Let\'s piss off Russia and China, they do have the \r\nmost bombs.\r\n\r\nThey asked him an environment question. He said that natural parks were \r\ngood.\r\n\r\nHe said the demos were controlled by Lawyers, and that was bad. He also \r\nsaid the Republicans were controlled by Big Money and HMOs and that was \r\nbad. The Iron Triangle argument comes up again.\r\n\r\nIt\'s a crusade, he will reform the government for the people. If it\'s a \r\ncrusade are we going to go steal the holy land from innocents? \r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n', '', 20010127103850, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (152, 'The Market & Chinatown', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '<B>Thunt and the Market: Day 2.</B>\r\n\r\nA few days ago I went ahead and entered the stock market.  Using my mighty \r\nameritrade account I purchased 10 shares of CORL (Corel, for Ben) at 15 \r\n7/8.  To my predicted dismay it fell to 14 ˝ that day causing me a \r\ntemporary 10 dollar loss, of course, now it’s day 2 and I’m up 50 bucks.  \r\nNot a lot, but that’s a days work for not working, and that’s good.  \r\n\r\n<B>Chinatown, man.</B>\r\n\r\nI went to Chinatown in SF yesterday.  It was fun.  We didn’t get too lost \r\nin getting there and once there we got to see lots of cool stuff.  We \r\n(Steve, Mike, John, Dillon, and myself) has dinner at a nice Chinese food \r\nrestaurant.  Then we went to the best music store I’ve ever been to, \r\nAmoeba Music in Berkley.  It was fantastic.  I scored a shitload of \r\nclassical music cds, the orgazmo soundtrack and a new copy of Citizen Kane \r\nfor not too much cash.  I strongly recommend going there if you’ve got \r\nmoney to spend.  CDs for 1.00, lots of em.\r\n\r\n', '', 20010127103856, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (153, 'Star Wars: xploitation', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'A letter I wrote to Rick Mccallum, some big wig at Lucas Films in regards \r\nto his comments at www.starwars.com about the lack of Star Wars DVDs, I \r\nsent it to every address I thought he might have.  Perhaps it will go \r\nthrough.\r\n\r\n"It\'s really about exploiting an exciting medium in the best possible way."\r\n\r\nYou sure said it Rick.  If I had any idea that the people behind Star Wars \r\nwere a bunch of profiteering gluttons, I never would have watched the \r\nfilms when I was a kid.\r\n\r\nPlease release the DVD without any special features.\r\n\r\n(of course a nice transfer, letterboxed, with DD sound would be highly \r\nappreciated)\r\n\r\nThen when George gets to it, release your special edition. If it\'s even \r\nremotely special, we will all buy it.  You know this.  Look at all the \r\nother crap that flies off the shelf with break neck speed.\r\n\r\nPlease.  Listen to the fans, before you have no fans left. \r\n\r\nThomas Hunt\r\nthunt@thepentagon.com\r\n\r\nbtw: Tell George he used 47 wipes in TPM and \r\nhe looked like an amateur director, instead of his usual Kurasawa-ripoff \r\nstyle.\r\n', '', 20010127103901, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (154, 'School is upon us', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'Now is the hour of our discontent, oh my brothers and only friends.  Well \r\nreally, I\'m not all that discontented.  I\'m rather looking forward to \r\nschool, as God willing (all of you must knock on wood to acknowledge your \r\nfaith in the superstitions that keep the world spinnin\' round); I\'ll be \r\ngraduating at the end of this coming semester.  Personally, I\'m not afraid \r\nof the classes, I\'m more afraid of the post-graduation stuff.  I don\'t \r\nknow how many of you are on the fast track through college to job to \r\nmarried with children to death, but that\'s a roller coaster that I\'m not \r\nready to board yet.  Thank you kindly, but no sir.  So, post graduation I \r\ndon\'t know what I\'m going to do but let\'s get back to the subject at \r\nhand.... The Spring 2001 semester.\r\n\r\nI suppose that while I have all your attention perhaps I should make some \r\npredictions. \r\n\r\n1. Hannibal will be rad - The new movie by Ridley Scott from the Thomas \r\nHarris book will rock as much as the book did.  The replacement of \r\nJodie "I understand my character, she would never do that" Foster with \r\nJulianne "Nudity doesn\'t bother me" Moore will not effect the film or the \r\ncharacter.  After a few frames, you\'ll accept her as Agent Starling and be \r\nmesmerized again by another brilliant Anthony Hopkins performance \r\n(hopefully it will erase from your mind the fact that he was in Zorro).\r\n\r\n2. Andy will redesign the flag 6 times - Last semester it was pretty much \r\nan every issue kind of thing, but this semester I think he\'s got it under \r\ncontrol and I think he\'ll only redesign it 6 times.  You can start your \r\nown pools on this too.\r\n\r\n3. The Hornet\'s "web people" will begin studying acronyms to try to look \r\nsmart.  Words like PHP, PGP, ASP, SQL, CYA, RTFM, NATO can be confusing \r\nfor some people, but I hope that this semester the Hornet will finally get \r\nthat whole JPG, GIF, PNG (not really an acronym, just a sound, ping!) mess \r\nfigured out.  Perhaps with a little help from the Macintosh computers that \r\nwill hide all the ROTFLOL errors from their SVGA IMAC screens.\r\n\r\n4. The man who sails the seven seas will become a pirate. ARRR!  To quote \r\nSteve Jobs "it\'s better to be a pirate than to join the navy".  Of course, \r\nthere is something to be said about being a First Class Seamen.  Or is it \r\nSeamen, First Class!\r\n\r\n5. Campus Engine will make a major comeback selling T-shirts and other \r\nfashionable attire.  College kids will adopt the logo of the failed \r\ncompany and wear it with pride.  Engine will become a slang phrase for \r\nbong hits after a former employee teaches the children how to chug-chug-\r\nchug...\r\n\r\n6. The pool on G\'s death will reach so high that the organizers of the \r\npool will consider hiring an assassin but they will back out at the last \r\nminute, leaving one angry hit man.\r\n\r\n7. People will learn to love reverse-board technology.  They will \r\nunderstand the value of having the newest messages at the top and learn \r\nwhen reading top to bottom, not to read threads before they read the \r\noriginal article.\r\n\r\n8. Andy will beat up 2-3 more members of the staff, leaving him to truly \r\nbe the master of the newsroom, the awesome artist, the triumphant tracer, \r\nthe end of endeeean: Andy!\r\n\r\n9. Dude, Andy fucking rules. That\'s all I\'ve gotta say.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWell, I think that\'s enough predictions for now.  If I started predicting \r\ntrouble for people who remain unnamed, my crystal ball and me would get in \r\ndeep shit.  And no body wants that.  He he.\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', 20010127103909, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (155, 'Financial Ruin & Farenheit 451', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'original date: ThuntDate: 2/10/00\r\n\r\nWell, I’m all out of money.  Yup, it finally happened, I’m over extended.  \r\nI might be able to dig myself out of it in a few months, but for now I’m \r\ngoing to have to halt all fun purchases and try to live on the ten bucks \r\nin my back pocket.  Is it possible? I think so, but if not, don’t be \r\nsurprised if you see me siphoning gas from your gas tank.\r\n\r\nIn other news, I watched Farenheit 451 by Francois Truffaut (I know, I \r\nprobably spelled his name wrong, but there is no end to the ammount of \r\nrespect I have for this man).  It was stunning.  Moving.  Amazing. But I \r\nmust say it is one of the most terrifying movies I have ever watched and I \r\ndon’t ever want to watch it again.  THEY WERE BURNING BOOKS!!!! Yes, I did \r\nread the book years ago and I remember being outraged, but it’s something \r\nelse to watch books be burnt and burnt and burnt.  God damn it was sad.  I \r\ncouldn’t believe their society. It scared the damn hell out of me.  Shit \r\nbitch, I’m telling you.\r\n\r\nAnyway, I gotta get back to work.  If Thunt.net seems to be stagnant, \r\nblame Sacramento State University and also I got a new job over at the \r\nState Hornet, so check that out…. L8r\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n', '', 20010131201421, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (156, 'Old Thunt.net News #01 - 03.31.99 - 06.10.99', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'Thuntdate 6.10.99\r\n\r\nI was happy ten minutes ago, and now I\'m sad. It\'s funny how things work. \r\nNot that I was too happy, cause I did wake up and six, and it is 7am and I \r\nam at work. But I was pretty happy. And now I\'m sad. I was writing a rant \r\non Jar Jar. I finished it. It ain\'t bad. Mack (hi Mack!) gave me the idea, \r\nconsidering how I had been bitching about him (Jar Jar, not Mack), but I \r\nhadn\'t written a rant. I\'m still adapting to the whole idea of writing \r\ndown my ideas to fill up this page. I should be pretty well adapted by mid-\r\nsummer. What makes me sad is little differences in the english language. \r\nwe or WE.\r\n\r\n\r\nThuntdate 6.7.99\r\n\r\nDay 2 of Live Thunt.net.... Well, I feel downright shitty today. I woke up \r\nand my throat is all fucked up. I really love being a human. Although I \r\ndid get some good news today, I got my grades. And because no one reads \r\nthis page, and I\'m totally fucking proud of them (despite the fact I \r\nprobably could have done better, at least I\'m not on fucking academic \r\nprobation anymore and I\'m still on the Dean\'s List UHHHH!!!) so I\'m going \r\nto post them... Here they are!\r\n\r\n\r\nSpring \'99\r\n\r\nCRJ132 - Violence and Terrorism - B+\r\nThe teacher was certifiable, he didn\'t like my first paper. But, FUCK HIM!\r\n\r\nHIST142B - Modern China 1800-Present - B+\r\nI could have done better here, but it was a hard upper division class.\r\n\r\nENG20 - College Composition - A\r\nI rule, my papers were so rad, he asked if he could keep a copy.\r\n\r\nCOMS2 - Argumentation - A\r\nA debate class, could I get anything but an A? I don\'t think so.\r\n\r\n\r\nHRS185 - Women in Film - B+\r\nIt was much harder than I thought, but I actually feel I learned a lot.\r\n\r\nMUSC142B - Pep Band - A\r\nBand is cool\r\nGPA - 3.606\r\n\r\nIt\'s good to be the king. I\'m on the Dean\'s list again, my grades don\'t \r\nsuck, and if I keep this up, who knows! Maybe I will get into UCLA film \r\nschool, there\'s always hope.\r\n\r\nMore Shit: Gabe and I put the definiative cut on the Saxline Jerry \r\nSpringer show yesterday, it is pretty awesome. We\'re going to do the \r\ntrailer for Campus Cops today and round out the week editing the Saxline \r\nDocumentary and the Phantom Documentary. A good week. I also got some \r\nwriting down on my screenplay yesterday and learned a lesson from \r\nVonnegut, "Writing is all about patience", "it is the art of making \r\nyourself look smart". So hopefully I will gain some paitence and \r\neverything will work out great. Well, I\'m having a pretty great day, and I \r\nhope you are too. Gooooood-Bye!\r\n\r\n\r\nThunt.net GOES LIVE!!! Thuntdate 6.6.99\r\n6,6,99 (flip them upside down, it\'s a palindrome).\r\n\r\nThunt.net is on today!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! I have just taken the webpage out of \r\nBeta status and brought it online! Today is the day, the rest of you\'re \r\nlife, you have been waiting to live a "Thunt" Day, but now here is you\'re \r\nchance!!! If anything is broken, please email me and I\'ll fix it right \r\naway. But otherwise, sit back, relax and enjoy Thunt.net, a brand fucking \r\nnew website hosted by k9.dv8.org by the wise and honorable Doug Coker, and \r\npurchased for the Great Thunt by Dan & Mike, because they rule. But enough \r\nof me, just go forth, and enjoy Thunt.net. \r\n\r\nThuntdate 6.1.99\r\nIt\'s my first day at work for the summer. WOOO! It\'s really fucking early \r\ntoo. It\'s 7:15 now. And I\'m realitively awake. But tired. I\'m going to be \r\nworking in the labs mornings all summer, so I figured I\'d continue my work \r\non the page. Might even up the new build to DV8 today. Also I was planning \r\non checking what Doug needed to do to make the hosting done so I can start \r\nbragging to all my friends that my email is thunt@thunt.net. hehehehe. \r\nThat\'s about it. I saw a bunch of films this weekend thanks to Mike, my \r\nhero who got a job in a video store so we got free films. (Not just films \r\nbut DVDs TOO!!) It was rad. Thanks Mike. I\'m all moved into my apartment. \r\nDriving to school is wierd ass. There was traffic but I skillfully avioded \r\nit. I rule. Well, anyway, back to sleeping in my empty lab. And in case I \r\ndon\'t see you, Good Afternoon, Good Evening and Good Night! \r\n\r\nThuntdate 5.17.99\r\nThe site lay dormant for quite a while, and it looked like this might be \r\nanother of the new designs that get left behind on my hard drive somewhere \r\nand forgotten. But the work has started again due to my friends Mike & Dan \r\nbuying me the domain name Thunt.net, which encouraged me to get off my ass \r\nand start working on a decent page to show the full glory of the new name. \r\nSo I\'ve begun building the secondary sections, adding reviews, and buffing \r\nup the page, I hope you like it, cause I sure do. :> \r\n\r\nThuntdate 3.31.99\r\nWell, I\'m finishing out my last day of work over break and I feel sick. \r\nNot my typical stomach nausua, but a whole new coughing and sneezing \r\nthing. It\'s pretty sweet. I\'m doing well on my spring break movie quest, \r\nI\'m trying to beat my record from last year of 24 movies over break. So \r\nfar I\'m on 16!!! I\'m also almost done with my AFI 100 Movies, 100 years \r\nquest. Only 12 to go! \r\n', '', 20010131201425, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (157, 'Old Thunt.net News #02 - 06.22.99 - 06.31.99', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'Thuntdate 6.22.99\r\n\r\nI got a mail from Amazon.com saying they wanted me to be an affiliate, I \r\nthought about it, and thought, hey commission is good, right? But then I \r\nrealized I hardly ever buy anything from Amazon.com, so why would I want \r\nto tempt you into doing that? But I thought, hey, I always buy from \r\nReel.com, they usually ship it the same day, and I always use coupons so I \r\nget a good deal, so I figured, I\'d keep you updated on Reel\'s sales and \r\nstuff, and if you buy stuff by clicking through my link, I\'d get 8 percent \r\nof the total (probably about 80 cents per order, which isn\'t alot, but \r\nwhat the hey..). So here\'s the info, hopefully it\'s up to date.\r\n\r\nCoupon Name - What it does:\r\n\r\n---------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n-----\r\n\r\nfreedvd - They take 1 dollar off your order, then you get a 20 dollar gift \r\ncertificate in your email. An excellent deal.\r\n\r\n\r\nbestpicture - 10 dollars off an order of 25 or more.\r\n\r\n\r\nproducer - 5 dollars off an order of 15 or more.\r\n\r\nMore info as things develop.\r\n\r\n\r\nClick the link here:\r\n\r\nReel.com - Give Thunt 8 Percent! \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThuntdate 6.19.99\r\n\r\nNew Movie Review in Movie Reviews Section, New Project info in Projects \r\nSection.\r\n\r\nSen-Sen Question Answered.\r\n\r\nActual proof that everything is on the web, if you just know how to look \r\nfor it. Today, Ben Black, ruthless searcher of the internet, helped me \r\nsolve a riddle that has puzzled mankind much longer than the riddle of the \r\nSpinx. The answer to: What is Sen-Sen.\r\n\r\nI will now quote from <a href="http://www.fffoods.com/sensen.htm">FF \r\nFoods</a>\' informative page about Sen-Sen:\r\n\r\nWhen a country swain went courting his rural sweetheart, he often carried \r\nin his pocket an unobtrusive little envelope of Sen-Sen. When his younger \r\nbrother indulged in smoking behind the barn, he too, had use for the \r\nexotic little pellets. For Sen-Sen was to the 19th century what breath \r\nmints are to our time. Any country store worth its salt, prominently \r\ndisplayed a box of the handy little packets within easy reach of its \r\ncustomers.\r\n\r\nThere\'s even more facinating information about Sen-Sen on their page, like \r\nhow it was invented, ingredients, and how you can order it! It\'s pretty \r\nneat. Well, I just wanted to say good job Ben, You are now promoted to Sir \r\nBen Black, of the order of Thunt. Wear your title with pride.\r\n\r\n"No, you don\'t get a merit badge. Just a sash, which you must fill with \r\nmerit badges."\r\n\r\n"Badges? We don\'t want no badges, we got no badges, we don\'t need no \r\nstinking badges!"\r\n(The Treasure of the Sierra Madre, old Bogart film, correctly quoted, by \r\none who has seen the film. Dir by John Ford I think.)\r\n\r\n\r\nOh, and btw: Matt\'s new review of Aliens: Special Edition DVD is up in the \r\nDVD Reviews Section!!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThuntdate 6.18.99\r\n\r\nWelcome back to your regularlly scheduled thunt.net. I think my carpel \r\ntunnel is acting up, so I might be a bit brief, but I really wanted to \r\nupdate a little because my friend Ben tells me he has started checking \r\nthis page lately, and that\'s the kind of chaos I want to inspire with my \r\nown domain name. People who wake up every morning to see if I wrote \r\nanything bitching about my day on my website... That and mass twinkee-\r\nmotivated murders.\r\n\r\nI worked 10 hours yesterday. 5 at my ECS Lab job (cool) and 5 at my new \r\njob at Computer Warehouse (ok). It wasn\'t that hard, but standing up for 5 \r\nhours straight is pretty lame. I know, I\'ll get used to it, or else, but \r\nstill, it was my first day, so let me take some time to whine. Other than \r\nthe standing and the usual begining of a new job confusion, it was pretty \r\ngood. The people were nice, and the customers seemed to be in no hurry and \r\naccepting of me being new.\r\n\r\nAnd now a look into the future of Thunt.net, all the way to next week.\r\n\r\nI watched some movies. I\'ll add them to the Summer list soon, and I read \r\nsome books, perhaps this weekend I\'ll write reviews, short, but sweet.\r\n\r\nAlso, Matt sent in a few reviews, and I\'ll try to have those up soon!\r\n\r\nMy books arrived in the mail, (2/3)... I got the Onion Book: Our Dumb \r\nCentury, and as expected, it is funny and an excellent coffee table book \r\nfor our coffee table (an old drive case for a vax, hell of a coffee table, \r\nI\'ll take a picture and scan it in someday). Also I got Silence of the \r\nLambs by Thomas Harris (nice name!). It\'s pretty good so far, I thought I \r\nwouldn\'t be interested cause I\'ve seen the movie alot, and I though the \r\nfilm was pretty great (good job hopkins!, and of course Demme!), but the \r\nbook is holding it\'s own. I bought it cause it was cheap online at \r\nbuy.com, and I had a coupon I got at dvdpricesearch.com it was a neat \r\ncoupon cause it was 10 off books, software, dvd, etc... (Normally I just \r\nhave coupons on DVDs), (kudos Matt). I also bought it because I orded \r\nHarris\'s latest book Hannibal (the sequal). It\'s in the mail now, \r\nsomewhere in Memphis, TN according to FedEx... Online shipping is \r\nfacinating isn\'t it?\r\n\r\nMore randomness:\r\n\r\nI walked by the ECS Deans office to hear (for the first time I\'ve ever \r\nheard it) "water cooler" talk, or coffee talk, some kind of office \r\nchatter, they were discussing the scene from Austin Powers 2 about the \r\nAlan Parsons Project. Interesting to hear this stereotypical chatter \r\nstuff, like how magazines said that people talked about Seinfeld episodes \r\nin the office the day after.\r\n\r\nMy friends are home in Davis I guess. But I\'m working in Sac. So it goes.\r\n\r\nMy hands are tired. \r\n\r\n\r\nwhat is "Sen-Sen"?\r\n\r\nIt\'s not in the m-w online dictionary and yahoo and altavista don\'t know.\r\n\r\nI\'ve heard it in the Music Man, "covering up a tell tale breath with Sen-\r\nsen" and now Silence of the Lambs:\r\n\r\n"she felt the ache of his whole yellow smiling Sen-Sen lonesome life"\r\n\r\nso is it like some thing to make your teeth white? or some smokers gum \r\ntype thing???\r\n\r\nAnybody???? I\'ll put your name on the page or something as a reward.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThuntdate 6.16.99\r\n\r\nWe are sorry to interupt your normal Thunt.net broadcast with a special \r\nreport.\r\n\r\nDIVX is DEAD!!!\r\n\r\nI\'m so excited, I almost made that blinking. That\'s right, it\'s not a \r\nrumor, it\'s not a slogan, it\'s the truth. Check out these links if you \r\ndoubt me.\r\n\r\nYahoo - "Circuit City posts loss after dropping DIVX"\r\n\r\nPr Newswire - Digital Video Express, LP to Discontinue Operations\r\n\r\nWOOOOOO! DEATH TO DIVX. And this just after our old pals at Di$ney decided \r\nto release Alice in Wonderland, Who framed Roger Rabbit, (and some of my \r\nfavorites) Dumbo and Dick Tracy on DIVX. Awwwww, boo hoo, poor Di$ney \r\nbeing stuck with the looser, well that\'s what you get for trying to rip \r\noff the consumer, you mother fuckers.\r\n\r\nAlso, in other fun news, Circuit City is "incurring an after-tax loss of \r\n$114.0 million". And they haven\'t even started to pay consumers the $100 \r\nrebate they get for being dumb and buying DIVX. I just hope some of these \r\npoor DIVX lusers start suing Circuit City so that they can go out of \r\nbusiness like they deserve to. Anyone who tries to fuck the consumer \r\nshould go out of business.....\r\n\r\nSo, as you can see, I\'m thrilled, but I\'d better let you get back to your \r\nnormal (now DIVX-FREE) lives.\r\n\r\nFUCK DIVX.\r\nThank you, and good night.\r\n\r\n\r\nThuntdate 6.13.99\r\nWelcome back to Thunt.net. It\'s been a busy weekend. I\'ve gotten \r\nabsolutely nothing done that I attended to, but so it goes. I finished a \r\nfew books, watched a few films. Expect a review of Austin Powers: The Spy \r\nwho Shagged me soon, and expect it to be mainly positive. I would also \r\nlike to take a chance now to add to Thunt.net. I created Thunt.net as a \r\nplace to expose my ideas to the internet. Sections such as reviews, rants, \r\netc... But I would also be interested in promoting your ideas, so if you \r\nwould like to add a review, etc to Thunt.net, please email it to me at \r\nthunt@thepentagon.com and if it\'s up to snuff, I\'ll add it to the page, \r\nand you can join the ranks of Thunt.net. That\'s about it. Doobidoob.\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', 20010131201429, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (158, 'Dotcom Detective', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '\r\n<i>author\'s note: this is to be read in the style of a 1920s detective \r\nnovel.  Imagine the voice of Humphrey Bogart...</i>\r\n\r\nMy name is Jones.  I work out of 53rd street.  I’m a private dick.  \r\nYesterday the bitch came to my office.  Why do I call her a bitch and not \r\na dame?  Well as they say, “the proof is in the pudding, enjoy your \r\nJello”.  She said she had a job for me.  I said, “You don’t look like the \r\ntype who does much hiring, isn’t it usually the other way around?”  She \r\nslapped me hard across the face and said “I’m business savvy.  Do you want \r\nthe job or not?”  Well, I haven’t had a real job since I had to do that \r\nthing to that redhead and the man she’d run off with and it would be nice \r\nto get back to some normal 9-5 dicking.  \r\n\r\n“Perhaps” I said, “What’s the job?”  \r\n\r\n“Well” she said, “I work for an insignificant corporation in the Union \r\nTelegraph building downtown and I’ve got a problem.”\r\n\r\n“Oh yeah, what is it?  That’s a pretty swank building.”  I almost \r\nadded “for a cheap slut like you” but my jaw still stung from that last \r\nshot she got off and I’d rather stick to my usual strategy of kicking my \r\nclients when they are down, not when they are sitting right across from me.\r\n\r\n“Well you see Mr. Jones, I’m the ruler of dozens of men and a few women.  \r\nA few months ago we signed a contract with a dotcom vender to deliver our \r\npaper clips to the office, as we had no possible way of doing this \r\nourselves…“\r\n\r\nI could see where her story was going.  In the last few months I’d handled \r\ndozens of dotcom revenge jobs.  Most of them were simple firebombing.  \r\nSome people just wanted some promotional merchandise that they could \r\ndestroy and defecate on in the privacy of their own home, the sick fucks.  \r\nBut I could tell that this bitch’s story was going to be different.  There \r\nwas something about the dull look in her eyes and the lack of chest \r\nornamentation that I knew her story would be especially interesting.\r\n\r\n“So you see I’ve re-signed with the company that bought the failed dotcom \r\nand my employees are angry.  They’ve been talking about revolution.  There \r\nis an organizer named TtamNrowB.  I hear that it is not his real name, but \r\nan acronym (try this at home, Junior Crimestoppers!), but I’m not really \r\nbright enough to figure those things out.  Can you help me detective?”\r\n\r\n“You still haven’t asked me what you want me to do, Miss?”\r\n\r\n”Flatlands, Marsha Flatlands.”\r\n\r\n“Well Miss Flatlands, what do you have in mind?”\r\n\r\nShe shifted in her chair in an obvious attempt to increase her \r\nattractiveness.  One of her spaghetti straps fell and once more I realized \r\nthat it anytime was a good time to invest in silicon futures.\r\n\r\nShe said “Well, Mr. Jones I’d like you to…”\r\n\r\nTune in next time, same Thunt time, same Thunt.net for the next exciting \r\nchapter.\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', 20010201110315, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (159, 'Top 100 reasons to Date Thomas', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'updated 2:53 - 3/7/00\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n          I read a forward once listing reasons why a girl should date a \r\nguy…. They were good reasons.  I’m going to list some, some are from my \r\nmind, others are from the list.  I don’t have the list.  I’m just going to \r\nad-lib some.  If it sounds just like the forward, fuck you.  If you like \r\nit, good, cause I wrote it for people.  Or for myself. At 1:25 it doesn’t \r\nreally matter does it?\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n1.     He’s not afraid of the dark\r\n\r\n2.     He does not drink real beer, only root beer.\r\n\r\n3.     He likes the twilight zone.\r\n\r\n4.     He is against censorship.\r\n\r\n5.     He is a member of the ACLU.\r\n\r\n6.     He always reads the comics first in the newspaper.\r\n\r\n7.     He’s well read.\r\n\r\n8.     He is computer literate.\r\n\r\n9.     He likes some musicals.\r\n\r\n10.            He feels bad for being the only one who hates “My Fair Lady”\r\n\r\n11.            He is fairly certain that he did not assassinate John F. \r\nKennedy.\r\n\r\n12.            The only wall calendar he owns is a 1995 REM calendar, \r\nwhich he still hangs up, knowing full well that it is the year 2000.\r\n\r\n13.            His friends do not call him Collins, Tom Collins.\r\n\r\n14.            He has seen most of the James Bond films.\r\n\r\n15.            He can sometimes control his urges to recite Tarantino \r\nfilms.\r\n\r\n16.            Sometimes he cannot control his urges to recite Tarantino \r\nfilms.\r\n\r\n17.            He can type 90 words a minute.\r\n\r\n18.            He prefers subtitled films to dubs.\r\n\r\n19.            He occasionally shaves.\r\n\r\n20.            Sometimes he combs his hair.\r\n\r\n21.            Occasionally he is convinced that there is a great amount \r\nof beauty in this world.\r\n\r\n22.            He likes to read Shakespeare.\r\n\r\n23.            He has 20/20 vision, and only wears glasses for reading, \r\nwhich he does non-stop.\r\n\r\n24.            He has not sold out.\r\n\r\n25.            He is not interested in money.\r\n\r\n26.            He is only bigoted against videotapes. (in favor of DVDs)\r\n\r\n27.            Only 5 people have asked him if he is the Anti-Christ.\r\n\r\n28.            Less than 10 people have made comparisons between him and \r\nAdolf Hitler.\r\n\r\n29.            Only 3 of those people have had compelling evidence to back \r\nup their fallacious claims.\r\n\r\n30.            He is knowledgeable about Greek Mythology.\r\n\r\n31.            He knows the names of all of the Greek gods and their \r\ncorresponding Roman Names.\r\n\r\n32.            He knows the words to Billy Joel’s “We didn’t start the \r\nfire” and REM’s “It’s the end of the world as we know it, and I feel fine”\r\n\r\n33.            He appreciates Black and White films.\r\n\r\n34.            He usually drives the speed limit.\r\n\r\n35.            He has never participated in a Race Riot.\r\n\r\n36.            He doesn’t live and die by the sword.\r\n\r\n37.            He flipped off the Capitol Building in Sacramento, and \r\nnothing has happened to him, yet.\r\n\r\n38.            He actually sat through all of “How Stella got her groove \r\nback” and lived to tell the tail.\r\n\r\n39.            He rarely mistakes their for there or they’re.\r\n\r\n40.            He hasn’t recently gotten in a huge argument over the \r\npronunciation of “the”.\r\n\r\n41.            He never tells little kids that there is no Santa Claus.\r\n\r\n42.            He pays rent on time.\r\n\r\n43.            He refuses to fail.\r\n\r\n44.            He can walk and chew gum.  At the same time!\r\n\r\n45.            He exists in three-dimensional space.\r\n\r\n46.            He does not oppose profanity.\r\n\r\n47.            He knows HTML.\r\n\r\n48.            He uses toothpaste.\r\n\r\n49.            He frequently wears sunglasses inside.\r\n\r\n50.            He voted today!\r\n\r\n51.            He has never conquered any small countries.\r\n\r\n52.            He always pays his credit card bills on time.\r\n\r\n53.            He has never used the phrase “all’s I know”.\r\n\r\n54.            He’s creative.\r\n\r\n55.            He’s cool.\r\n\r\n56.            He is rarely called a looser.\r\n\r\n57.            He is an anarchist.\r\n\r\n58.            On more than one occasion, he has been called Superfly.\r\n\r\n59.            He has seen Friday and Next Friday.\r\n\r\n60.            He has seen all three Shaft films.\r\n\r\n61.            Gravity doesn’t bother him.\r\n\r\n62.            He is the “man of mystery”.\r\n\r\n63.            Sometimes he glows in the dark.\r\n\r\n64.            He is not radioactive.\r\n\r\n65.            Elvis won’t stop visiting him.\r\n\r\n66.            Letterman always requests jokes from him.\r\n\r\n67.            He has shaken Conan O Brien’s hand.\r\n\r\n68.            He has saved the world from total destruction on more than \r\none occasion.\r\n\r\n69.            He has never been properly thanked for his role in saving \r\nthe world, but he doesn’t let that get him down.\r\n\r\n70.            He coined the term “Men in Black”.\r\n\r\n71.            He has lost more money than Bill Gates has ever had.\r\n\r\n72.            Alan Greenspan often asks him for financial advice.\r\n\r\n73.            He is not a communist.\r\n\r\n74.            Although sometimes, he believes that in a perfect world \r\nsuch communist theories might work.\r\n\r\n75.            Ok, so maybe he is a communist, but that ain’t that bad.\r\n\r\n76.            He believes in absolute rule. (ie: with himself as a ruler)\r\n\r\n77.            He can see in 3D without those silly looking glasses.\r\n\r\n78.            He thinks those stupid 3D picture things are really silly.\r\n\r\n79.            He knows several rocket scientists. And has never asked \r\nthem to help him destroy the world, not even once!\r\n\r\n80.            He has read Cyrano De Bergerac.\r\n\r\n81.            He thinks that Mr. Bigglesworth looks ok, even without his \r\nhair.\r\n\r\n82.            He rarely mocks bald people.\r\n\r\n83.            He hopes one day to read War and Peace.  And to be \r\nsurprised at it being so short.\r\n\r\n84.            He frequently composes sonnets with Shakespeare’s ghost.\r\n\r\n85.            He is still preparing for the reunion of the Four Original \r\nBeatles.\r\n\r\n86.            He would never relate the coming of the Four Horseman to \r\nthe coming of the Four Beatles, at least until now.\r\n\r\n87.            He hopes to make this list so long that people would say it \r\nis unreadable.\r\n\r\n88.            He has only been threatened at gunpoint 5 times!\r\n\r\n89.            He has refused to date countless supermodels.\r\n\r\n90.            He has refused to father children, on several non-\r\nconsecutive occasions.\r\n\r\n91.            People don’t hate him because he is beautiful.\r\n\r\n92.            He is humble.\r\n\r\n93.            He has not had dandruff since he switched to Head and \r\nShoulders.\r\n\r\n94.            He has never spilled his drink, since he discovered the \r\nglory of the straw.\r\n\r\n95.            He rarely speaks of the immense power of the Spork.\r\n\r\n96.            He would never bore you with his unifying theory of cutlery.\r\n\r\n97.            He thinks Brain would be an excellent world ruler.\r\n\r\n98.            He thinks Pinky should be sent to the guillotine at the \r\nfirst chance.\r\n\r\n99.            Sometimes he can spell.\r\n\r\n100.       He’s only 20!  And it is very likely that he will live to be \r\n100!\r\n\r\nI’ll add more to this list soon.\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', 20010202084354, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (160, 'Thunt\'s Rants: Die Jar Jar, Die', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'The title of today\'s rant is not The Jar Jar, The, for those of you who \r\nspeak German, it is instead a rant based on the worst character from the \r\nworst Star Wars Movie. That\'s right, you guessed it, Jar Jar Blinks. I\'m \r\ngoing to go ahead and break my rant on Jar Jar into sections, because I \r\ncan.\r\n\r\nThe Lines:\r\n\r\n\r\n"Messah Jar Jar Blinks" - Ok, now I\'m not one to pull out the old "racist \r\nflag" but let\'s face it, this is one of the few times when I agree with \r\nthem. It does sound an aweful lot like "Yesah Massah".... Also, with the \r\nGunGuns presumed to be Jamacan, it does fit rather well by stereotyping \r\nthem as characters and as a race.\r\n\r\n"How Ruude" - Is Lucas still watching Full House re-runs with his kids? \r\nDoes Michelle still crack him up? Well personally I think that show wore \r\nout it\'s welcome on my television long ago, and now even in a galaxy far \r\nfar away Michelle has fans? WTF! Really, give me a break. (Better watch \r\nout, he\'ll use that line next and make Episode II into one big Kit Kat \r\nCommercial.)\r\n\r\n"Ouchie Time" - Well, Jar Jar didn\'t say this, but I feel it was his evil \r\ninfluence that made one of the GunGun generals say "ouchie time".... It \r\nwas pretty aweful. Also this could feed into the negative stereotype idea, \r\nperhaps it\'s not just Jar Jar who talks like an idiot, perhaps it\'s his \r\nwhole species.... Boy that\'s a negative trait...\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nR2-D2 - R2 is my man. During his introduction to the trilogy, that idiot \r\nJar Jar is in his way, so R2 cusses at him, Jar Jar says "How Ruude", so \r\nyou know if Jar Jar was offended it must have been pretty damn bad, way to \r\ngo R2!!!\r\n\r\nForest Gump - Let me say that I enjoyed Forest Gump, as a good film, good \r\neffects, acting, music, etc. But I did not enjoy the message that, if you \r\nare an idiot, everything will turn out fine. Jar jar too portrayed this \r\nmessage. He caused a problem and was banned from his community. Then he \r\nwas almost killed by a tank, but no worries, Jedis come and save him. Then \r\nhe goes home, they want him to leave, but no worries, Jedis save him \r\nagain. Then Jar Jar gets a free spaceship ride off of his planet when it \r\nis attacked, boy that was lucky. Then he\'s stuck on Tatonine and caught \r\nshoplifting, but no worries, little future evil Jedi was there to save \r\nhim. Then he\'s fighting a war to protect his way of life, course he \r\npractically destroys his whole army with a sling shot. But no worries, \r\nit\'s just funny old Jar Jar. Ha Ha. Then he opens the back of one of their \r\nammo trucks, but of course, instead of loosing all the GunGun ammo, it \r\nfalls on bad guys, that Jar Jar, wow. Then they are trapped, it is Jar \r\nJar\'s time to die, but what luck! That crazy evil Jedi just blew up the \r\ndroid controller ship right before the droids could have done the world a \r\nfavor and killed Jar Jar Binks. What luck! Of course, I do recall a line \r\nonce where a person said "Luck, I don\'t believe in luck". Of course that \r\nwas a long time ago, and George Lucas has changed from one who worships \r\nheros, to one who worships incompetance and foolishness.\r\n\r\nThe Final Solution - In case anyone was unclear on the symbolism in the \r\nnew 52 Wipe version of Star Wars, let me clear it up. When we looked out \r\nthe window from the Naboo Palace and saw the tanks and troops marching \r\nthrough the arch, that was an exact copy of when Hitler took Paris, the \r\narch is fantasticly similar to the Arch de Triumph in Paris. Then the \r\nQueen\'s servants were being rounded up to be sent to "camps". Also don\'t \r\nforget to equate the failure of the Senate to take action with the \r\nweakness of the League of Nations and Churchill\'s plans to just let Hitler \r\nhave the Sudtenland, Poland, the Rhineland, etc... Finally we have Darth \r\nSidious saying his classic line "Wipe them out, All of them." It was \r\nessentially Hitler\'s call for the final solution. Now, I agree that the \r\nHollocoust was horrible. But in this case, I feel that the death of the \r\nNaboo is worthwhile if we can wipe out the GunGuns. The best thing about \r\nwiping out the GunGuns is that Jar Jar would really suffer. You know that \r\nold pick-up line that "if I was the last man on earth...", well imagine if \r\nJar Jar was the last GunGun in the galaxy. First he would probably \r\nsay "Messah, all da GunGuns dead, Messah so sad." But eventually he would \r\nget it through his thick skull that reproduction, even for pleasure is \r\npretty much out for him. Then we would see sad Jar Jar Blinks. Sure, he \r\nwould try to console himself with Galactic whores for a while, and maybe \r\nthat would help, but in the end I\'ll bet we could convince him to allow us \r\nto freeze his body for science, "The Last GunGun". We would of course tell \r\nhim that we would keep his body in a safe place for when we learn how to \r\nclone GunGuns, but in realitiy he would not be placed in an Austin \r\nPowersesce vault, but on display at the musuem. Classes of little whining \r\nannoying kids like Anakin would be brought through to throw shit at him, \r\nand throw up on him. We would have 3D videos telling the story about how \r\nJar Jar was a wuss and hid under a tank while they slaughtered his \r\nfriends, and that is why he survived, he was too pityful to kill. Imagine \r\nthat. Ouchie Time indeed, Motherfucker. \r\n\r\nOne of the only Jar Jar related hilights of the new film was when Qui Gon \r\ncaught his tounge with his hand. Of course, I think he should have pulled \r\nhis lightsaber and cut it off. Hopefully in Episode II, Anakin will grow \r\ntired of Jar Jar and cut his fucking head off. Course that would make him \r\ngo to the light side, by killing such immence evil.\r\n\r\nThat\'s it, if theres anything I left out, or you would like to add, email \r\nme.\r\n\r\nl8r \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', 20010202084359, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (161, 'Thunt\'s Rants: Miramax & Disney making films do different cuts of lines so they can show it on TV.', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'I was watching the Commentary track on Good Will Hunting and I heard \r\nagain, another discusting fact about Disney and Miramax. Matt Damon and \r\nBen Affleck discussed having to record alternate lines with less swearing \r\nso that Disney can show the film on TV. WHAT THE FUCK! If I was them, I \r\nwould tell Disney to go outside and go fuck yourself. It\'s just bullshit. \r\nIt\'s bad enough that they would show a movie like Good Will Hunting on TV \r\nand cut it up with commercials and "trim" down some scenes. I mean, it\'s \r\njust totally fucked up. Well, this is my first rant for the page. It\'s \r\nshort, but do you agree or disagree? Maybe I\'ll put a poll up or some shit \r\nlater. ', '', 20010202084403, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (162, 'Old Thunt.net News #03 - 07.07.99 - 10.03.99', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '\r\n\r\nThuntdate 10.3.99\r\nWriting for the Hornet\r\n\r\nWell, I\'ve been published now, so I think it\'s time to devote some of \r\nThunt.net to the glory of Thomas Hunt: The Hornet Years.\r\n\r\nCheck out my Hornet Articles\r\n\r\nAnd take care of yourselfishness, and eachother.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThuntdate 9.14.99\r\nWriting like Hunter\r\n\r\nFor a while now I\'ve believed that when I read a book that is good enough \r\nto change the way I think, I would end up writting in a style similar to \r\ntheirs. Not exactly the same, but a combination of my own wacked style, \r\nand their style. Well, there comes a time when one must test that theory.\r\n\r\nBefore I walked up here to this terminal, I took another menthol coated \r\ncough suppressent out of my pocket and put it in my mouth. Yummy, I \r\nthought, as the suppressent began supressing my cough, and in some ways my \r\ndepression. This school has too many god damned people in it. Instead of \r\nsitting at a good terminal, I\'m at this shitty one called marcus that has \r\nit\'s monitor too close to other monitors and computers, and hense is \r\nphasing in and out and really freaking me out. Also my chair is shitty, \r\ndespite the fact that it rolls. The people on campus are everywhere. I \r\ncan\'t even get a table to myself at lunch, I have to sit with others and \r\nusually they are smoking like a furnace and chatting away on their god \r\ndamned cell phones, like they could be somewhere else, doing something \r\nmore important, Yeah right! At least the god damned basterds don\'t ask me \r\nfucking directions now that I\'ve got my headphones on, I may look like \r\nsome reject from the generation of music videos in movies that was the \r\n80s, but at least I\'m using a cd player not a cassette deck, and it blows \r\nthe hell out of all the annoying noises of the day. Course, I have be more \r\nalert that someone is going to sneak up on me and put a knife in my back, \r\nending the noise forever, but I\'m already pretty careful, so I\'m not too \r\nworried. New email. Time to save. I mean, who would bear the whips and \r\nscorns of time? Would I? I suppose I would, as always, as Freddy said "The \r\nshow must go on". I don\'t know why it has to, but it just does. This \r\ncomputer is slow as hell. I hate those god damned cell phones, I remember \r\na time, back when you had actual booths to talk in, so that others would \r\nnot hear your important and private conversations, but now that everyone \r\nhas a god damned phone, there are no more boxes, they just walk and talk \r\nand blather on about how their frat is going to have a lot of members, and \r\nhow they are going to be home later tonight and how great it would be to \r\ngo pick up some of the old date rape drug and go out for a little of the \r\nold in-out, in-out tonight. Someday I\'m going to get some headphones that \r\nfit. The girls are really good looking this year. And there are a lot of \r\nthem. Don\'t know what to do about that. I figure I\'ll just wait until they \r\nall get boyfriends from the various frats, and just let it go it\'s normal \r\ncourse. Yes, I know, anger, resentment, judging people, a jedi should not \r\ndo these things. But Yoda was a puppet and had someone\'s hand up his ass \r\nfor a long long time, even in a galaxy far far away. \r\n\r\nAnd enterprises of great pith and moment\r\nWith this regard their currents turn awry,\r\nAnd lose the name of action.\r\n\r\nThe plans of those who are intelligent,\r\nAre frequently fucked over,\r\nBy those who are not intelligent,\r\nDon\'t we live in a fucked up world?\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThuntdate 9.12.99\r\nI watch movies.\r\n\r\nThis weekend while thunt was trying to do his homework, in \r\nprocrastination, he watched:\r\n\r\n\r\nApocalypse Now - As awesome as it usually is, you should go rent it you \r\ndork. Espically if you haven\'t seen it.\r\n\r\n8mm - I have to agree with the tagline I read once on Dark Horizons, \r\nNicolas Cage watches porn, good for him. It was a lot like that. Schumacer \r\n(the destroyer of the batman series) didn\'t do as bad a job as I thought \r\nhe would. The story was ok, but they wussed out on showing alot of the \r\nreally freaky stuff to get their R rating, and they didn\'t delve into \r\nthe "seedy underground" as much as I would have liked them too. If David \r\nFinchner (Seven, The Game) had directed it, it would have been freaky and \r\nawesome. Also Schumacher kept cutting back to this boring backstory about \r\nCage\'s wife and baby kid, I mean who cares, I\'m in this film for "seedy \r\nunderground" not happy family life threatened by "seedy underground", but \r\nseedy underground taking over man\'s life. Needless to say, the underground \r\ndid not transform cage into something cool and seedy, but he did his thing \r\nand left the underground to do its.\r\n\r\nL.A. Story (on DVD from the good folx at Netflix) - I love LA Story. I \r\nlove it because it has many funny scenes and I can\'t get enough of Sarah \r\nJessica Parker being a young and incredibly sexy california bimbo. It \r\nknocks me out every time. Go see it. Written by and Starring Steve Martin. \r\nHe\'s funny. I guarentee it.\r\n\r\nThe Faculty (again on DVD from the good folx at Netflix) - So close, and \r\nyet so far. Two awesome guys made this movie but the couldn\'t decide what \r\nthey wanted to make. Kevin Williamson (writer of Scream, Scream 2, Scream \r\n3) and Robert Rodreguize (director of El Marachi, Desperado) had a good \r\nidea, some fun special effects, and a lot of really good scares, but they \r\nhad no clear path. They should have found direction before they made the \r\nconfused mess that is the faculty. The characters are not realistic they \r\nare more idealistic (see the Star Quarterback who quits the team to work \r\non academics, and the head cheerleader who ends up with the head geek). So \r\nmany good contemporary issues are brought up by the film, but not given \r\nany real concern. Such as the opening scene which discusses why the \r\nfootball team is getting new uniforms, but no new books or computers for \r\neveryone else. Football rules in this town, they say. The faculty is fun \r\nto watch and scares the shit out of you sometimes, because I had no idea \r\nthey had the special effects budget they did, but all in all it comes up \r\nshort. If only they would have had the balls to get really creepy and let \r\nthe bad guys win, or if they decided to do the "bold heros attack evil \r\naliens" movie. Instead they went and inbetween route, with the simple \r\nkilling of the "queen" which of course saved everyone else. Blah.\r\n\r\n\r\nOk, so I\'ve only watched four movies this weekend, but that\'s kind of a \r\nlot consider I was slated to hit the books really hard, which I did. Not \r\nto the degree I wanted to, but enough to get by.\r\n\r\nSo have a nice day, all you people that read thunt.net occasionaly, and \r\nthink about signing up for the thunt.net mailing list (the box to sign up \r\nis in the sidebar).....\r\n\r\nProps to ben for reading the page and replying more than anyone else. \r\n(Hell, he probably is the only one who reads it, boo hoo, boo hoo. ) :> \r\n\r\n\r\nThuntdate 9.10.99\r\nRandomisoity.\r\n\r\nYesterday was 9.9.99. Nothing happened. No end of the world, no massive \r\ncomputer crashes, I guess a bunch of guys paid a lot of money for the \r\ndream cast, but other than that not much else happened. I\'m not too \r\nshocked.\r\n\r\nI have to go to marching band today. blech. Outside, rehersing and shit. \r\nI\'ll bet woody allen doesn\'t have to go to marching band. How does he \r\nwrite so many good movies. he\'s working on a spring project and a fall \r\nproject, that\'s two movies this year. the guy is just fucking rad. As you \r\ncan see my grammer and puncuation are substandard today, but I don\'t care. \r\n\r\nI read a book yesterday: Better than sex, confessions of a political \r\njunkie, by Hunter S. Thompson, it was great. I definately recommend it to \r\nall of you. It was a real kick.\r\n\r\nI\'m reading "fear and loathing on the campaign trail \'72" now. It\'s going \r\nto be fun.\r\n\r\nI think that worshiping the sun makes a lot of sense. You can\'t stare at \r\nit too long. You can\'t say that about statues of Jesus or stuff. It\'s \r\nreally big. You can see it anywhere in the world, even in space. If you \r\nwere far away in space, you could still see it. It\'s that big. You might \r\nneed a telescope or something but I\'ll bet you could still pick it out as \r\na little point of light. And at night it goes away and bad things happen, \r\npeople break into cars, and happy couples have sex, which only causes them \r\npregnancies, abortions, and marriges. Sometimes not in that order. Perhaps \r\nother suns watch over us at night. Perhaps the light from the stars is an \r\nequally powerful deity. Why not? They too are suns who rule over other \r\nsolar systems. No one can live without the sun. It makes plants grow, \r\nfeeds animals, that we then eat. Sun is good. Perhaps we should worship \r\nnot just the sun, but all natural light. Light is good. The sun makes \r\nlight. Light helps me to read my books. This monitor is sending light to \r\nmy eyes. If you have optical cables on your stereo, your sound travels as \r\nlight. Lightspeed! \r\n\r\nthis was Randomisoity. a word I made up and mis-spelled. \r\n\r\n\r\nThuntdate 7.22.99\r\nI will now break the silence of thunt.net for a matter that is very near \r\nand dear to me. (author\'s note: the silence was caused by a repeative \r\nstring of work, eat, sleep, that caused feelings of worthlessness in \r\neverything, including the regular updating of this page. Currently I\'ve \r\nsucceeded in overdosing in Sleep, causing my brain to be realitively awake \r\nat this early 7 o\'clock hour.)\r\n\r\nAhem\r\n\r\n\r\nFuck John F. Kenedy Jr.\r\n\r\n\r\nWhy the hell did we spend so much money finding his god damned body if \r\nthey are going to bury his stupid playboy ass at sea? Really, I mean what \r\nthe fuck! Ok, you can\'t find the body, you bury at sea. Or, you\'re on a \r\ncruise liner for a "3 hour tour" and the body starts to stink, you bury at \r\nsea. Or perhaps you\'re a pirate and you just murdered your captain to \r\nbegin your own advancement. You bury at sea. But if the coast guard spends \r\nfour days and a bunch of wasted TV time (not that I\'ve had time to do a \r\nlittle of the old watch \'n mock) you don\'t bury at sea. I don\'t care if \r\nhis "sexist man alive" ass looks like wrinkled old dog shit, you have a \r\nfucking funeral. They didn\'t bury JFK at sea did they? He was even in the \r\nfucking Navy. He drove a boat, or some shit, he certainly had the right to \r\nbe buried at sea after he was shot. I can only assume they are burying \r\nthis little Jr. fuck at sea because he was such a dumbass (see Denver, \r\nJohn) that he flew his plane poorly in bad weather and killed his dumbass, \r\nhis wife, and her sister (sister my ass, she was part of the whole thing!).\r\n\r\n\r\nWell, I\'m glad I got that off my chest. In closing, Fuck JFK Jr. and Fuck \r\nJFK. Thank you, and good night.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThunt@Defcon date 7.9.99\r\nWell, we arrived in vegas this morning around 10 am. We promptly got lost \r\nfor about an hour while we searched for the hotel that the convention is \r\nat. Eventualy we bought an over priced 6.00 map and that led us there. Now \r\nwe are here. So far, the Defcon webpage has been hacked click. And the CTF \r\ncontest has begun. There is this badkitty chick here signing autographs \r\nand selling her porn page like mad. It\'s wild. Only one or two women at \r\nthe con, and one is selling porn. I might get an interview with her later, \r\nbut I doubt it. We got our picture taken by Canadian Tv, eh. Don\'t know if \r\nthey\'ll show it but it\'s cool. Documentary is ok. I don\'t know if I want \r\nto interview people because everyone is paranoid about their picture being \r\ntaken. Some cool guys from "hack canada" are here.... nice guys. They\'re \r\ndoing "guess the fed panel now" I can hear it in the background, pretty \r\ncool. \r\n\r\nThey\'res a guy with a red spikey mohawk passing out caffene packets. "pure"\r\n\r\nI just talked to a guy named "rep" who writes for Phrack... pretty rad.\r\n\r\nI\'m tired. we drove all night and we don\'t really have a room or a shower \r\nor anything yet... There\'s not enough ice in the cooler.\r\n\r\nmore to come, i\'m going to upload this now, so you all can learn what\'s up.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nOne Day Until Vegas BABY! - Thuntdate 7.8.99\r\nWell, the countdown is down to 1. My last day of work before vegas, I\'m \r\nvery tired and we\'re leaving tonight at 8! It\'s going to be like a 12 hr \r\ndrive. What a long trip, I feel like a member of the donner party, going \r\non an ambitious trip across the country to the promised meal, err land. \r\nIdeas have solidified for the documentary and I should be able to pull off \r\nprinciple photography while i\'m there with no hitches, then all I have to \r\ndo is bring it back, import it into the computer somehow, edit, output, \r\nand I\'m set... :> \r\n\r\nI got a Palm Pro. It\'s neat. More to come later. Must go home and watch: \r\nRambo, Clerks or Ghostbusters on DVD. :>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTwo Days Until Vegas - Thuntdate 7.7.99\r\nIn two days, Thomas Hunt will enter the city of sin, Las Vegas for the \r\nannual Defcon (hacker) Convention. Vegas baby, Vegas.\r\n\r\n\r\nNow, you\'re probably asking, isn\'t Thunt a history major and a future \r\ndirector, what is he doing at Defcon?\r\n\r\nKeeping a Diary of all that happens. \r\nGaining ideas for a script about Defcon \r\nShooting a documentary about the trip to Vegas and the Convention \r\nReporting back to you right here on this webpage \r\nHanging out and looking for beautiful babies. \r\nActing like a wierd combo of Swingers and Fear and Loathing And Much Much \r\nMore!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSo, are you pumped? Are you excited? Are you thinking since Thunt is out \r\nof town it will be a great time to visit Sacramento?\r\n\r\nSo, that\'s about it. VEGAS BABY, VEGAS!!!!!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', 20010202084407, 'flashbacks', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (163, 'Dotcom Detective, Part II', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '\r\n	I still can’t forget the mouth on that bitch yesterday.  There was \r\nsomething about the way she spoke to her present and former employees that \r\njust gave me the creeps.  And I’m a private dick, I should be used to this \r\nkind of language.  But to hear it from a bitch, that’s something else \r\nentirely.\r\n\r\n	After I agreed to take her case yesterday, she took me over to her \r\noffice to meet her staff.  Then for some unknown reason, she just went \r\nberserk.  She beat one employee to the ground screaming “postit ion!  \r\nAssume the postit ion!!”  Then she pulled another employee into her office \r\nand fired her on the spot.  I suppose she was trying to impress me with \r\nthe size of her dick.  But she didn’t realize that private dicks keep \r\ntheir dicks private for the same reason Shaft keeps his public.  There was \r\njust no comparison between her dick and mine, so she paid me the five \r\nhundred and I was on the case.\r\n\r\n	The first thing she wanted me to do was rough up a hooker who \r\nworked in the office under her.  I assumed it was your typical catfight \r\nsituation, but boy was I wrong.\r\n\r\n	I knocked on the door.  It opened a crack, with a chain holding it \r\nclosed.  \r\n\r\n	“Who is it?” she said.\r\n\r\n	“Tina Slinger?”  I said.\r\n\r\n	“Yes?”\r\n\r\n	“My name is Jones.  Your boss Miss Flatlands sent me here to talk \r\nto you.  I was wondering if we might have a word.”\r\n\r\n	“Ok” she said, as she closed and opened the door removing the \r\nchain.  “Come on in.”\r\n\r\n	I walked into her apartment.  It was plush and well decorated in \r\npastels.  The life of a hooker suddenly didn’t seem that bad.\r\n\r\n	“Miss Flatlands tells me that you do tricks in the office.”\r\n\r\n	“Are you interested?” she said, “20 for a blow, 50 for a fuck, and \r\nfor a 100 you can stay all night.”\r\n\r\n	Affordable rates, I thought, and not a bad package as I surveyed \r\nher tight fitting t-shirt and thigh high skirt.  But not today, I \r\nthought.  I’m on a case.\r\n\r\n	“Has Miss Flatlands spoken to you about her disapproval of your \r\nprofession?”\r\n\r\n	“Oh.  Is that what this is all about?  I’m sorry that she’s a \r\nhermaphrodite, detective, I really am.  But I follow the prostitute’s \r\ncode: men yes, women maybe, freaks with both sex organs no.”\r\n\r\n	“That’s quite a code.”\r\n\r\n	“Well mainly its because we weren’t trained in pleasing freaks of \r\nnature.”\r\n\r\n	“I see.”\r\n\r\n	“So what did she want you to do, pound me?”\r\n\r\n	“Yes, she did.”\r\n\r\n	“Well, are you gonna do it or not?”\r\n\r\n	“Not this time.  The hermaphroditic bitch lied to me, and I don’t \r\ndo dishes for lies.  I must get going.  Thank you very much for your time, \r\nMiss Slinger.”\r\n\r\n	“No problem detective, oh and if you’re ever in the neighborhood, \r\ndrop by and I’ll do you for free.  I’m just dying to get my mouth around \r\nthat Private Dick.”\r\n\r\n	Hookers, I thought.  They’re all the same, absolutely in love with \r\nthe LD.  \r\n\r\n	“Sure” I said “I might stop by”, knowing full well that it wasn’t \r\ntrue.  I had other problems to deal with and this neighborhood was the \r\npits.  Frankly, I hoped I’d never come back through this way again.  \r\n	But what to do about this hermaphrodite bitch.  I suppose I’ll \r\nhave to…\r\n\r\n	<I>Will Mr. Jones beat the bitch into a bloody pulp? Will he let \r\nbygones be bygones and take the bitch out for a beer?  Will he attempt to \r\nuse the LD to please the unpalatable hermaphrodite monster?  Find out on \r\nthe next Thunt.net.</I>\r\n\r\n	\r\n', '', 20010202084413, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (164, 'Dotcom Detective, Part III', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '	Well, I’d dealt with the hermaphrodite all right.  But that was a \r\nbloody mess and only psychopaths like Lecter, Bateman, and Caulfield like \r\nto sit around and discuss that kind of shit.\r\n\r\n	Suddenly the clouds parted and the sun shined brighter than I have \r\never seen.  I dropped to my knees as I absorbed all of the glory of God’s \r\ncreation.  Then the Lord came down from heaven and in a voice that sounded \r\nlike Bobcat Goldwaith the Lord exclaimed “Jones?”\r\n\r\n	“Yes?”  I said.\r\n\r\n	“Do you enjoy serving me?” said the Lord.\r\n\r\n	“Well, it beats the hell out of doing laundry.”\r\n\r\n	“Excuse me?”\r\n\r\n	“Uhhh, yes, I greatly enjoy serving you.”\r\n\r\n	“Good, because I have a job for you.”\r\n\r\n	What a week I thought, first I get hired to murder a hooker by a \r\nhermaphrodite with dental problems.  And now God is on my ass.  I’m never \r\ngoing to get to watch that tape of the Super Bowl I made last week.  And \r\nit is only a matter of time before somebody tells me the ending.\r\n\r\n	“Baltimore beat the hell out of them.”  Said God.\r\n\r\n	“What?”\r\n\r\n	“Oh, you didn’t know I could read your thoughts?”\r\n\r\n	“Well, I thought you might be able to but I needed to do an inner \r\nmonologue to keep the readers entertained.  Otherwise it’s all talk talk \r\ntalk.\r\n\r\n	“Hmmm.  Sounds like a good idea.  I’ll have them put some in the \r\nnext version of the Bible.”\r\n\r\n	“When is the street date for that anyway?”\r\n\r\n	God sighs and said “I wanted to release it in 2000, but the \r\nlawyers haven’t cleared the rights yet.”\r\n\r\n	“You have lawyers in heaven?”\r\n\r\n	“They’re on loan from Hell.”\r\n\r\n	“And you think that’s a good idea.”\r\n\r\n	God shrugged and said “You’ve gotta have somebody to throw \r\nlightning bolts at.  And I think the communists and Mormons were getting \r\ntired of the constant anal pain.”\r\n\r\n	“Touché.  So, not to rush you or anything, but what’s the job?”\r\n\r\n	“Well my son, there is a bit of a revolution going on.  I don’t \r\nreally like to talk about it because too many people know already and that \r\ngives the surprise away.  But regardless of what I can tell you, I can \r\ntell you this:  I want you to be in charge of propaganda.”\r\n\r\n	I thought to myself, most people would consider this a holy quest, \r\na gift from the great garbanzo bean, a divine offer from monster.com, but \r\nto me it was just another job.  Although there was something about running \r\npropaganda for God’s revolution that really interested me.  And it sure \r\ndid beat working for hermaphrodites.  So I said, “Sure thing God, when do \r\nI start?”\r\n\r\n	“Tomorrow” he said.  “Tomorrow you will tell the people about my \r\nrevolution.  Tomorrow you will know the reasons that things happen.  And \r\ntomorrow you will all rise up for my revolution.”\r\n\r\n	God is a bit repetitive, I thought, but he sure does know how to \r\ndo a cliffhanger.  Tune in tomorrow to learn more about the revolution.  \r\nRight here on Thunt.net – Inform the masses.\r\n', '', 20010205111041, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (165, 'Dotcom Detective, part IV', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '	So the last time we spoke, I’d been tapped on the shoulder by \r\nGod.  A true holy command.  At first I followed God’s will like a fucking \r\nlap dog.  But no inspiration came.  God had left me hanging out to dry \r\nlike he did to his chosen people time and time again.  That pink whore was \r\ntrying to play me for a fool.  Boy was I angry.  So angry that I felt I \r\nneeded something to relax me and help me forget about God’s vicious ploy.  \r\nSo I stopped in at the local tea house.\r\n	The tea house was decorated in the classical British style.  Lots \r\nof deep rich oak walls, dim lighting and well-dressed men and women \r\nkicking back after a hard day lounging around on their fat rich asses with \r\na cup of tea.  It seemed like the perfect day to kick back and forget the \r\nanger that had plagued me earlier.\r\n	I walked up to the maitre-d and requested a table.\r\n	The cocksucking whore said “I’m sorry sir, but all of our tables \r\nare in use by a private party.”\r\n	Less then a second after he spoke, he knew he had made a mistake \r\nas he felt the cold steel of my .45 magnum on his clammy white temple. \r\n	“I believe you have one empty table.”\r\n	“Ahhh” he cleared his throat and said “we do, sir.  Step right \r\nthis way.”\r\n	That’s right bitch, I thought as I slid the magnum back into my \r\ntrench coat.\r\n	The table was nice but it was right next to the private party that \r\nhad reserved the entire tea house.  Some how I could tell by their top \r\nhats, diamond tiaras, and well dressed man servants standing behind them \r\nthat we weren’t going to get along.\r\n	“Now, what can I get for you sir?”\r\n	“Earl Grey, straight up.” I said, “And make it snappy.”\r\n	“Of course sir.”\r\n	My tea arrived quickly and soon I had a hot cup in my hand.\r\n	“You there.  What are you doing at our private tea party?” said \r\nthe well dressed man who seemed to be the leader of the party.\r\n	“Just sitting here, drinking my tea, trying to relax.” I said.\r\n	“You can’t relax here you commoner!  Get out of our private tea \r\nparty!”\r\n	“Sir, you are making me Angry.”\r\n	“Your anger is disinteresting to me, common man!  Maitre-d, Maitre-\r\nd, remove that thing from our tea party.”\r\n	That was it.  Sometimes these rich fucks go too far.  He’d picked \r\nthe wrong man to mess with.\r\n	I rose from my table and in a single movement I hurled my tea cup \r\nat his face.  It smashed up against his cheek and allowed the searing Earl \r\nGrey to scald his face and neck.  He fell to the ground screaming like a \r\nlittle girl.\r\n	I said to the crowd of horrified debutants, “Who’s next?”\r\n	The rich felchers dispatched their servants to attack me.\r\n	I screamed out, “No! Brothers, let us unite!  Let us have an Angry \r\nTea Party.”\r\n	They stopped and began to contemplate my offer.  Then one of them \r\ngrabbed the tea kettle and poured boiling hot tea on the head of his \r\nmaster ruining her $200 hair cut and her $1500 Armani outfit.  That was \r\nall it took.  The others joined in as we tore that tea room to shreds.  \r\nEvery one of those rich pukes got burned and bruised, including that \r\nasshole maitre-d, who I scalded myself.\r\n	As we were pouring the last of the tea on the remnants of the \r\nparty I realized that I was still in the employee of the Lord.  This is \r\nwhat he wanted me to do.  He wanted me to start an Angry Tea Party and \r\nspread the word that the days of the rich were numbered and that the poor \r\nwere quickly becoming aware of their collective strength.\r\n	With my quest now clearly defined I set forth upon a mission and I \r\ncreated the <a href=http://angryteaparty.com>AngryTeaParty.com website</a>.  The website is a place where all of you will \r\nbe able to spread your anger, drink their tea and have a fucking party.  I ask you, \r\nthe people of this earth to follow God as I have and write for the Angry Tea Party.  \r\nWe need Rants, Reviews and Poetry \r\nto fuel the fire of our revolution.  Rants should be any expression of \r\ngreat power.  It need not be angry but it must be strong in it’s views.  \r\nReviews can be of movies, music or Other.  Other can review anything from \r\nrestaurants, dotcom collapses, shoes, classes, gum, backpack straps, \r\nwebsites, pens, pencils, etc.  Absolutely anything!  Poetry is essentially \r\nthat which is not a review or a rant.  Prose poetry and short stories are \r\nmore than welcome.  The key to the party is you.  We need your help to \r\nmake this the best Angry Tea Party ever!\r\n	So please visit <a href=http://angryteaparty.com>AngryTeaParty.com</a> today and then fire up the old \r\nword processor and show us your true power.  \r\n\r\nWrite for <a href=http://angryteaparty.com>AngryTeaParty.com</a> today and join the revolution! \r\n\r\nEat Snacky Smores!\r\n', '', 20010206110800, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (166, 'Libraries are Crooks!  They must be stopped!', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '', '', 20010207111936, 'net_interest', 'washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/articles/A36584-2001Feb7.html');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (167, 'Facts, Rumors and False Truths', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '\r\nAhhh, the demand of the people for new content.  Since the people are \r\ndemanding it, I’ve decided to pull a few rumors out of the old rumor mill \r\nand print them here on Thunt.net.  Since, like the Hornet, we have no \r\njournalistic standards, I see no reason why I shouldn’t print these \r\nharmless rumors.  Remember the key word here is rumor.  Rumor can \r\nsometimes mean false.  Other times it can mean true.  It’s up to you, True \r\nBeliever to make your decision and see the lies. (Or the truth)\r\n\r\n<B>“Fucking Incompetent” </B>\r\n\r\nLet’s talk about these words.  These words are a mighty insult; an insult \r\nthat I’m sure none of you thunt.neters would take sitting down.  These \r\nwords are a direct attack on your ability to do your job correctly, but \r\nlet us guess who these words have been labeled upon recently.  Could it be \r\nthat one estranged AD told one E that she was “FUCKING INCOMPENTANT”?  \r\nCould that be true?  Well it is true because that’s what I’ve heard from \r\nthe extensive grapevine streaming out from the hornet, the grapevine that \r\nI try to ignore, but hey, when it’s this good, how can I “just say no”?  \r\n\r\n<B> “Embarrassed about the paper?” </B>\r\n\r\nWell, we all knew this was going to be a year from the record books.  As \r\nthe selection of the false E was closed last year, we all discussed it and \r\nwe all knew how bad it would be.  Even full-time members of the hornet \r\nsadly stated, “Some years, you know it’s going to be a good year and some \r\nyears you know it’s going to be a bad year.” Some knew that it would be \r\nworse than others.  But let us, right here on thunt.net (I’m referring to \r\nmy friends and enemies in the message board), lets get all of the goods \r\nand bads out on the table and decide how bad it really is.  I’ve heard all \r\nkinds of horrible stories from the Hornet’s recent past.  I heard that a \r\nfew years ago, a totally wacked Editor in Chief ran a story on the front \r\npage stating that the newly built Mendocino Hall was really a landing pad \r\nfor G’s Martian Buddies.  He later wrote a letter against our dearest \r\nfaculty-advising friends, distributed it to all of the faculty mailboxes \r\nand fled the country in disgrace.  The funny thing about that story is \r\nthat I’ve always rooted for him, not the faculty advisors.  It’s funny how \r\nsometimes the bad guy is really the good guy.  So, back to modern times.  \r\nThere is no doubt that everyone has read Vince’s letter to the editor from \r\nlast week and David’s letter this week (that I had the pleasure of \r\npreviewing on one of those neat printouts that look like the paper, you \r\nknow what I’m talking about, boy it’s neat to be outside and yet see so \r\nmuch).  They were both pretty damn disappointed in the Hornet’s latest \r\nstripper escapades and complete lack of reporting.  These are pretty \r\nstrong charges from former hornet faithful.  Moreover, with the way things \r\nhave been going in the message board it’s clear that I, while once the \r\nvillain of the office am now being raised to the level of savior.  \r\nAlternatively, if not savior, at least now, I am in perfect position to \r\nsay, “I told you so”.  And nothing is better than that.  “I told you so.”  \r\nIn addition to David and Vince’s indignation I’ve also had the pleasure of \r\ntalking to last years designer savant, who also expressed some of the same \r\nideas espoused by Mr. Sommers and Mr. Faola.  (She’ll probably kick my ass \r\nfor mentioning her here, but hey, I’ve got a big ass and I’m sure I’ll \r\nheal.)  So the paper sucks, all of the “hard” work of the little men could \r\nnot save them from their evil boss.  I hope that next week they write \r\nanother article without facts and suck on G’s big dick some more.  Why do \r\nI say hope, let’s face it, we all know what they’re going to do next \r\nweek.  What a sweet future lies ahead, oh my brothers and only friends.\r\n\r\n<B> “False E?” </B>\r\n\r\nWell, it’s been a while, and I’ve stopped my mouth from spreading rumors \r\nlong enough.  It is a year of stolen elections and it is time to expunge \r\nold rumors from my closet.  Now let me remind you Junior Crimestoppers out \r\nthere that these are rumors.  I’m not saying that they’re true or \r\nanything.  They could be as false as the Apollo Moon Landing; I’m just \r\nusing my right to free speech (knock, knock) to say what I’ve heard, no \r\nmore, no less.\r\n\r\nWhat I heard was during last years voting for E, there was a minor coup \r\ndetat played by America’s favorite player (not shaft).  1. They were \r\nsupposed to hold to vote until one voting member returned from a meeting.  \r\nThey didn’t. 2. Other student votes were not present at the meeting.\r\nThere were three candidates for E.  We will call them by cute nicknames as \r\nwe always do here at thunt.net.  One candidate was named Clueless-\r\nOutsider.  Clueless-Outsider had an excellent standing and reputation with \r\nthe student body but knew nothing about newspapers.  One candidate was \r\nnamed Decent-Man.  Decent-Man was a decent man; he’d done nothing wrong, \r\nbut hadn’t really done anything right.  He was decent and would have done \r\na decent job.  One candidate was named Clueless-Insider.  It was clear by \r\nhis performance inside, that he was absolutely clueless, despite his cool \r\ninside status.  America’s Favorite Player had a really cool plan.  If \r\nClueless-Outsider becomes E, then I can rule him and run the paper my \r\nself. (Insert evil laughter, HAHAHAHAHAHA)  The voters heard the speeches \r\nand AFP called for a vote.  The vote was won by Decent-Man.  Hooray for \r\nDecency and good will!  Clueless-Insider came in third, as no one really \r\nwanted him.  And the AFP led Clueless-Outsider came in a close second.  \r\nWell, according to the rules this vote is it, congratulations Decent-Man, \r\nright?  No.  Wrong.  The AFP said that even though she wanted the vote, \r\nthat the board should talk about it some more.  The board, without any \r\nstudent representatives, said, “Sure, lets break the law, that would be \r\ncool, fuck Decent-Man!”  The board then discussed, discussed and \r\ndiscussed.  Finally, they were deadlocked.  The two Clueless-Outsider \r\ncamps and Decent-Man camps were dead even.  So what did they do, they \r\nchose Clueless-Insider as a compromise.  This worked out great for all \r\nparties.  The board got to go home.  The AFP got someone she could \r\ncontrol.  Although not as easy to control as Clueless-Outsider, but hey, \r\nwhen you’re evil, you can’t win em all.  And that is the story of the \r\nrumor of the Election.  (Please note that for you trying to prescribe \r\nadditional meaning to my parable, please insert Al Gore for Decent-Man.  I \r\nknow it was a transparent label, but I wouldn’t want poor Al to feel bad.)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', 20010216083024, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (168, 'Sunday Procrastination', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '\r\nBoy do I have expensive tastes.  Here I am crusing around the web, and I \r\nspot <a href="http://dv8.org/~dcoker/events/">Doug\'s page of photos</a>.  \r\nNice photos, shot by a digital camera, outlining where doug\'s been \r\nrecently.  If you check the portland and the defcon sections, you can even \r\nfind pictures of yours truly.  And I think to myself, damn I\'m so jelous \r\nof doug\'s page full of memories.  So now I want a digital camera.  \r\nSomething I totally can\'t afford.  Seeing how I just bought a mini disc \r\nplayer/recorder and a fair ammount of CDR media.  How can I be torn \r\nbetween such capitalism and anti-capitalism.  \r\n\r\nSo much to do, but procrastination is so good.  \r\n\r\nCollege College College, \r\nRead Read Read.  \r\n\r\n\r\n', '', 20010218111801, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (169, 'What would happen if my other professors met my ethnics studies professor', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'I have a class that I absolutely cannot stand.  Ethnics Studies 11.  My \r\nprofessor treats us like children because there are freshmen in the class \r\nand lets face facts, they are children.  In addition, she feels that \r\nbecause she is a professor now she does not have to do any research before \r\nspouting out her conclusions and that everything she says is pure truth, \r\nbecause she said it.  I would now like to examine, for my entertainment \r\nand perhaps yours, what would happen if my other professors, who actually \r\ndo research and are generally knowledgeable about their subjects were to \r\nmeet this Ethnic studies professor and were forced to suffer through her \r\nclass with me.\r\n\r\nEnglish 50 – My English 50 professor would no doubt scoff at her belief \r\nthat literary characters are real people.  Her example today was that the \r\nbook <I>The Indian in the Cupboard</I> was racist and she asked why the \r\nbook was not the other way around (The White Boy in the Cupboard).  He \r\nwould laugh at her and remind her as he reminds us that literary \r\ncharacters are not real.  To do a Freudian analysis of Hawthorn is foolish \r\nbecause Hawthorn is not following Freud.  He is following his own \r\nbeliefs.  Not to mention that the characters in his books are no real.  \r\nThe do not do anything other than what is written on the page.  Tom Sawyer \r\nwill never die, because Twain did not write that chapter.  They are \r\nfictional, NOT REAL!  \r\n	Also on the subject of <I>The Indian in the Cupboard</I> she \r\nstated that it is so hard to “regulate ideas”.  It was amazing.  She was \r\ntalking pure Orwellian censorship and the whole class sat silent before \r\nher learned opinion.  If I thought she was interested in discussion I \r\nwould have responded but I am well aware that the only opinion that \r\nmatters is her own.  This part of the class was fantastic.  I only wish I \r\nhad a tape recorder with me so I could have caught the words of this \r\nlatter-day PC Thug and passed them along, they were stunning.\r\n\r\nAnthropology 102 – My Anthro Professor would have no doubt pointed out to \r\nthis uniformed fool that when she spoke of why anthropology seems to cover \r\nother cultures as “the other”, that it is the main point of anthropology \r\nto study “other” cultures.  Yes, they seem to be treating the Indians like \r\ntheir culture is different from the culture they are writing their papers \r\non their word processors, with their faxes, phone calls and emails.  Well \r\nguess what!  The CULTURES ARE DIFFERENT!  The anthropologists are trying \r\nto study them!  It is necessary to acknowledge these differences when \r\nstudying them. In addition, she would point out that the use of the word \r\nshaman does separate the “Indian Doctors” from our modern scientific \r\ndoctors.  Shamans used witchcraft, magic, and herbs to cure people, while \r\nour modern doctors use the scientific method and western scientific \r\nmedicine.  There is a difference.  Shamans are not doctors.  Sure, to your \r\ntribe they were doctors, but because they lack x-ray machines and shit, \r\nthey are not modern doctors.  Maybe you could call them healers because \r\ntheir goals are to heal, but the ENGLISH word DOCTORS implies SCIENCE.  NO \r\nSCIENCE, NO DOCTOR.\r\n\r\nHistory 162 – My History 162 Professor, who is also my hero, would \r\nprobably throw shit at this misinformed professor.  He would point out \r\nthat everything she has taught us so far and everything she is endeavoring \r\nto teach is VICTIUMOLOGY.  IE: The study of the horrible things that the \r\npeople of the past did.  So far we have learned that the people of the \r\npast were bad to immigrants, made stereotypes, had slaves, i.e.: THEY WERE \r\nBAD.  It is amazing that she can fill a whole semester with the horrors of \r\nthe people of the past but she is doing good so far.  In addition, the \r\nonly people who seem to be good are the people who taught her, the \r\nenlightened minds of the 60s.  Did I mention she went to Berkeley?  It \r\nsure is true that before the 60s at Berkley, everyone was bad.  And after \r\nthe 60s at Berkley, everyone was good.  What an amazing time the 60s \r\nwere.  Gosh, I’m so glad to live in the good times that the 60s created, \r\nwe are so lucky.  Otherwise we would be bad like those slime balls of the \r\npast.\r\n	Also the esteemed published History Professor would smack her for \r\nthe way she does research.  She went to Roseville or some other god damned \r\nplace and someone tried to give the parking spot they were pulling out of \r\nto someone else, not HER! It was obviously because they were RACIST.  Do \r\nyou know why she sees racism everywhere she goes, it’s because she’s \r\nLOOKING FOR IT.  It is a common rule when studying History to not have \r\nyour conclusions made before you do your research.  If you have your \r\nconclusions made you will ignore other evidence that doesn’t support your \r\nconclusion, it happens all the time.  Let us examine her story.  1.  She \r\ndoesn’t note what direction the exits of the parking lot were.  Perhaps \r\nthis man was simply turning in the direction that he was going.  I do not \r\nexpect him to go in the direction away from his destination just to please \r\nthe angry native american driving the mini-van.  2. Perhaps these two \r\npeople knew each other and he was trying to be friendly to an \r\nacquaintance.  There are dozens of other factors that could have been \r\nvital to telling the story, but she left all of those out so that she \r\ncould present her BIASED story to the class as TRUTH.  \r\n\r\nHistory 192 – My History 192 professor would probably try to explain to \r\nher using evidence.  We just read a book about the great plains (<I>The \r\ncontested plains</I> by Elliot West) that clearly proved that the native \r\namericans underwent dozens of changes in their culture before and after \r\nthe white man came.  They were not a perfect society, an Eden, as she \r\nbelieves.  Also he might point out what another great History Professor \r\nonce said “The people who complain about the white man should examine the \r\nwork of the Mongols.  When the Mongols came you wouldn’t have any of your \r\nculture or your land because they would kill every last man woman and \r\nchild and take your land and wipe out your culture.”  They were lucky that \r\nthe Mongols never invaded North America or things would have been very \r\ndifferent.\r\n\r\nWell, I think that’s enough of a rant for today.  This class sucks, but I \r\nhave to take it to graduate (that’s another rant for another day).  \r\n', '', 20010221105802, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (170, 'ThuntLife: Roll #01', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'Well, after my gushing last week over dougs rad photo gallery, I went out \r\nand shot a roll of film and now (thanks to doug\'s rad script) it\'s online! \r\nWOOOO\r\n\r\n<a href="http://thunt.net/thuntphotos/roll01/">Click here for Roll #01</a>\r\n\r\nAnd now a brief outline of the photos.  I suggest you open two windows and \r\nread the comments as you view the photos.... (in the future I will have a \r\nsuperior way of viewing comments and photos, but at 8:30 AM on a saturday \r\nwith a test and a project due next week, I\'m just glad I had the time to \r\nget the scanning done.)\r\n\r\nThe photos were shot by Thunt approx Feb 12-16, 2001.\r\nThe photos were shot on a Kodak Cameo Instamatic Camera using 35mm color \r\nfilm.  Developing was handled by Albertsons (formerly Luckys).  Film cost \r\nand developing costs were covered by a generous grant from the Thomas Hunt \r\nFoundation.  Thumbnails were created by Doug Coker\'s cool thumb.pl script. \r\nScanning by Thunt with a assistance from HP.  Cropping by Paint Shop Pro \r\n7.0 the program you download when you don\'t have photoshop installed on \r\nyour machine.\r\n\r\n1. A golf club\r\n\r\n2. Josh, the whitest boy in my ethnics studies class.\r\n\r\n3. Shane, now in Austria.  Probably still on the phone.\r\n\r\n4. Mike, with that whole bug-eyed thing going on.\r\n\r\n5. Sarah, looking frightned and confused by Thunt\'s Camera.\r\n\r\n6. Chris, sick and in a bad mood, Chris is probably going to kick my ass.\r\n\r\n7. Chris, showing his clear intent to kick my ass.  Will the more subtle \r\nviewer please note the shadows on Chris\'s face and the over exposure of \r\nthe finger.  \r\n\r\n8. Thunt himself.  Photo credit: Sarah. (note the high quality photo, she \r\nused to be photo editor at the Hornet.  Good job Sarah.)\r\n\r\n9. Pat, this is one of the few photos of my boss on Camera.  Normally he \r\nmoves so fast that he can not be caught on normal speed film.\r\n\r\n10. Sun, this is a really great photo.  Catching the sun almost directly \r\ninto the camera created a great lens flare and the rest of the shot has a \r\nvery erie quality.  Serene, but deadly.  I\'d pat myself on the back more, \r\nbut you can look at the photo yourself, it\'s nice.\r\n\r\n11. Josh, and John, a couple of bad asses walking down the street smoking \r\ntheir cigarettes.  Kind of reminds me of reservior dogs.\r\n\r\n12. Sunset, with a fense.  Honestly, this didn\'t come out to great, but \r\nthe idea here is to present you with a whole roll, goods and bads, gods \r\nand clods.  Go back to picture 10, that\'s a good one. :>\r\n\r\n13. Richelle, with eyes closed.  You can\'t have too many pictures of \r\npeople with their eyes closed.  Of course, I think that red eye shit is \r\nmuch cooler than closed eyes.\r\n\r\n14. Hornet Jeep being towed #1. ***\r\n\r\n15. Hornet Jeep being towed #2, note the nice lense flare, the sun is so \r\ncool.  I hope that it is a major player in many of my pictures. ***\r\n\r\n16. Hornet Jeep being towed #3. ***\r\n\r\n16. Hornet Jeep being towed #4. ***\r\n\r\n18. Row of Newstands, guess which one belongs to the hornet.  Please note, \r\nas an honest nature photographer I did not adjust my subject in anyway.  \r\nThis is the way the newstand has been for weeks in the wild.  \r\n\r\n19. Mike, on his unicycle.  [Unicycle not pictured]\r\n\r\n20. My Car.\r\n\r\n21. Andy showing off his work.\r\n\r\n22. Matt and Mike impressed with Andy\'s work.\r\n\r\n23. Andy shoots a hole-in-one and we finish off the roll.\r\n \r\n*** Please note, I will be discussing the towing of the jeep and other \r\nHornet related events on Monday.  Please check back then.  Think of the \r\nweekend as a good time to ponder.  Why is the Jeep being towed?  Why God? \r\nWHY?!?\r\n\r\n', '', 20010224082840, 'normal', '');
