INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (191, 'In honor of the death of kings', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'In Honor of the death of kings\r\n(the ides of march)\r\n\r\n\r\nA lone man sits in his chair by the window watching the grass sway back \r\nand forth on the open praire.  The sky is a vibrant orange as the sun \r\nslowly sets.  As the sun fades behind the mountain the man pulled back the \r\nhammer on the shotgun and slowly brought it to his shoulder.  He looked \r\nagain out the window longingly.  He sighed and pulled the trigger.\r\n\r\nThat was three weeks ago.  Three weeks ago that Lawerence Henry committed \r\nsuicide.  What impacts did this have on the world?  The unfortnate answer: \r\nseveral.  Henry was a bit of a stock owner you see.  A bit as he owned 35% \r\nof IBM and 45% of Cisco Systems.  It goes without saying that the market \r\ntook a little dump.  What do I mean by a little dump?  I mean when you \r\nwake up after a bender and find a dumptruck sized load of shit in your \r\npants and wonder if you really had a good time or not.  Because of the \r\nmarket crash a record 352 people committed suicide last week.  Which we \r\ncan only correctly state as a record because during the first week after \r\nhis death there were only 125 and during the second week a mere 250.  352 \r\nis quite a number when you make these kind of comparisions.  Sure, a mere \r\n727 people have left the earth because of this man\'s death.  Make that 728 \r\nincluding the man himself, but I would like to think that this is a little \r\nextreme because one old man decides to kill himself.  I would like to \r\nthink that people have a little more control than that.  I would like to \r\nthink that we live in a world of sanity and not a world of insanity.  But \r\nwhat I like to think doesn\'t mean a god damned thing to anyone else.  Only \r\nto me and I suppose since you\'re reading this it means something to you.  \r\nThe world has gotten out of hand.  I know it\'s a lousy transition but \r\nyou\'re reading my mind right now and sometimes I shift from train to train \r\nwithout telling you.  Like a Beatles song that ends abruptly because of a \r\nbad rip I reserve the right to go anywhere I want.  And I\'ll be sure to \r\ntake you with me.  The world has gotten out of hand.  The power of the few \r\nhas never meant so much to the many.  Buying and selling is all that \r\nremains of the culture.  Buying.  Selling.  Buying again.  You can\'t stop \r\nbuying can you?  Well neither can I.  And how can I expect to stop?  With \r\nnew things commign out every day?  New techologies?  New toys? New movies? \r\nNew CDs?  I just gotta have them all and you do too.  I know you do.  In \r\nfact you\'re probably thinking about buying something right now, because \r\nthat\'s the way our bankrupt culture works.  Got a girlfriend? You\'d better \r\nbuy her something if you want to keep her.  Got a wife?  Don\'t forget your \r\nanniversary or your ass is in the shitter.  I\'m not kidding about this \r\nshit.  I can\'t tell you how many relationships ended because of the lack \r\nof roses or the size of someone\'s diamond.  It\'s not a metaphor I\'m \r\ntalking about the size of the rock here.  And no, you one testicaled \r\nfreaks out there, I\'m speaking about diamonds and nothing else.  \r\n\r\nLawerence Henry is dead and the economy has gone to shit.  But let\'s face \r\nit.  Things were pretty shitty before the economy crashed weren\'t they?  \r\nYou had just a good a reason to do it then as you did now right?  The \r\nworking man is left with little power in this world, with the exception of \r\nhis vote and the right to return products to Target.  And hell, they don\'t \r\neven count the votes anymore so what\'s the point.  The rich run it all, \r\nfrom Microsoft to the Presidency there was no aspect of this world not \r\ncontrolled by Lawerence or one of his fraternity brothers.  They all may \r\nnot have nicknames and sweaters but in the end they all belong to the \r\nfraternity of inheritance and private propety.  Property being the kind \r\nusually Ľ the size of Wyoming, with armed guards ensuring that the sign \r\nreads correctly.  There will be no tresspassing.  Maybe all that matters \r\nis that the poor remain happy with their Beatles records and their race \r\nbased inner class conflict.  I suppose there is some joy in that.  \r\n', '', 20010315071049, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (192, 'Starbucks To Begin Sinister \'Phase Two\' Of Operation', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '', '', 20010317081624, 'net_interest', 'http://www.theonion.com/onion3709/starbucks_phase_two.html');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (193, 'Ryan Anne Dead', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '</pre>\r\n<img src=http://thunt.net/images/ryan-anne-dead.gif><br>\r\n<pre class=normal>\r\nIt is our sad duty to report the passing of long time supporter of \r\nThunt.net, Ms. Ryan Anne Polli of Wilton, California.  \r\n\r\nMost recently, Ryan broke the record for longest staff member at the State \r\nHornet, serving six consecutive semesters as art director.  Her major \r\naccomplishments while at the paper included: redesign of the front page, \r\nwinning of the prestigious pacemaker award and seduction of the editor-in-\r\nchief.  Her successor, Andy Duong proudly stated that he "has accomplished \r\ntwo of her three major accomplishments and he hopes to be successful on \r\nthe third before the semester comes to a close."  Ryan continued her \r\npassion for graphic design excellence or excellence in graphic design as \r\nshe liked to say right up until her unfortunate fiery death.  Most \r\nrecently she was involved in pimping her boyfriend\'s band Silent Horizon \r\nto the before mentioned State Hornet.  Ryan hoped that one day her \r\nboyfriend Matt Linder would become a Christian Rock Superstar (like Jesus) \r\nand dump her for a younger blonder taller thinner blacker bluer redder \r\nwhiter blacker more religious (crucifix masturbating champion) exorcist-\r\nproof woman.  Ryan hoped that her future would lead her to accomplishing \r\nher dream of spending her days drawing pictures of pretty pretty pretty \r\npretty ponies, but alas this was not the case.\r\n\r\nAccording to the Thunt.net Message Board, "Ryan was on her way home from \r\nchurch with her boyfriend, and she got in a car wreck."  She unfortunately \r\npassed away at 11:30 am, March 18, 2001 at the Bradshaw Veterinarian \r\nClinic (which was the nearest trauma center to the scene of the \r\naccident).  According to Doctor Mephisto, treatment with animal \r\ntranquilizers on hand proved unsuccessful.  Doctor Mephisto later \r\nattempted to revive the patient by performing an emergency neutering, but \r\nalas, this too proved to be unsuccessful.\r\n\r\nFormer boss and one-time boyfriend David Sommers, when reached for comment \r\nsaid "Dammit, just when I thought we were on the road to hooking back up, \r\nshe had to go and die on me, now I\'ll have to find someone else to stalk.  \r\nBut regardless, I\'m incredibly pleased to see that when you hire an \r\nassassin from the Endeen Assassination Corporation (EAC) that it looks \r\njust like an accident.  I can honestly say that I have never been more \r\nsatisfied from spending twenty bucks.  I\'m so glad I finally found a use \r\nfor the profits from my Campus Engine stock."  Ryan\'s one time friend \r\nCandice Luse was rather broken up over Ryan\'s passing and simply \r\nsaid "What a relief, maybe the dreams will stop now."  Sarah Sieber, long \r\ntime friend and confidant said, "I will have exclusive photo rights for \r\nthe funeral.  As usual, I\'ll be shooting for Thunt.net.  And now, I \r\nfinally have a shot at Davey Sommers, I think he\'s sooooooo cute." \r\n\r\nAfter much investigation, we were able to reach Mr. Dusty Wolf (who spoke \r\non the condition of anonymity) at a gay commune in the South Seas.  Mr. \r\nWolf suggested that we call his commune, a sanctuary for alternative \r\nlifestyles, we told him to go fuck himself, which he promptly did.  Mr. \r\nWolf seemed to have used a great deal of acid, but we interviewed him \r\nanyway.  Mr. Wolf, when asked about Ryan, had a lot to say.  "A lot of \r\npeople know I had a thing for Ryan, but that was simply because she had a \r\nboy\'s name.  It was butch; it makes me horny just thinking about it.  I \r\nfeel warm in my bathing suit area, like that time in the hot tub…. Oh and \r\nDavid\'s couch, that was fun" said Mr. Wolf.\r\n\r\nShe is survived by her parents Stephen and Anne Polli and several horses.  \r\nOne horse named Blacky, when asked to comment said "More oats for me."  \r\nAnother horse however did not share his contented outlook; Mr. Clompy \r\nsaid, "It is a very sad day for horses, wulwululuwluwluwluwluw."\r\n\r\n', '', 20010319001149, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (194, 'Police sketch released', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '\r\nWith Ryan Endeen, head of the EAC (Endeen Assassination Corporation) \r\ndenying responsibility for the punctured tire that led Ryan Anne Polli\'s \r\ncar to crash, we must now take into account that there must have been a \r\nsecond shooter on the grassy knoll that sunny March day.  We at Thunt.net \r\nhave managed to locate a copy of the police sketch of this "second \r\ngunman".  We present it to you the readers of Thunt.net, but we warn you \r\nthat this sketch is not pretty.  The person pictured in this sketch is a \r\nroyal bitch and is one of the ringleaders in Ryan\'s unfortunate \r\nassassination.  If you see this dirty bitch anywhere, do not attempt to \r\napprehend her, please call the police immediately.  Only by uniting with \r\nthe authorities, can we catch the perpetrators of this heinous crime.  \r\nFinally, without any further ado we give you the police sketch what could \r\nbe Ryan\'s assassin:\r\n</pre>\r\n<div class=normal align=center>\r\n\r\n<a href=http://www.thunt.net/images/comics/initial_sketch.jpg> Click here \r\nto view the sketch</a><br>\r\n(Warning: Sketch is not for little children.)<br>\r\n\r\n<pre class=normal>\r\n\r\n', '', 20010319221422, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (195, 'Ryan Dead Chat tonite at 8!', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'Gentle and loyal readers of Thunt.net, we need your help to bring Ryan\'s \r\nkillers to justice!  Only you possess the knowledge and natural good looks \r\nto help us solve this case.  \r\n\r\nWe will be having a meeting of the Thunt.net Justice League tonight (wed) \r\nin the Thunt.net chat room at 8:00 pm.\r\n\r\n<U>Topics that will be discussed</U>\r\n\r\n  -  Why do girls pluck their eyebrows?\r\n  -  Why do girls have false eyelashes unless they are also plucking\r\n     their eyelashes?\r\n  -  Does Thunt.net need a chat room?\r\n  -  Who killed Ryan?\r\n  -  Who wanted her dead?\r\n  -  Who benefits?\r\n  -  And of course: Who cares?\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', 20010321082949, 'normal', '');
