INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (248, 'All Along The Watchtower', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'Words and Music by Bob Dylan\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nThere must be some kind of way out of here<BR>\r\n Said the joker to the theif<BR>\r\n There\'s too much confusion<BR>\r\n I can\'t get no relief<BR>\r\n Business men they drink my wine<BR>\r\n Plowmen dig my earth<BR>\r\n None will level on the wine<BR>\r\n Nobody of it is worth<BR>\r\n<BR>\r\n No reason to get exited<BR>\r\n The thief he kindly spoke<BR>\r\n There are many here among us<BR>\r\n Who feel that life is but a joke<BR>\r\n But you and I we\'ve been through that<BR>\r\n And this is not our fate<BR>\r\n So let us talk falsely now<BR>\r\n The hour\'s getting late<BR>\r\n<BR>\r\n All along the watchtower<BR>\r\n The princess kept the view<BR>\r\n While all the women came<BR>\r\n And went bare feet servants too<BR>\r\n Outside in the cold distance<BR>\r\n A wild cat did growl<BR>\r\n Two riders were aproaching<BR>\r\n And the wind began to howl<BR>\r\n<BR>', '', 20010518112114, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (249, 'Six pairs of Tities and a Fire', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '<I>\r\nAlright. Now dig this, baby.<BR>\r\n<BR>\r\nYou don\'t care for me, I don\'t care about that.<BR>\r\nYou got a new fool ha! I like it like that.<BR>\r\nI have only one a burnin\' desire.<BR>\r\nLet me stand next to your fire,<BR>\r\n</I><br>\r\nWhat a night.  I got about four hours sleep and I don\'t mind too much.  \r\nLet me set the scene for you….<BR>\r\n<BR>\r\nIt\'s 2:25 in the morning.  I\'ve been sleeping for about four hours now.  I \r\nhear someone outside screaming "Thomas!".  I assume it\'s Andy who has \r\nwoken Matt and I up for such exciting events as: "Andy Arrives \r\nHome", "Andy and Andrea come home from a dance" and "I\'m Andy! I\'m \r\nDrunk!".  He bangs on the door, he rings the doorbell repeatedly, but at \r\n2:25 in the morning and knowing his track record of idiocy, I’m content to \r\nride it out.  Finally at 2:30 he stops.  "Hurrah!", I said, "I won\'t have \r\nto kill Andy today". <BR>\r\n<BR>\r\n<I>\r\nYou know that it would be untrue<BR>\r\nYou know that I would be a liar<BR>\r\nIf I was to say to you<BR>\r\nGirl, we couldn\'t get much higher<BR>\r\n</I><BR>\r\nThen he starts again and this time he yells out "There\'s a fire next \r\ndoor".  This deserves real punishment I think, joking about a fire to wake \r\nus up is really low, even for Andy.  So I get out of bed, put my robe on \r\nand begin thinking about how I\'m going to grab Andy by the throat and \r\npunch him in the head until he passes out in a bloody heap.  Then I think \r\nI\'ll tie him to a tree and hang him upside down until morning so he can \r\nunderstand the difference between friends and enemies. <BR>\r\n<BR>\r\n<I>The time to hesitate is through<BR>\r\nNo time to wallow in the mire<BR>\r\nTry now we can only lose<BR>\r\nAnd our love become a funeral pyre</I><BR>\r\n<BR>\r\nAs I rush to the door, I notice that Matt is already up ahead of me and I \r\nrush out the open front door.  I look out across the street and see a huge \r\norange fireball, "Holy Shit!" I say, Andy wasn\'t lying.  Now that\'s a \r\nsentence you don\'t hear very often, and thus deserves repeating, Andy \r\nwasn\'t lying.  By this time, I was still looking around for Andy, but he \r\nwas nowhere to be found because it wasn\'t Andy yelling at us, ringing our \r\ndoorbell, banging on the door and throwing pennies at our windows, it was \r\nAndy\'s roommate Joe.  Suddenly the entire story shifted, because Joe, \r\nunlike Andy, knows when you should wake up your roommates and a huge fire \r\nacross the street is an excellent reason.  <BR>\r\n<BR><I>\r\nThat\'s what I\'m talkin\' about<BR>\r\nNow dig this. Ha! Now listen baby! <BR>\r\n<BR>\r\nYou try to give me your money. You better save it, babe. <BR>\r\nCome on baby, light my fire<BR>\r\nSave it for your rainy day. <BR>\r\nCome on baby, light my fire<BR>\r\nI have only one a burnin\' desire. <BR>\r\nTry to set the night on fire, yeah<BR>\r\nLet me stand next to your fire, </I><BR>\r\n<BR>\r\nThe entire roof of the apartment complex across the street was engulfed \r\nwith the fire, there was also a great deal of sparking and noise like the \r\nfire had hit a fireworks or ammunition stash, but closer examination \r\nshowed that it was an electrical fire, with blue sparks popping and \r\nflashing from the corner of the roof.  The entire neighborhood was out on \r\nthe streets watching this thing.  The fire department was there in force, \r\nabout 3 or 4 fire engines, a paramedics van, a chiefs car and much much \r\nmore.  After about five minutes of shock, I ran upstairs to get my video \r\ncamera and Matt\'s digital camera and we went to work.  Unfortunately when \r\nI got back outside, the Fire Department had taken care of most of the \r\nfire, but we still got some excellent photos by Matt, available here: <a \r\nhref=\'http://thunt.net/photo/fire\'>thunt.net/photo/fire</a>.  The video of \r\nthe fire will be up in a few days.<BR>\r\n<BR>\r\n<I>Ah, move over, Rover. And let Jimi take over. <BR>\r\nYeah, you know what I\'m talkin\' about. <BR>\r\nYeah. Get on with it, baby</I><BR>\r\n<BR>\r\nWhat about the Six pairs of Tities?  Well lets just say my mildly wild \r\nnight of Fire wasn\'t the only thing happening that evening.  The six pairs \r\nof tities are a whole different story all together.  A story that must be \r\ntold by Joe Rodriguez, in video form.  So, stay tuned to Thunt.net, as we \r\nexplore: Six pairs of Tities and a fire.  <BR>\r\n<BR>\r\n', '', 20010519104312, 'normal', '');
