INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (269, 'Weather and Grunge', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'As I sit here up in Ft. Collins I think back to Sacramento.  Yesterday I \r\ntalked to my good friend Justin who informed me that you guys were in the \r\nmiddle of a heat wave and that it was over 100 degrees there.  Wow, that \r\nmust be hot.  It\'s hard for me to understand such heat as I glance out on \r\nthe mountains, which I can barely see because there are clouds blocking \r\nthem out.  It\'s about 65-70 degrees here; with a slight mist from the \r\nrecent rain and the clouds overhead insure that there will be more rain \r\nthis afternoon.  So I just thought I\'d gloat a little.  Hope you guys are \r\nenjoying the heat.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nNow on to more important business.  I\'m watching this awesome documentary \r\nabout the Grunge music scene in Seattle called "HYPE!"  Shocking enough to \r\nme it\'s on the oxygen network.  If you can believe this shit?  Oxygen is \r\nthe second women\'s network as I recall.  The first being the Golden Girls \r\ndominated Lifetime network.  I swear, they run Golden Girls for twelve \r\nhours every day.  And what\'s worse is I kind of want to watch them all \r\njust hoping that the episode with Quentin Tarantino will come on.  As all \r\nof you Tarantino fanatics know, Quentin played an Elvis impersonator in an \r\nepisode of Golden Girls where they went to Vegas or something.  I really \r\nwant to see it.  But I can\'t put myself through watching twelve hours a \r\nday of Golden Girls or even to watch the beginning of the episodes.  Who \r\nthe fuck out there finds "Blanche" attractive, fucking shit the woman is \r\nold.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n<B>Pasadena on Fox</B> - I can\'t believe how low people will go to rip off \r\nthe Sopranos.  I just saw an ad for this Pasadena show.  It has a mob \r\nfamily and a young daughter who learns that her parents are mobsters.  \r\nWow, how original.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nDamn this is a good documentary.  Lots of live performances, including the \r\nfirst ever performance of  "Smells like teen spirit" and according to the \r\nnet, the soundtrack is a great album, like the soundtrack to Singles.  \r\nAlso Oxygen is trying to keep my watching by asking a very difficult \r\ntrivia question about documentaries at every commercial break and then \r\ngiving the answer when they come back to the show.  But what they weren\'t \r\ncounting on, was that I might actually know the answers to some of the \r\nquestions, and I mean know them cold.  Example: two of the easy questions \r\nwere: 1. What was the name of the documentary about two kids trying to get \r\ninto the NBA?, obviously the answer is Hoop Dreams.  Another easy one was \r\nwho directed the documentary Roger and Me?, obviously the answer is \r\nMichael Moore, who also directed The Big One, wrote the book Downsize \r\nThis, and created the television shows "TV Nation" and "The Awful Truth" \r\n(now on Bravo, check your local listings).  Since I knew the answers to \r\nthese questions, I guess I don\'t have to watch the show anymore.  I don\'t \r\nhave to wait for them to come back from the commercial break!  I can \r\nleave!  The question won\'t haunt me in the middle of the night!  I won\'t \r\nhave to watch commercials for parentsanonymous, inside of every woman \r\nthere is a girl: let her out, and every type of horrible tampon ad you can \r\nimagine.  But the documentary was so good I watched it anyway, despite my \r\nmastery of the questions. ', '', 20010809122854, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (270, './ - Burning a NeXT Cube', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '', '', 20010811200245, 'net_interest', 'http://simson.net/photos/hacks/cubefire.html');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (271, 'One evil genius trying to destroy the State Hornet', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'Well, it appears that thunt.net and I have become the focal point for many \r\nrumors and speculations about the State Hornet.  I’ve even heard that the \r\nfaculty adviser over there is warning people about me and telling people \r\n(journalists, the type of people who should learn to always have two \r\nsources for everything) that I am some kind of evil genius bent on the \r\nutter destruction of the State Hornet.  I would like to say loudly and \r\nclearly that this is not my plan.  The Hornet seems bent on destroying \r\nitself, and I must say, it is doing a damn good job of that (picking more \r\nand more incompetent people to be EIC is a damn good start).  But here at \r\nthunt.net all we do is spread the rumors, and we seem to excel at that.  \r\nSo, here we go again:\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n<B>Ban Thunt.net!</B> - Word from inside the hornet is that spring chicken \r\nEIC Layla Bomb wants to ban the IP of the evil website that is going to \r\ndestroy the newspaper.  The IP does not belong to a porn site or a Haitian \r\nrevolutionary’s website, but to good old Thunt.net.  I hope she does \r\nsucceed in banning Thunt.net.  You know it will only be about ten minutes \r\nlater when I get around it, either by an email distribution system or a \r\nseries of mirrors.  The thing I like best about the State Hornet is that \r\nthey are the press, the media, the ones who are supposed to be fighting \r\nfor the first amendment, but they hate it so much when little old me \r\npublishes rumors and news on my little old web page. So, ban me you \r\nfuckers, ban me all you want.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n<B>Layla Bomb: Not Found</B> - This is a good one.  Miss Bomb went on \r\nvacation all summer and didn’t tell anyone where she went.  King Fitz even \r\ncalled the police and filed a missing persons report on our dear Miss \r\nBomb.  Miss Bomb showed up from a vacation that is heavily documented \r\n(diary entries every five minutes) on her website (<a \r\nhref=http://ellmyruh.tripod.com/>Layla Land</a>).  She returned to find a \r\npaper on its knees.  Layla has not hired a staff, or any writers and will \r\nnot be doing a survival guide this year.  Also, the advertising staff has \r\neven been canceling ads because they weren’t even sure that there was \r\ngoing to be a newspaper this semester.  Additionally computer-genius Miss \r\nBomb allowed some mac guru to wipe all of the hard drives of the hornet’s \r\ncomputers, including the servers.  Leaving the hornet without any \r\ntemplates of what the paper used to look like, so making a new issue \r\nquickly will not be easy.  In another stroke of brilliance, no one can \r\nfind the original cds for the software needed to create the paper \r\n(Photoshop, Quark, etc), so they’re really fucked now.  This is why I \r\nthink that Layla is the best EIC ever.  Even better than Dina, sorry dear, \r\nbut when you’re beat, you’re beat.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n<B>Biggest Looser Ever</B> - Guess who’s coming back to the hornet.  After \r\nattending one comic book convention, sans resume, sans samples, sans \r\nbusiness cards, Andy has given up his dream of having anything to do with \r\ncomic books to go back to the hornet and be Layla’s bitch.  Andy has \r\nreturned to the de-maculating, underpaid position of Creative Director.  A \r\nposition once held by another three time looser, Ryan Anne Polli.  Will \r\nAndy beat her record and go for four, only time will tell, but it’s a safe \r\nbet. \r\n<BR><BR>\r\nThe best part about the story is how Andy got his job back.  First, Andy \r\ncalled Layla’s voicemail and left several panicked calls, begging for his \r\njob back.  Then he met with her and begged some more.  I’ve even heard \r\nstories that he got down on his knees and pleaded with her to get his lame \r\nposition back.  It’s just really sad, and I’m not sure I want to talk \r\nabout it anymore.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nWell, that about sums it up for rumors today on Thunt.net.  I’d just like \r\nto wish good luck to all the poor fools who have to work at the hornet \r\nthis semester.  Like horses on the overland trail, you’ve got a long road \r\nahead of you and unfortunately there is little chance of anyone putting a \r\nbullet in your head and putting you out of your misery.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', 20010820205207, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (272, 'Layla Linked in Love Scandal with a Horse', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '<img src=images/layla/horse_love.jpg><BR><BR>\r\nSacramento, CA – Breaking news from <a \r\nhref=http://ellmyruh.tripod.com/>Layla Land</a>, the absolute home for all \r\nLayla-related entertainment, Layla met someone while she was in New \r\nHampshire.  But until today we didn’t know who this someone was, whether \r\nthey were man, woman, or beast.  Today we know the truth.  While in New \r\nHampshire, Layla was not sleeping with a man, not sleeping with a woman, \r\nbut sleeping with a BEAST!  \r\n<BR><BR>\r\nFor several months now, according to her “New Hampshire Journal” Layla has \r\nbeen fucking a horse named Timmy.  Timmy is a brown horse who enjoys \r\neating hay, jumping over fences, and according to un-named sources, \r\nfucking Layla.  Layla went on several dates with Timmy, and Timmy \r\nimpressed her with his knowledge of oats, and of course deep-deep-\r\ndicking.  \r\n<BR><BR>\r\nHorse fucking was a common occurrence during medieval times, when young \r\ngirls could not simply go to the corner sex store and purchase a \r\nvibrator.  Young ugly women were forced to either take their passions to a \r\nwooden stick, or a long horse’s dick.  The latter was the obvious choice, \r\ndue to the lack of splinters.  But in modern times, those who fuck horses \r\nhave become outcasts, freaks, degenerate slime that some believe should be \r\nshot on sight.  But in this reporters eyes, Layla and Timmy’s love should \r\nbe celebrated like any normal couple.  So, the next time you see Layla, be \r\nsure to congratulate her on her special relationship.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nBecause, if Timmy’s happy, then we’re happy.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n<img src=images/layla/timmyroll.jpg><BR><BR>', '', 20010822153806, 'normal', '');
