INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (274, 'Layla Land Lawyers Lawsuit Links Lazy Lay-about in Legal Lasso', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'Matt Brown took time out of his busy schedule to inform me of what\'s up \r\nover at <a href=http://ellmyruh.tripod.com/>Layla Land</a>...  So I \r\nfigured I\'d pass the fun along to you:\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n<B>Layla Land:</B> "Saturday, August 25--I\'ve been extremely busy lately, \r\nbut in my spare time\r\nwhen I should actually be sleeping, I\'ve been reading up on U.S. copyright\r\nlaws to make sure that the material on my site is not in the public domain.\r\nI found that I was correct in my assertions that all writing and \r\nphotography on this Web site (with the exception of a few photos, which \r\nhave been credited to their owner) are definitely mine."\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nSo Layla has called us out in no certain terms.  After reading this I just\r\nsat back and assumed a letter would be coming in the mail from Layla\'s \r\nLawyers\r\nany day now.  Until Matt informed me that according to the document that \r\nLayla\r\nclaimed she read it clearly states:\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n"Under the fair use doctrine of the U.S. copyright statute, it is \r\npermissible\r\nto use limited portions of a work including quotes, for purposes such as\r\ncommentary, criticism, news reporting, and scholarly reports. There are no\r\nlegal rules permitting the use of a specific number of words, a certain\r\nnumber of musical notes, or percentages of a work. Whether a particular use\r\nqualifies as fair use depends on all the circumstances. See Circular 21 and\r\nFL 102."\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nAlso according to Matt this is the same law that the National Enquirer \r\nhides under\r\nwhen they manipulate photos (and they would have done more than horse \r\nfucking, I\'m\r\nsure they would have went to what is on all of our minds right now in \r\nthese dark\r\nhours of late August, and that question is: Is Layla fucking Andy?  Which \r\nI will \r\naddress in the second half of this column.)  Since Thunt.net is falls \r\nclearly under the broad umbrella of "commentary, criticism,\r\nand news reporting" I think that we\'re in the clear here and you will be \r\nable\r\nto enjoy those horse fucking photos until the end of time.  How about \r\nthat?  Pretty\r\ngreat country we live in...\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nAnyway, back to Andy fucking Layla, it seems like the poll seems to be a \r\nbit one-sided\r\nand the angry comments against me on the message board have been on the \r\nrise, proving\r\nthat this Andy fucking Layla issue is one that deserves more in depth \r\nstudy.  \r\n<BR><BR>\r\nSo I decided a fact/conclusion chart would be in order.  Unfortunately I \r\ndidn\'t have time to make it to scale, so it is a bit crude, but here it is:\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" border="1">\r\n<tr>\r\n    <td><b>FACT:</b></td>\r\n    <td><b>CONCLUSION:</b></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n    <td>Andy spends ALL DAY at the hornet.</td>\r\n    <td>Andy is fucking Layla.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n    <td>Andy spends ALL NIGHT at the hornet.</td>\r\n    <td>Andy is fucking Layla.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n    <td>Andy is posting angry messages about me on the message board</td>\r\n    <td>Andy is fucking Layla.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n    <td>Andy shot me with a b-b gun.</td>\r\n    <td>Andy is fucking Layla.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n    <td>Andy asked Matt to hold his calls, unless it was Layla.</td>\r\n    <td>Andy is fucking Layla.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n    <td>Andy has Layla\'s number on speed dial.</td>\r\n    <td>Andy is fucking Layla.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n    <td>The homepage on Andy\'s computer is set to Layla Land.</td>\r\n    <td>Andy is fucking Layla.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n    <td>Layla gave Andy his job back.</td>\r\n    <td>Andy is fucking Layla.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n    <td>Andy refused to go out to breakfast with the gang to go to a staff \r\nmeeting.</td>\r\n    <td>Andy is fucking Layla.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n    <td>Andy rented the movie Black Beauty.</td>\r\n    <td>Andy is fucking Layla.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n</table>\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nThis concludes Thunt.net\'s indepth report on Andy fucking Layla.', '', 20010827205110, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (275, 'An Open Letter to Andy', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'Dear Andy,\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nWe, your friends, don\'t understand what your problem is.  Is it just \r\nbecause you want to fuck Layla, that you become such an anti-social \r\nbitch?  Nothing is wrong with your being straight.  It doesn\'t bother us \r\nthat you\'re not gay.  It\'s okay.  Just because you think you\'re shaft, \r\ndoesn\'t mean you have to take shaft.  Furthermore, we would like to meet \r\nLayla, because you are fucking her.  That makes her one of your "friends" \r\nand therefore one of our "friends".  And any friend of yours is a friend \r\nof ours.  And friends do share with friends, not that we would be \r\ninterested in this case, but someday you may have something we want.  Not \r\nthat we would say that we are your friends, we like to think of ourselves \r\nas more of acquaintances, because you hold no loyalty toward your friends, \r\nso it would be worthless to call ourselves your friends.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nWe understand why you love Layla.  It\'s because she\'s got you on your \r\nknees.  And you\'re begging for your job, won\'t you please, Layla.  Layla.  \r\nShe probably says to you all the time, darling won\'t you please, Layla.  \r\nBlink 182.  You\'re worried about paying rent, but remember that darling \r\nwill you ease my worried mind.  \r\n<BR><BR>\r\nAnd now a poem, by A.H. Duong\r\n(this poem was found on Andy\'s computer in a directory marked "Bestiality \r\nand Child Porn".  We do not know how the two are related.)\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n	Lustful eyes full of joy<BR>\r\n	Ass of a horse<BR>\r\n	Y not<BR>\r\n	Let me love someone other than my hand<BR>\r\n	Andy wants to fuck you. <BR>\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nLayla, in case you don\'t know, our "friend" Andy loves you.  He loves you \r\ndeeply.  Like that hooker in Deep Throat, he wants to suck your dick.  \r\nSucking day and night is all that will satisfy him.  He want to suck your \r\ncock until it is numb.  Remember Layla, when you\'re alone, and life is \r\ngetting you DOWN, you can always have Andy go DOWNTOWN.  Listen to music \r\n(mainly "Because I got High" and "Who let the dogs out") and the traffic \r\n(caused by Andy\'s truck) in the city.  Linger on the sidewalks where \r\nHoward the Hornet\'s ass is pretty.  How can you blow?  The lights are so \r\nmuch brighter there, Andy is willing to take a shot in the mouth, you can \r\nforget all your troubles and horsefuck all your cares as you go DOWNtown.  \r\nThings will be great.  When you\'re FUCKING ANDY.  Nothing like asian meat \r\non your plate, when you\'re SUCKING ANDY\'S dick, DOWNTOWN.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n	Fuck you very much,\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n	The friends of A.H. Duong\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n(Thomas, Joe, Matt, Juan, Josh, Russ, Josh L., David, Andrea, no wait, \r\nshe\'s not your friend anymore, Brendan, Matt W.  and you don\'t have \r\nanymore friends do you?  Oh, we almost forget your butt-buddy Howard.)\r\n\r\n', '', 20010829203208, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (276, 'Books in Review', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'Now in an attempt to follow the advice of the self-proclaimed "best band \r\nin the wurld", U2, I will attempt to elevate the commentary of Thunt.net \r\nwith "Books in Review".\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nCurrently I am reading:\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nGates of Fire by Steven Pressfield – It\'s an engrossing history/fiction \r\nabout the Spartan\'s desperate last stand at Thermoplye.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nI have recently read:\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nOn the Road by Jack Kerouac – An epic tale of one man\'s journeys in the \r\nUnited States.  A true classic of the beat era.   Kerouac uses incredibly \r\nsimple language, but the whole book seems to read like poetry.  My \r\nfavorite line was "We went seventy.".  There is just something so simple, \r\nbut so joyous in that line.  I can\'t describe this book, but I can tell \r\nyou that you should read it.  It is a slow book, the kind of book to be \r\nread a chapter a day in the evenings when the sun is setting, but it is \r\ndefinitely a book worth reading.  It contains the idea of freedom in it.  \r\nAnd freedom is an idea worth holding in your head and thinking about for a \r\nwhile.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nTrainspotting by Irvin Welsh – The tale of a young Scottish lad\'s troubles \r\nwith heroin.  You\'ve probably all seen the excellent movie by the same \r\nname, but the book remains worth reading.  Mainly because it is written in \r\nScottish, not English, and when you read it you are forced to sound out \r\nevery word until the voice in your head adapts and speaks Scottish to \r\nyou.  It\'s a trip.  Also it includes several stories that were not in the \r\nmovie.  While the movie is clearly one story, the book reads more like a \r\ncollection of short stories about the same group of characters.  Sometimes \r\nthe author really throws you a curve when he has one character narrating \r\nin one story and another character narrating in the next.  It\'s a bit of a \r\ntrip, but soon you begin recognizing the narrators because they all speak \r\ndifferently.  Like Spud who always uses the word "likesay", even in his \r\nhead. It\'s a fun read.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nBreakfast at Tiffanys by Truman Capote – I\'ve wanted to read Capote for a \r\nlong time now and I finally got to him last week.  I had this book and \r\nseveral others on my shelf and it was only a matter of time.  Breakfast at \r\nTiffany\'s is absolutely stunning.  It\'s only 115 pages long, so it\'s \r\nrather short, but it tells a complete and wonderful story.  Capote also \r\nuses a simple writing style similar to Kerouac, and manages to graft his \r\ncharacters instantly into your mind.  The name of the main character, \r\nHolly Golightly is so perfect that it has become a part of the English \r\nlanguage, similar to Joseph Heller\'s Catch-22, very few people know that \r\nthe book came before the term.  Breakfast at Tiffany\'s is definitely worth \r\nreading and you should be able to finish it rather quickly.  If you\'re \r\nlucky you\'ll find the same version of the story I found, because it had \r\ntwo or three other short stories included, one of which "The Christmas \r\nStory" (or something like that) was incredibly moving and even made me \r\ncry.  Capote is a stunner, I plan to read In Cold Blood and Music for \r\nChameleons in the next few weeks.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nThank you for reading Books in Review, on Thunt.net.  Please post your own \r\nreviews of what you\'ve been reading to the message board.  We\'re all \r\ncurious to know what you\'ve been reading.  Maybe someone will read that \r\nbook because of your recommendation or perhaps if a few people have read \r\nit, we can discuss the pros and cons of the book.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n \r\n', '', 20010908180212, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (277, 'Josh Leon\'s Party', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'This is probably the most difficult article I\'ve ever had to write.  I \r\nmean, there\'s a lot of pressure on me.  I just met a whole bunch of people \r\nat this party who know me only as "thunt.net" and now they\'re probably all \r\npointing their web browsers this way to see what I have to say about the \r\nparty.  I thought about many different ways of doing this article.  I \r\nthought of a straight person by person route, analyzing and picking on \r\neach person I met, but then I remembered what good old Hunter S. Thompson \r\nsaid, "When the going gets tough, the tough go Gonzo."  And so I did.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n<I>Editor\'s note:  First of all, the photos from this spectacular event \r\nare up in the <a href=http://thunt.net/photo>photo section</a>.  Second of \r\nall, I spoke to Mr. Thunt briefly after he finished this article.  He \r\ninformed me that he had created a masterwork of fiction.  I asked him what \r\nthat meant and he informed me that he had taken the party and twisted it \r\naround and made it into a story, so that the people who attended the party \r\nwouldn\'t be sure of what actually happened and what didn\'t happen.  He \r\nalso informed me that everything had been re-arranged for dramatic \r\npurposes.  I just thought it was best to inform you, the audience, of Mr. \r\nThunt\'s twisted themes, and to remind you, as always, never to believe \r\nwhat you read.</I>\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nIt was around 10:30 when I called Andy to see if we were gonna go to \r\nthis "Josh Leon party".  The party started and 9:30 and typically Andy and \r\nMatt hadn\'t even left yet.  I told Andy I\'d give him a ride and he said \r\nthat I had to be there in five minutes.  I said I would.  He repeated five \r\nminutes, I mean it, five minutes.  I grabbed my trusty Radio Shack timer \r\nand set it for five minutes and told him to fuck off.  I arrived four \r\nminutes and 32 seconds later, flaunting the timer.  Andy, packing a bottle \r\nand a video camera told me I was driving.  He and Matt got in the car and \r\nwe were underway.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nAs we pulled into the apartment complex, Andy started talking about how he \r\nwanted us to make our entrance.  He spoke of him going in first so that he \r\ncould get the reaction shot on Layla\'s face, he also spoke of him \r\nannouncing us, and other grandiose schemes of lunacy.  I\'m a shy person \r\nmyself, so I told him we would just walk in like normal, leave the great \r\nentrances to Batman and his heterosexual life mate Robin.  After we \r\nparked, two slightly toasted gentleman rushed to car, shocked and excited \r\nto see us.  The gentlemen were two "formers"….  Former EIC \r\nDavid "Chairman" Sommers and Former Opinion Editor Brendan Wonnacott.  \r\nThey clapped us on the back and led us to the party.  They seemed to be \r\nexpecting some serious fireworks, and I, ever worried for my own security \r\nasked them for assurances that if this was an ambush, or if anything went \r\ndown, that they would have my back.  They assured me that this was true \r\nand we went inside.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nThe party was clearly in low gear.  A collection of hat-wearing smokers \r\nwere out on the balcony and a random assortment of people gathered in the \r\nliving room boozing.  The first person I recognized was Layla Bomb, the \r\ncurrent EIC of the Hornet.  I thought she looked familiar because I had \r\nseen her picture a few weeks ago when I wrote that horse-fucking article.  \r\nI walked up to her and introduced myself (<a href= \r\nhttp://thunt.net/photo/2001/09-09-01_-_josh_leon_party/DCP_1518.JPG>see \r\nphoto</a>).  I don\'t think she recognized me as I used my super-sneaky \r\nalias "Thomas".  But then the beautiful Jen Tillett screamed out "Oh my \r\nGod, Thomas Hunt in the flesh!", so I suppose the whole secrecy thing was \r\npretty much blown at that point.  \r\n<BR><BR>\r\nI continued to circulate the party meeting other Hornet people new and \r\nold.  I met Marin and Kim from the dorms.  They informed me that they came \r\nwith Janet, someone else from the dorms.  I informed them that this was \r\nfine with me.  I continued on my way.  I found Josh Leon barricaded in his \r\nroom reading an "academic" version of the bible with a harem full of girls \r\non his bed.  I was impressed.  I thought to myself, I never knew Josh Leon \r\nwas such a player, but I guess now I know the truth.  \r\n<BR><BR>\r\nEventually I ended up on the balcony with the smokers where I met Tara \r\nMcDonald (or something like that, it\'s so hard to learn people\'s names at \r\na party).  Tara informed me that she was very angry because her name was \r\nmentioned on my website.  I dredged the depths of my memory and realized I \r\nhad no clue who this girl was.  I certainly hadn\'t written about her, but \r\nI did recall that there was some message on the message board about her \r\nhaving a "nice ass".  Nonplussed, she continued to tell me how my message \r\nboard was full of gay-bashing, racist, sexist people.  I told her that I \r\ndon’t censor my message board, whatever people want to post is what they \r\npost.  She still seemed angry and told me that she read a short story of \r\nmine that I submitted to the News & Review.  She asked me how the story \r\nturned out, confusing reality with literature.  I explained to her that \r\nthe story was made up.  She seemed confused.  She told me that my website \r\nand my story were smut.  I don\'t think she is a very nice person.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nRude Tara was interrupted by Brendan pushing a beer into my hand.  As I \r\ntried to explain to him that I was the designated driver and thus couldn\'t \r\ndrink, I noticed that Brendan had bigger problems on his hands.  Or more \r\naptly put, in his hands.  Somebody had gotten the already drunk Josh Leon \r\nstoned and it seemed his knees were giving way.  Brendan, flanked by \r\nSommers carried the inebriated Leon to his bed where again chicks flocked \r\nto him.  To be more specific, one chick named Sharra (not Charmin) and a \r\nguy named Derrick (not Darrin) lay on either side of our intoxicated \r\nhost.  Apparently Josh Leon\'s magnetism was not limited to merely the \r\nopposite sex.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nSuddenly a phone began ringing.  It was a small "american-style" cell \r\nphone.  I answered it.  It was some guy named Ed looking for Bridget.  We \r\nscreamed for Bridget, then we went to work on Ed.  Ed told us that he was \r\none of Bridget\'s ex-boyfriends and he desperately wanted her back.  He \r\nstarted to expose all kinds of other highly personal issues to us, but \r\nthen Bridget came and took the phone away.  She freaked out and told us \r\nnot to answer it if it rang again.  She left the room.  Suddenly the phone \r\nrang again, so we answered it.  It was our old pal Ed again.  Ed told us \r\nabout the problems that he and Bridget experienced in the sac.  Apparently \r\nEd was very much into experimentation, but Bridget was not.  I felt bad \r\nfor Ed but there was nothing I could do for him, so I handed the phone to \r\nMatt Brown.  Then Matt hung up on Ed to take call waiting.  It was Tony \r\nHarvey.  He was calling Bridget back.  The room made the instant \r\nconclusion, that somebody should go pick up Tony.  Matt began surveying \r\nthe room to see if anyone was sober and could pick Tony up.  Typically, I \r\nwas the only one sober and thus it was my duty to go get Tony.  Bridget \r\nnoticed that we were using her phone and she came with me.  We raced to \r\nTony\'s, brought him back, and then the party really got started.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nI walked out on the balcony to get some fresh air and I found myself alone \r\nwith Layla.  As I always do with people that hate me, I decided to engage \r\nher in conversation.  I asked her opinion of the horse-fucker story.  She \r\nremained silent.  I realized she was probably from Generation X or some \r\nMTV-addled generation, so I decided to talk to her in "who wants to be a \r\nmillionaire" style.  I gave her two choices: "were you offended" or "did \r\nyou think it was funny".  Survey says: Offended.  I laughed and told her \r\nthat everyone else thought it was funny, hoping to make it clear that no \r\none really believes that she is fucking horses, despite the ample \r\nphotographic evidence.  She seemed perturbed and did little to carry on \r\nthe conversation.  I jokingly asked her if she was going to sue.  She \r\nsnapped back, have you been worrying about it?  I smiled and told her that \r\nI knew copyright law and it was clearly on my side.  She made a quip about \r\nhow Thunt.net was not the National Enquirer.  I was glad she knew the \r\ndifference.  I think of Thunt.net to be more like The New York Times, \r\nmyself.  Suddenly there was a loud crash in the next room as Brendan was \r\nwrestling Andy.  I watched the carnage unfold and Layla drifted off \r\nwithout saying goodbye.  I wasn\'t surprised, these GenX/GenY type people \r\nreally have no manners anyway.  \r\n<BR><BR>\r\nAfter the wrestling match, which shockingly was won by Andy, I went to \r\ncheck on Josh and his harem.  I found Josh to be in dire straights.  Jen \r\nTillett had put down her Bud Light (Jen Tillett always drinks Bud Light, I \r\nthink it\'s her beer of choice, if I was ever in a bar and I was going to \r\nbuy Jen Tillett a drink, I would make it a Bud (grand pause) Light.) and \r\nshe was attacking Josh Leon.  I asked Russ what all the commotion was \r\nabout.  Russ told me that Josh had told Jen that she liked fucking Brendan \r\nup the ass or some other such nonsense and that Jen had taken offence at \r\nit.  Jen beat Josh bloody and banged his head up against the filing \r\ncabinet next to his bed.  Then Jen, joined by her tag-team partner Sharra \r\nthrew Leon off his bed and continued to pound him into submission.  \r\n<BR><BR>\r\nIt was about then that the cops showed up. The music stopped and everyone \r\nstarted freaking out.  Shouts of "5-O" circulated the sedated crowd.  As \r\nthe only sober person there I figured I should go out and speak to them.  \r\nI descended the staircase from Leon\'s apartment knowing full well that no \r\none was following me and it was to be me and the cops, mano-e-mano.  It \r\nturned out that they weren\'t cops, but simply security guards.  They \r\ninformed me that we had to break up the party because there had been \r\ncomplaints about the noise and that if we didn\'t break it up, they would \r\ncall the police and we would be fined.  I apologized for the noise and \r\nasked them if it would be okay if we kept the party going but kept the \r\nnoise to a minimum.  They informed me that there would be no further \r\nwarnings and that the next time they got a noise complaint they would call \r\nthe police.  I told them that was fine, we wouldn\'t be noisy anymore.  \r\nThroughout our conversation they were constantly fingering and talking on \r\ntheir fancy walkie-talkies (the only weapon a security guard can carry), I \r\nwas impressed.  One of them got out a pad to write down my name, since he \r\nthought I lived in the apartment.  I informed them that I did not live \r\nthere, I was just sent out to speak.  They didn\'t like this.  They wanted \r\nto speak to the man who lived there, I told them that I would inform him \r\nof his rights.  They were displeased.  I told them that the owner was \r\nsleeping.  They questioned how he could be sleeping in the middle of a \r\nparty and I kindof, looked at them.  They got the idea.  I again \r\napologized for the noise and returned to the party.  The cops took off.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nI went back inside and told everyone that we had a second chance, but we\'d \r\njust have to keep the volume down from now on.  I also told them that from \r\na worst-case perspective, when the cops arrived to cite us for disturbing \r\nthe peace, I could try to talk them out of it as well.  Josh Leon seemed \r\npleased and told me I was his lawyer.  It was a job I wasn\'t crazy about \r\ntaking, it was clear, even this early in the night that Josh Leon was \r\ngoing to need a lot of legal advice before this thing was over.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nI needed a break from all the action so I went and sat in Josh\'s bedroom.  \r\nUnfortunately, I didn\'t find much of a break.  I found Russ from Canada \r\ntalking to his cousin from Canada and I\'m not sure, but I\'m pretty sure \r\nthat he was hitting on her.  I didn\'t want to judge him, him being \r\nCanadian and all, but it sure looked like that was what was happening.  \r\nAlso Keith Reed was sitting in the corner talking about how he wanted to \r\ntalk to Trader Joe and that he had a great trade for him.  He spoke of \r\nmany different trades, from four lobsters for two pigs and ten salamis for \r\none ham, but Trader Joe seemed uninterested.  Although it is still unclear \r\nto me whether or not Trader Joe is a real person and whether or not Keith \r\nwas actually speaking to him, or just speaking to himself.  The party was \r\ndefinitely in second gear, it had gone from strange to weird.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nI walked back out into the front room and I was greeted with all kinds of \r\nhorrors.  Someone had gotten Andy high and he was dancing around with a \r\nlampshade on his head.  Bridget had passed out in the corner and Josh Leon \r\nwas collapsed in an easy chair.  Only Russ and Brendan seemed to have any \r\nenergy left as they rapped along to a Jimmy Hendricks song.  People began \r\nfiling out the door, unable to deal with the weirdness of the scene.  I \r\nstayed, drawn to the weirdness as I always am, unable to turn away.  But \r\nsomehow without the normals, the weirdness started to loose its thrill.   \r\nAndy took off the lampshade.  Bridget woke up and had a conversation with \r\nSommers.  Everyone was sitting on the carpet staring at each other.  Jen \r\nTillett was sucking on her fingers.  The party was beginning to end.  \r\nSomeone turned up the volume on the stereo and it began to blare the \r\nclosing notes of Hendricks\'s fantastic rendition of the star-spangled-\r\nbanner (live at woodstock).  Everyone seemed to bob their heads together \r\nas Jimmi went higher and higher, until finally he could do no more, and he \r\nbrought the song back down and with it went the party.  Even the weird had \r\ntoo much now, they had jobs and lives to return to.  Several left without \r\nsaying goodbye, you just glanced once at where they were sitting and \r\nnoticed they were gone.  Josh Leon retired to his bedroom and began \r\nsetting his alarm clock.  Andy was butchering a guitar and I told him it \r\nwas time to leave.  Andy gathered up Matt and his camcorder and we were on \r\nour way.  Josh Leon\'s party had ended.  It was something like three a.m. \r\nand we were hungry.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nPrologue:\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nWe flew down Howe Ave in the mood for Tacos.  Andy began singing the \r\npraises of Del Taco, but Matt and I are both more into Taco Bell.  We \r\nasked Andy if he had any money.  He didn\'t.  So we went to Taco Bell.  I \r\nordered a ten pack to feed the huddled masses in my car and Andy kept \r\nscreaming from the back seat that they were going to spit in my food.  His \r\nfears were soon forgotten as he munched silently on a taco I paid for.  We \r\ngot back to the old apartment building only to be greeted by the sound of \r\nanother party.  Andy and Matt\'s downstairs roommates Joe and Juan \r\nRodriguez (no relation) were having a party.  I was tired and needed rest, \r\nbut we went inside anyway.  Andy stayed outside smoking and Matt started \r\nhanding out the food.  The grande meal was a good idea, purchased to feed \r\nthe masses, and here were the masses.  I grabbed a Mountain Dew from the \r\nfridge and enjoyed my tacos.  Matt, Joe and some girls named Christina and \r\nJessica began taking tequila shots.  I stayed for a while, watching MTV \r\nand every other channel (Joe was trying to watch them all at once), but \r\nsoon it was too much for me.  I need the quiet that only comes from \r\nrespectable married people who have to work for a living.  I drove down \r\nthe road to my friend Justin\'s place, used my key to enter and found a \r\ndead quiet apartment.  It was just what I needed to get this story down on \r\npaper and to relax after what had been a long evening.  I fired up the \r\nlaptop and hooked into the high speed internet connection.  It was four \r\na.m., and about time to update Thunt.net, I thought to myself…. \r\n<BR><BR>\r\n<center>THE END</center>\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n<I>Author\'s Note:  If your name was mentioned in this article, I\'m certain \r\nthat I misspelled it.  For this I apologize.</I>\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n', '', 20010909055129, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (278, 'The begining of the End', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'I, like the rest of Americans today was shocked and saddened to see the \r\nutter destruction of the World Trade Center in New York and the vicious \r\nattack on The Pentagon in Washington D.C..  I was awoken at 07:30 PST, \r\njust in time to see building two fall live.  I began monitoring the story \r\nfrom the TNCC (Thunt.Net Command Center).  Pictures of the command center \r\nare available in the <a href=http://thunt.net/photo/>photo section</a>.  \r\n<BR><br>\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n	<a href="http://thunt.net/photo/2001/09-11-01_-_TNCC/DCP_1593.JPG"><img border=0 src="http://thunt.net/photo/2001/09-11-01_-_TNCC/DCP_1593.small.jpg" width="220" height="146" alt="40628 bytes"></a><br>\r\nTNCC<br>\r\n</center>\r\n<BR>\r\nIt is now 20:00 PST and I have watched approximately 10 straight hours of \r\nnews coverage on the four monitors here in the TNCC.  I have spoken to \r\nSecretary of Defense Bhaskar Sinha via secure telephone from Davis, CA \r\nwhere we are glad to say he has reached a secured, yet undisclosed \r\nlocation.  Secretary of State Justin White arrived at the TNCC, around \r\n16:30 PST, we debriefed Secretary White and came to a consensus on a \r\ncourse of action.  We went to Papa Murphy\'s to secure a pizza, and Raley\'s \r\nto secure some soda and ice cream.  While we walked from the TNCC to the \r\nhelicopters waiting to take us to our destination we encountered NSA \r\nDirector Michael Keenan and he accompanied us on our journey.  We were \r\nalso in contact throughout the day with FBI Director John Humphreys, CIA \r\nDirector Mathew Brown, Secretary of Education Andrew H. Duong and \r\nSecretary of the Interior Joshua Pryor.  Our entire staff are all at \r\nsecured locations and are in no danger.\r\n<BR>\r\n<br><center>\r\n<img src="http://thunt.net/photo/2001/09-11-01_-_terrorist_bombing/001wtc.JPG"><br>\r\n<BR></center>\r\nNSA Director Keenan was saddened to report that prior warning of the \r\nattack was available on the auction site Ebay (<a \r\nhref=http://thunt.net/mirrors/ebay.html>thunt.net exclusive</a>), but \r\nexperts failed to understand the information until it was too late.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nDirector Keenan also collected photos on the internet today, available for \r\nyour perusal in the <a href=http://thunt.net/photo/>photo section</a>.  \r\n<BR><BR>\r\nBelow are the contents of Thunt\'s notebook kept as the day\'s events \r\nunfolded:\r\n<BR>\r\n<br><center>\r\n<img src="http://thunt.net/photo/2001/09-11-01_-_terrorist_bombing/010911wtc_08.JPG"><br>\r\n<BR></center>\r\nRather quoted Lincoln:  "One cannot imagine the foot prints of an enemy in \r\nthe Applications or drinking from the Ohio."\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nBest description, heard in the background of one of the amateur \r\nvideotapes:  "Fuck, the whole tower just collapsed, oh my God."\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nNews 10: Breaking news!  Arden Fair Mall closed.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nBases on Threat Condition Delta.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nChannel 10 is breaking in for local weather.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nConstant mention of how the tragedy reminded people of the movie Pearl \r\nHarbor.  I completely agree, both were horrifying.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nABC:  Man in the background with a pen in his mouth.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nJennings with glasses, horrible frames.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nRather looks beat-up.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nBaseball, Space Needle, Disneyland closed.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nBlair on TV, London on alert:  "Will not rest until this evil is driven \r\nfrom this world."\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nPope: "unspeakable horror".\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nRather, Lincoln again:  "Let not he who is houseless tear down the house \r\nof another, let him build his own house and be safe from violence."\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nRather, Jefferson: "The price of freedom is eternal vigilance."\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nEmmy\'s canceled.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nOf course during this disaster MTV was actually playing videos.  I paused \r\nmy coverage to watch U2\'s "Stuck in a moment and you can\'t get out".  It \r\nwas surprisingly fitting.  They almost broke in with Dan Rather\'s voice, \r\nbut cut back to the video.  Soon after, MTV ended, and switched to CBS \r\nnews.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nHSN off the air.  Only channels on are Cartoons, Kid Shows and the News.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nE! & Sci-fi are still on.  Not even a horrendous terrorist bombing can \r\nstop celebrity gossip or reruns of Star Trek.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nRather, Paine:  "Times that try men\'s souls."\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nHamas:  "Humanity taking revenge against US oppression."\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n<B>Coverage Wars:</B><BR>\r\nCBS:  Early lead.  <BR>\r\nCNN: Took lead. <BR>\r\nABC:  coming on strong.  Amateur video, dead wife of Solicitor General. \r\n<BR>\r\nCNN: Back to front with Amateur video of Doctor. <BR>\r\nABC:  Two major exclusives.  Amateur video of rubble and video of under \r\nbelly of plane into building. <BR>\r\nCNN:  Exclusive, bombing in Afghanistan.  All other networks pick it up, \r\nexcept Fox News, who doesn\'t give a shit about its viewers. <BR>\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nJennings is so tired.  Ink marks on his hands.  Pen in hand.  No jacket.  \r\nClicking off things on his fingers.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nNo commercials.  All day.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n6:30 pm – All three networks restarted shows with logos and recaps.  Cnn \r\ncontinues unheeded.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nGreat respect for HSN and VH1.  HSN switched to a canceled programming \r\nright away, later picked up CNN coverage.  VH1 dropped programming right \r\naway and picked up CBS news.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nNBC\'s coverage is embarrassing.  Not even covering the live pentagon \r\nbriefing.  Although NBC does lead in hot chicks.  Cambell Brown is hot and \r\nthe new blonde with hair Katie Couric doesn\'t look half bad.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nNBC and CBS have the same headline:  Attack on America.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nEnd Thunt\'s notebook.\r\n<BR><BR><BR>\r\nThe bombing today was horrible but it is only the beginning.  The \r\ntwentieth century witnessed a new kind of war, a nuclear war.  The twenty-\r\nfirst century is poised to witness a far worse kind of war, a war of \r\nterror.  Today\'s attack was horrifying but imagine if the terrorists had \r\nused chemical or biological weapons.  If that type of attack had occurred \r\nwe might be saying goodbye to all of New York, not just a handful of \r\nbuildings downtown.  America has just faced the worst tragedy in all of \r\nher history, but I fear that this is not the end.  I\'m Thomas Hunt, \r\nreporting live from the TNCC.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<center>\r\n	<a href="http://thunt.net/photo/2001/09-11-01_-_TNCC/DCP_1594.JPG"><img border=0 src="http://thunt.net/photo/2001/09-11-01_-_TNCC/DCP_1594.small.jpg" width="220" height="146" alt="40628 bytes"></a><br>\r\nThunt<br>\r\n</center>\r\n', '', 20010911201706, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (280, 'Hollywood Now! Special Edition: Redux', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'more info on the WTC at: <a \r\nhref="http://thunt.net/wtc/">http://thunt.net/wtc/</a>\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nI really don\'t like this new trend in movie re-releases.  I like the idea \r\nof a re-release.  I like it when they restore the print, fix up the sound \r\nand release the movie on the big screen so that those of us who were too \r\nyoung or too not born can go see the movie on the big screen.  But I don\'t \r\nlike these new re-releases where they\'re changing the movie and adding and \r\nsubtracting scenes, putting goofy digital characters behind all the main \r\nplot and totally altering the ending.  It sucks for many reasons.  Soon \r\nall re-releases will have to be like that.  Movies that have nothing wrong \r\nwith them will be re-cut so that audiences can "see it again for the first \r\ntime" and shit.  Even the Monty Python Re-Release, which I think would be \r\na great re-release only with a new print and new sound, felt the need to \r\nadd new scenes.  Of course they only added 24 seconds, and were clearly \r\npoking fun at the silly re-release idea, they still did kowtow by adding \r\nin new footage.  Soon they\'ll be re-cutting all re-releases.  Here are \r\nsome ideas I\'ve had:\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nCasablanca – Now with 45 minutes of added footage.  Did you always wonder \r\nwhat happened to Rick\'s Piano Player Sam?  Now you can find out, because \r\nwe\'ve used breakthrough computer technology to digitally (not analogally) \r\nrecreate Sam.  Follow Sam on his adventures in Casablanca without Rick and \r\nElsa for 45 minutes after Rick and Claude Reins walk off into the fog.  \r\nWhat will happen?  What excitement!  Will Rick return for his good buddy?  \r\nSee the movie the way it was meant to be seen, before the racist censors \r\nsaid that Sam was just a minor character and that his story wasn\'t \r\nimportant enough to come to a complete conclusion.  We\'ve corrected that \r\nwrong, also we\'ve enhanced the movie by creating a bold new print: IN \r\nCOLOR and we\'ve substituted that boring soundtrack with what the creators \r\nintended: music by Queen and some replacement singer singing Queen\'s \r\nsongs, because Freddy is Dead (long live Freddy, he really was the best \r\nrock singer of the 80s).  In Theaters: October 31st, 2001.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nCitizen Kane – Do you find Orson Welles 1941 classic boring and \r\ndepressing?  We do too.  We\'ve taken the film and restored it to all of \r\nit\'s glory.  Kane no longer looses his bid for governor, his wife and son \r\ndon\'t die in a car accident and we\'ve cut out all that boring shit about \r\nRosebud.  Who really cares about that anyway.  We\'ve also added a new \r\ncharacter: Fonzie.  Watch as Governor Kane and Fonzie take on the city \r\nbosses in New York.  Watch as happily married Kane envy\'s the Fonze\'s \r\nability to pick up chicks.  (please note in 1941, the word chick still \r\nmeant prostitute, Fonze would actually be paying these women).  We\'ve \r\nfreshened up the print (it looked too dark and depressing) and we\'ve added \r\na new soundtrack by the Dixie Chicks, because we like their Dixie Tits.  \r\nComing soon to a theater near you!\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nPearl Harbor – The best movie of the otts is back again, we command you to \r\nsee it again.  We\'ve added three more hours detailing the lives of the \r\nparents of members of the love triangle.  Guess what!  They were involved \r\nin a love triangle too, what incredible irony!  We\'ve also cut out that \r\nbattle scene because what\'s really important in a movie about Pearl Harbor \r\nis what happened between Ben Affleck and Kate Breckentits.  This is what \r\nAmerican History is all about.  For example, the Vietnam War is only a \r\nmetaphor for Ben\'s fight with alcoholism and the collapse of Silicon \r\nValley is really just symbolic of Kate\'s rise to stardom.  You can learn \r\neverything from Hollywood and the Star System.  And now you can see Pearl \r\nHarbor again, for the first time.  You will be supplied with an adult \r\ndiaper so that you won\'t have to leave the theater and interrupt your \r\npearl harbor experience.  Armed guards will help you with the diaper and \r\nensure that you stay seated the entire time so that you too can enjoy \r\nMichael Bay\'s epic: Pearl Harbor (voted best movie of all time by every \r\nmajor film critic, including Thunt).\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nWow, what amazing and exciting films we have to look forward to.  I just \r\ncan\'t wait for these hot new releases, because I\'m an ignorant shithead \r\nand don\'t realize that I could just walk two blocks to the video store and \r\nrent them for three bucks.   I\'d rather pay eight bucks to see them in the \r\ntheater, because of 3 more scenes that fuck up the pace of the film and \r\nthat cool scene where they inserted my favorite character into the \r\nbackdrop so that there is only ten minutes when Affleck isn\'t on screen \r\nand that\'s when that big boat is sinking.  I wish they\'d cut that part out \r\ntoo.  Who really gives a shit about boats sinking.  I want to see people \r\ndancing and fucking around parachutes.  That\'s what I\'m all about. \r\n<BR><BR>\r\n', '', 20010915003655, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (279, 'Thunt.net launches WTC Coverage', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', 'Thunt.net is launching our full WTC Coverage from the TNMC (<a href="http://thunt.net/photo/index.php3?id=55">Thunt.Net \r\nMobile Command</a>).  More information, photos, news, videos, etc will be \r\navailable at a constantly updated website: <a \r\nhref=http://thunt.net/wtc/>http://thunt.net/wtc/</a>.\r\n<br><br>\r\nDon\'t forget to click on the article below entitled "The Begining of the \r\nEnd" to get an idea of what we\'ve been up to today at TNCC (Thunt.Net \r\nCommand Center).\r\n', '', 20010912024033, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (281, 'Équipage De Thunt', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '<br><b>more info on the WTC at: <a \r\nhref="http://thunt.net/wtc/">http://thunt.net/wtc/</a>\r\n<BR>\r\nmore info on Équipage De Thunt at: <a href=http://thunt.net/wanted/>http://thunt.net/wanted/</a></B>\r\n<BR><br>\r\nAttention Thunt.net readers.  I have received a top secret report from a \r\nsource who calls himself LampshadeMan.  Here is the report in it\'s \r\nentirety:\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nFor the last six months I have been infiltrating a terrorist group known \r\nas Équipage De Thunt or "Thunt Crew".  They do not know that I am a spy \r\n(or a ninja).  If they found out they would expose the fact that I am a \r\nhermaphrodite.  \r\n<BR><BR>\r\nA few weeks ago, I was at a party [location deleted].  It was there that I \r\nlearned about another party, a party far more sinister and downright \r\nevil.  I was invited to this party.  The "Thunt Crew" was not.  I knew \r\nthat this would be bad, worse than anything I have ever seen before, \r\nhorrifying and terrifying even.  \r\n<BR><BR>\r\nWhen I arrived at the party I knew that something bad would happen.  I \r\njust didn\'t know how far they would take it.  Later I found their plans, \r\nshowing that they took it as far as they could.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n<B>Excerpt from Équipage De Thunt Plans: I.  The Padre will go in first, disguised as a Swedish Nun.  Once inside \r\nhe will begin talking to [name deleted] and [explicative deleted] [name \r\ndeleted].  Carry out part one of the mission.</B>\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nI wasn\'t able to recognize him in his disguise.  But I was able to \r\nrecognize what he had done.  I noticed that the punch tasted a little off, \r\njudging by the smell it had clearly been pissed in.  Also there was  a \r\nweird smell coming from the microwave.  Further examination led me to \r\nbelieve that somehow he had shit in the microwave.  The psychokinetic \r\nabilities of this man boggles the mind.  I also found the host of the \r\nparty Codename NICE ASS? crying in the corner.  Apparently someone dressed \r\nas Robin of Locksley had told her that she was an ugly bitch and that no \r\none at the party could tell the difference between her ass and her face.  \r\nThey attempted to discover the difference by seeing which end shit came \r\nout of, but it turned out that shit came out of her mouth as well as her \r\nass.  The loveable rouge then disappeared to Sherwood forest, but I knew \r\nthat he was not gone yet.  \r\n<BR><BR>\r\nI heard a loud crash coming from the roof and I knew that the party was \r\nnot over yet.  I later learned that the crash was part of Thunt Crew plan II. \r\n<BR><BR>\r\n<B>Excerpt from Équipage De Thunt Plans: II. Odd Job will be dropped by helicopter piloted by Swoop onto the roof \r\nof the house.  He will then hack into their communications and force them \r\nto listen to Britney\'s new album again and again and again.</B>\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nSoon the air was filled with screaming and I noticed a crowd of people \r\ncoming towards me.  They were rushing by me to get out the door.  They \r\njumped out windows and bashed themselves on the head with beer bottles in \r\nan attempt to block out all consciousness.  I then heard the sound.  The \r\nsound of a poppy teenage blonde screaming at the top of her lungs.  You \r\nguessed it, it was Britney Spears.  Her lyrics were horrible and her music \r\nwas stolen from N-Sync.  I was horrified at the sound and fled the \r\nbuilding.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\nI was just in time to see The Padre and Odd Job holding on to a rope \r\nladder attached to a Helicopter flown by Swoop.  The helicopter was \r\nvirtually silent and I believe it was one of those CIA Black Helicopters, \r\nbut I\'ll never know for sure.  They flew off into the night leaving the \r\nparty destroyed and no clues to where they were headed or who financed \r\ntheir operation.  I knew it had to be Thunt.  He\'s the only one who could \r\nmastermind this kind of operation.  I had to find him and stop him so I \r\nwent to GUYS (with guns) and told them what I knew about Équipage De \r\nThunt.  They believed that I had helped with their operations and told me \r\nthey were looking for me.  That is why I had to go underground, to further \r\nmy attempts to join Équipage De Thunt, and to destroy their evil leader.  \r\nI will post more as soon as I can.  Au revoir, LampshadeMan.\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n<hr noshade>\r\n<BR>\r\nI attempted to contact the members of Équipage De Thunt.  They claimed \r\nthat they were playing Scrabble from 10:00 pm until 2:00 am.  I didn\'t \r\nbelieve them, but they did have photographic evidence: (<a \r\nhref=http://thunt.net/photo/index.php3?id=57>click here</a>).  Although \r\nI\'m not sure if it\'s real.  After what I saw, I\'m not sure if anything is \r\nreal anymore.<BR><BR>\r\n\r\n', '', 20010915190612, 'normal', '');
INSERT INTO thuntnet_archive VALUES (282, 'Shocking Photos!', 'Thomas Hunt', 'thunt@thunt.net', '<table><tr bgcolor=#0066CC><td><font class=normal><font color=white>\r\n<b>&nbsp;&nbsp;ATTACK UNDER AMERICA: <a href=http://thunt.net/wanted/><font class=normal><font color=#CCCCCC>GUYS WANTED MOST</font></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>\r\n</font></td></tr></table>\r\n<br>\r\nThunt.net Exclusive:  GUYS with Guns have announced today that they have \r\nlocated the two of the possible locations of the evil terrorist \r\norganization Équipage De Thunt.  Unfortunately for the GUYS, Équipage De \r\nThunt was well aware of their aerial hi-jinks and was able to escape with \r\ngreat ease.  The photos were later intercepted by EDT agents and supplied \r\nvia messenger to Thunt.net.  Here they are:\r\n<BR><BR>\r\n<center>\r\n	<a href=http://thunt.net/images/map/map.jpg>\r\n	<img src=http://thunt.net/images/map/map_small.jpg border=1><br>\r\n	click to enlarge</a><br>\r\n</center>\r\n<br>\r\n', '', 20010917150338, 'normal', '');
